cheddar cheese
cream of chicken soup
butter
salt
pepper
onion
directions:
mix everything together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
top with 1/4 cup melted butter and 2 cups crushed cornflakes, mixed together.
bake at 350° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
condensed milk
cold water
instant vanilla pudding
whipping cream
vanilla wafers
bananas
directions:
in large bowl, combine milk and water.
add pudding mix.
beat well until blended.
fold in whipping cream.
spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart round glass bowl.
top with 1/3 each of the vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
repeat layers twice, ending with pudding mixture.
chill thoroughly.
garnish, if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn meal
flour
baking soda
buttermilk
salt
onion
directions:
combine corn meal, flour and baking soda in a mixing bowl. stir in buttermilk and beat until batter is smooth.
stir in salt and onion.
drop heaping tablespoonfuls of batter into a deep fryer; fry until golden brown.
drain on paper toweling before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onion
clove garlic
bell pepper
celery
tomato
tomato sauce
mushrooms
corn
olives
egg noodles
cheese
directions:
brown beef.
cook pepper, celery and onion in a small amount of fat, then add to ground beef and cook about 20 minutes.
cook noodles according to package directions.
combine noodles with meat mixture.
layer meat and noodle mixture with grated cheese and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lemon jell-o
boiling water
pineapple
cream cheese
sugar
pecans
directions:
mix pineapple and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil. reduce heat and simmer on stove 15 minutes.
remove from heat and cool.
mix jell-o and boiling water.
stir in softened cream cheese and mix well, then add pineapple and nuts.
chill until thickened, then fold in cool whip.
put in pyrex dish and chill until firm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cherry pie filling
pineapple
marshmallows
bananas
pecans
directions:
pour all ingredients into a large bowl and stir.
mix well. this salad may be served second day, if not used the first.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread crumbs
parsley flakes
garlic
onion
tomato sauce
parmesan cheese
salt
directions:
you will also need wooden toothpicks.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vanilla pudding
cream cheese
milk
powdered sugar
oreos
whipped topping
directions:
in deep bowl, put pudding, cream cheese and 1/2 cup of milk. mix until creamy with hand mixer.
add powdered sugar and mix thoroughly, then add remaining milk, 1/2 cup at a time, and mix until creamy.
crumble enough oreo cookies to line bottom of dish as a crust in a lasagna pan.
add the pudding mix and top with whipped topping.
refrigerate until serving.
prior to serving, crumble a few more oreos on the top to provide a crisp, crunchy taste.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion soup mix
water
cream of mushroom soup
directions:
mix dry and liquid ingredients in crock-pot.
cut steak into small pieces.
add to other ingredients.
cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
serve over mashed potatoes, noodles or rice. serves 4 to 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
cream of chicken soup
cream of celery soup
pet milk
sage
cornbread mix
chicken broth
directions:
put chicken in large casserole dish.
spread chicken soup, celery soup and milk over chicken.
mix all these well with chicken.
mix remaining ingredients and add last for topping. (can use cornmeal and egg with sage and chicken broth instead of packaged mixes.
add cornbread last.) bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until bread is golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
bananas
brown sugar
oil
salt
milk
flour
baking soda
baking powder
apple
nuts
directions:
combine eggs, banana, sugar, oil and milk.
in a separate bowl mix flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
add to banana mixture.
fold in apple and nuts.
pour batter into 3 small greased and floured pans or two (9 x 5-inch) pans.
bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
cool in pans 10 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crackers
celery
green pepper
eggs
onion
tomato juice
mayonnaise
directions:
crush the soda crackers in a large bowl.
mix all vegetables together in another bowl, then mix tomato juice and mayonnaise with all the vegetables.
pour this mixture over the crushed crackers. let all of this mixture stand in the refrigerator overnight.
serve on crackers or on a bed of lettuce.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
crisco
eggs
flour
baking powder
baking soda
salt
buttermilk
almond flavoring
vanilla
directions:
cream sugar and shortening.
beat in eggs 1 at a time.
sift dry ingredients together.
blend in alternating with buttermilk. beat well.
add almond and vanilla.
mix well.
bake in greased and floured bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
semi-sweet chocolate morsels
condensed milk
salt
vanilla extract
nuts
directions:
in heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt morsels with sweetened condensed milk. stir in vanilla and spread evenly onto wax paper lined 8-inch square pan. chill 2 hours or until set. turn fudge onto cutting board, peel off paper and cut into squares. cover and store at room temperature.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn oil
sugar
cider vinegar
wine vinegar
water
salt
black pepper
cucumbers
onions
directions:
pour all ingredients over noodles and let marinate in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
wash cucumbers and leave skins on. cut cucumbers in half lengthwise, then slice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornbread mix
onion
green pepper
tomatoes
bacon
velveeta cheese
salad dressing
mustard
salt
directions:
mix well and let set overnight.
will make 2 quarts and 1 pint.
you can cut this in half.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of mushroom soup
milk
rice
ham
directions:
mix all ingredients in 8 x 8-inch pan.
bake at 375° for 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
pecans
cooking oats
baking powder
salt
cinnamon
eggs
zucchini
oil
directions:
preheat oven to 400°.
grease muffin cups.
in large bowl, mix the first 7 ingredients.
beat eggs; stir in oil and zucchini. stir all together until moistened.
bake for 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
italian dressing
bread crumbs
spaghetti sauce
onion
clove garlic
noodles
mozzarella cheese
directions:
dip chicken in italian dressing, then bread crumbs.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
add a layer of mozzarella cheese the last few minutes (3 to 5) of cooking.
cook jar of spaghetti sauce over low heat.
add onion and garlic clove.
remove when finished cooking.
cook spaghetti noodles.
prepare plate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
cherry pie filling
yellow cake mix
margarine
directions:
spread crushed pineapple in the bottom of baking dish. spread cherry pie filling over the pineapple.
spread yellow cake mix over pineapple and cherry filling.
melt margarine and drizzle over the other ingredients.
bake at 350° until golden brown on top.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
cocoa
salt
baking soda
vinegar
oil
cold water
directions:
mix all ingredients together.
pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sugar
vanilla
egg yolks
soda
baking powder
flour
directions:
spread out on cookie sheet and make edges up side.
cover with cherry pie filling.
beat egg whites until stiff.
add 6 tablespoons sugar.
cover filling and sprinkle with ground nuts. bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
raspberries
sugar
vodka
directions:
in a 1-gallon jar fitted with a lid, combine the raspberries, sugar and the gin.
stir the mixture well.
secure the lid.
let mixture stand, stirring it once a week, for 4 months.
strain the mixture through a cheesecloth lined sieve into a pitcher, pressing hard on the solids.
return it to the jar.
makes about 4 cups.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg whites
salt
cream of tartar
sugar
whipping cream
fruit of your choice
directions:
line cookie sheet with wax paper; grease lightly.
draw 8-inch circle in middle of sheet.
beat egg whites until foamy.
add salt and cream of tartar; beat until stiff, glossy peaks form.
add sugar gradually; beat 2 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
kidney beans
onions
tomatoes
tomato paste
chili powder
sugar
salt
pepper
cheddar cheese
directions:
brown beef and onions.
drain.
add all ingredients.
cover and simmer 45 minutes.
add cheese just before serving while hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breast
tomato sauce
onion flakes
broth mix
water
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
place chicken in baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
in a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
cover and bake 30 minutes.
remove cover; continue baking 30 minutes longer.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
cream of celery soup
cream of chicken soup
water
veg-all
directions:
mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes
head lettuce
grated cheese
fritos
dressing
beans
directions:
drain beans.
mix all ingredients together, except fritos. add fritos just before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef
onion
salt
pepper
lemon juice
sour cream
directions:
slice meat in julienne strips.
add sliced onion, salt and pepper to taste.
sprinkle lemon juice over mixture and mix in sour cream.
chill well.
serve in crystal bowl with crackers. great appetizer!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
stalk celery
water
condensed cream
herb seasoned croutons
onion
margarine
water
directions:
place chicken in ungreased 2-quart casserole or 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
toss croutons, celery and onion with the 1/2 cup water and the margarine until croutons are moistened.
reserve about 1 1/2 cups of this stuffing.
spread remaining stuffing over chicken.
mix soup with 1 1/2 cups water; pour over stuffing.
top with reserved stuffing.
cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
turkey
cream of mushroom soup
cream of celery soup
cream of chicken soup
rice
directions:
mix together and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg
flour
oil
buttermilk
sugar
baking powder
baking soda
salt
directions:
beat egg until fluffy.
beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
for thinner pancakes, add 1/4 cup milk.
cook on griddle or skillet until golden brown.
makes about 9 pancakes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cottage cheese
o
directions:
you may use any combination of jell-o and fruit you want. (lime jell-o and pineapple, orange jell-o and mandarin oranges.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
linguine
tomato
cucumber
onion
italian dressing
salad supreme
directions:
for option, try broccoli.
mix all together.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
coffee
baking soda
raisins

nuts
flour
salt
directions:
you will need 3 coffee cans.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
margarine
flour
directions:
mix in a bowl the cream cheese, margarine or butter and flour. wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
divide in quarters and roll each into 8-inch circles.
melt 1 stick of butter and brush on dough, then sprinkle filling.
cut each circle into 8 triangles, rolling large end to pointed end and pinch ends.
beat egg yolk with 2 tablespoons water and brush on top.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
shortening
sugar
eggs
flour
cream of tartar
soda
salt
sugar
cinnamon
directions:
heat oven to 400°.
mix thoroughly the butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs. blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
shape dough by rounded teaspoonful into balls.
mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
roll balls in mixture and place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set. remove immediately from baking sheet.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lemon lime soda
white wine
lemon
lime
directions:
chill ingredients; pour over ice and sliced fruit.
makes 16 punch cups.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oreo cookies
margarine
powdered sugar
cream cheese
instant chocolate pudding
milk
directions:
crush oreos and layer 1/2 on bottom of glass bowl or flower pot. cream together margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese. add cool whip, dry pudding mix
and milk, mixing well.
pour on top of oreos. add remaining crushed oreos to top.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
cheese
oatmeal
egg
catsup
mustard
onion
salt
pepper
parmesan cheese
directions:
combine all ingredients except parmesan cheese.
mix thoroughly.
pack lightly into an 8-inch square baking pan.
bake at 350° for 20 minutes. sprinkle top with cheese.
bake 10 minutes longer.
let stand for 5 minutes. cut into squares.
yields 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
eggs
milk
butter
onion
cheddar cheese
chopped spinach
directions:
in a large bowl, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
stir in beaten eggs, milk and butter.
add remaining ingredients and stir until moistened.
pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
cut into 1-inch squares.
makes 2 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork
onion
dill pickle
sugar
brown sugar
ketchup
mustard
directions:
mix altogether in a baking dish.
bake at 350° for 20 minutes. spread bacon strips across (optional).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg yolks
sugar
vanilla
almond
baking powder
egg whites
graham cracker crumbs
nuts
whipping cream
directions:
mix together egg yolks, sugar, vanilla, almond and baking powder.
set aside.
whip egg whites until very stiff and fold into yolk mixture.
also fold in graham cracker crumbs and nuts. pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
cool.
whip the whipping cream and spread over cool cake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ranch style red beans
tomato
onion
grated cheese
pepper
directions:
at the last minute before serving, add 1 cup catalina dressing and about 1/2 bag crushed fritos.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef
fat
onions
clove garlic
catsup
worcestershire sauce
vinegar
brown sugar
paprika
salt
dry mustard
red pepper
water
flour
water
parsley
noodles
directions:
cut beef into 1-inch pieces and brown in hot fat.
add onion and garlic; brown lightly.
mix together catsup, worcestershire sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, paprika, salt, mustard and pepper. stir in with meat.
add 3 cups water; cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
thicken with mixture of 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water.
pour goulash over cooked noodles and garnish with parsley. serves 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn muffin
eggs
cottage cheese
onion
broccoli
butter
salt
directions:
mix cottage cheese and salt.
add eggs.
mix broccoli, onion and butter.
then add cornmeal mix.
beat until smooth.
bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
orange juice
lemon juice
confectioners sugar
directions:
prepare cake mix according to package directions. place 1 teaspoon of batter in each well-greased miniature muffin pans. bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
salt
eggs
milk
butter
corn
directions:
mix all ingredients together.
bake at 375° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
swiss
ham
paprika
white wine
whipping cream
flour
salt
pepper
butter
chicken
directions:
pound breasts until thin.
lay slice of cheese and ham on each breast; roll and insert toothpicks to secure.
mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag.
put breasts in bag and shake to coat.
melt butter in frying pan and brown chicken rolls on all sides.
add white wine and bouillon cube.
cover and simmer 30 minutes.
remove chicken from pan.
add cream to pan and cook on medium-high for 3 minutes until smooth and creamy.
pour over chicken.
serves 3.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn
corn
margarine
corn bread
sour cream
directions:
in a large mixing bowl, mix well the 2 cans of corn, margarine (melted) and the corn bread mix (dry).
stir in approximately 3/4 of the sour cream.
mix well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
instant coconut pudding
boiling water
poppy seed
oil
eggs
directions:
mix boiling
water and poppy seed together.
set aside. mix remaining
ingredients.
add seed and water mixture.
pour into 2 greased
loaf
pans.
bake at 325° for 1 hour.
freezes well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
cocoa
flour
sugar
soda
salt
eggs
buttermilk
vanilla
directions:
in a saucepan combine butter, cocoa and 1 cup water.
bring to a boil and stir constantly.
remove from heat.
in a large bowl sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
add cocoa mixture; mix until blended. pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
immediately pour frosting over brownies; spread evenly.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes
eggs
grated cheese
english peas
miracle
bacon bits
directions:
layer all ingredients in order listed.
cover with miracle whip mayonnaise and sprinkle bacon bits on top.
refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onions
celery
green bell pepper
cumin
garlic
chili powder
salt
velveeta cheese
ro-tel tomatoes
chopped lettuce
tomatoes
corn chips
directions:
combine first 7 ingredients in crock-pot; mix well.
add salt and pepper.
cook on low for 3 to 4 hours or until done to taste. heat cheese and tomatoes in saucepan until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
layer lettuce, ground beef sauce, tomatoes, cheese sauce and crushed corn chips on individual plates.
yield:
12 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
refrigerator pizza crust
margarine
pizza seasonings
mozzarella cheese
pizza sauce
directions:
grease 1 large cookie sheet and unroll pizza dough, cutting the rectangle in half crosswise, then cutting 8 (1-inch) strips. place strips apart on cookie sheet and brush with margarine. sprinkle evenly with seasoning and put into 350° oven for 11 to 17 minutes.
bring out long enough to sprinkle cheese on top and return to melt.
serve immediately with warm pizza sauce to dip. makes 16 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
yeast
water
milk
sugar
shortening
salt
egg whites
flour
directions:
put sugar over yeast in lukewarm water and let foam.
scald milk, sugar, oleo and salt.
when cool, add dissolved yeast.
fold in egg whites, stir in flour.
dough should be soft.
do not add more flour.
let stand covered until double in size.
stir down and put covered in refrigerator.
let set overnight.
bake in muffin tins.
two small balls dipped in melted oleo forms one roll.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vanilla ice cream
graham cracker pie crust
strawberry topping
chocolate sundae syrup
nuts
whipped cream
maraschino cherries
directions:
in a mixing bowl, stir slightly softened ice cream until smooth.
spoon the ice cream into the pie crust and cover.
place pie in freezer for several hours, until hard.
remove pie from freezer and let stand for 10 minutes to soften.
spoon strawberry topping onto serving plate.
cut pie and place on top of strawberry topping.
garnish with chocolate sundae syrup and other toppings, as desired.
sprinkle with nuts and a cherry.
return to freezer.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oranges
cranberry sauce
pear halves
apple
sugar
raisins
pecans
vinegar
ground cinnamon
ground ginger
directions:
combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
reduce heat and simmer until thick.
let cool and store in refrigerator.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
butter
powdered sugar
salt
flour
water
vanilla
ground almonds
powdered sugar
directions:
cream shortening and butter until light and fluffy.
add powdered sugar and salt.
mix well.
stir in flour.
stir in water, vanilla and almonds.
shape dough into 1-inch balls.
place on ungreased baking sheets.
flatten slightly.
bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
dredge cookies in powdered sugar while they're still warm.
yields about 8 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cabbage
green onions
carrot
green pepper
radishes
cucumber
dressing
directions:
combine all ingredients except dressing.
cover and chill. toss with dressing just before serving.
yields 8 to 10 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white corn syrup
brown sugar
salt
butter
vanilla
eggs
pecans
directions:
mix all ingredients.
bake 45 minutes in preheated oven at 350°. decorate with whole pecan halves.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flank steak
salad oil
vinegar
clove garlic
salt
directions:
place steak in shallow pan.
combine oil, vinegar and garlic. pour over steak.
cover and let stand in refrigerator for 3 hours or better yet overnight, turning several times.
preheat broiler. broil steak 3-inches from heat, about 5 minutes.
season.
turn; broil 3 minutes.
add more seasoning.
remove to cutting board. carve very thin slices diagonally across the grain.
serves 4 to 5.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
graham cracker crumbs
chocolate chips
butterscotch chips
walnuts
coconut
condensed milk
directions:
melt oleo in a pan.
add graham cracker.
mix and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13 inch greased pan.
layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, walnuts if desired and shredded coconut.
pour condensed milk on top and bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
cool and cut into bars.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sharp cheese
macaroni
condensed cream
pimento
mayonnaise
onion
directions:
mix all ingredients.
before baking, cover with crumbled cheese crackers and dot with butter.
bake at 325° for 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
unsweetened chocolate
flour
baking powder
salt
butter
brown sugar
eggs
vanilla
sour cream
boiling water
directions:
melt chocolate in small bowl over hot water; cool.
grease and flour 2 to 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
sift flour, baking soda and salt onto wax paper.
beat butter until soft in large bowl.
add brown sugar and eggs; beat with mixer at high speed until light and fluffy (5 minutes).
beat in vanilla and chocolate.
stir in dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream.
beat well with wooden spoon after each addition.
stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
pour into pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. cool pans on rack for 10 minutes; turn out on racks.
cool completely and ice with chocolate fudge frosting.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
egg
margarine
sugar
eggs
cream cheese
directions:
mix the cake mix, egg and margarine good and press into a 9 x 12-inch sheet cake pan.
next, mix and cream together good the sugar, 2 eggs and sour cream.
spread on top of cake mixture.
bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
cut when cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
boneless chuck roast
ketchup
water
mustard
lemon juice
vinegar
onion
directions:
cook on top of stove several hours.
(meat will eventually shred.)
cook on low to medium heat.
if liquid disappears, add water and ketchup (if needed).
cut beef in pieces and put into pot; add all ingredients to the beef.
cook 3 to 4 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
vegetable oil
onions
mushrooms
cornstarch
pepper
water
yogurt
noodles
garlic
chicken broth
directions:
slice chicken into thin strips.
in a large skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. add onions.
saute 2 minutes.
add mushrooms and saute 3 minutes longer.
remove vegetables from skillet; reserve.
heat remaining oil in skillet. add chicken and garlic.
cook as for stir-fry. return vegetables to skillet.
add broth and pepper.
in a small bowl, combine water and cornstarch.
stir into skillet mixture. over medium heat, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. remove from heat and stir in yogurt.

keeps forever in the fridge.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

pecan
eggs
water
oil
directions:
beat eggs, water and oil until blended well. add cake mix and mix well. add icing to batter and blend with a spoon. bake in greased and floured tube pan 1 hour at 350°. cool in pan at least 15 minutes. (you may use a bundt pan.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cookie crust
milk
marshmallows
heavy cream
creme de cacao
creme
directions:

add marshmallows and stir until melted.
cool thoroughly.
combine whipped cream, creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
fold into cooled marshmallow mixture.
pour into chilled crust and freeze.
serve frozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
salad oil
sugar
brown sugar
vanilla
eggs
flour
soda
salt
chocolate chips
directions:
blend together the salad oil, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla. fold in the beaten eggs. sift together the flour, soda and salt. add the chocolate chips. drop by rounded teaspoonful on nongreased pan. bake at 375°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oleo
cocoa
sugar
nuts
flour
baking powder
eggs
vanilla
directions:
melt oleo and cocoa over low heat.
add flour, sugar and baking powder; stir to blend.
add eggs and vanilla; blend.
add nuts. pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
coconut
confectioners sugar
margarine
vanilla
condensed milk
paraffin
chocolate chips
directions:

melt paraffin and chocolate chips in top of double boiler over low heat, stirring frequently.
cut coconut mixture into small squares and dip into chocolate (use toothpicks).
let cool on waxed paper.
store in refrigerator.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pistachio pudding
fruit cocktail
pineapple
pack black walnuts
bowl
directions:
mix all these together, chill overnight and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
mayonnaise
mustard
curry powder
salt
chicken
celery
green onion
slivered almonds
raisins
directions:
combine 2 tablespoons juice drained from pineapple with mayonnaise, mustard, curry powder and salt.
set aside.
cut chicken into small slivers and mix with remaining ingredients. add flavored mayonnaise and blend well.
serve with lettuce, pineapple and green grapes, if desired.
(can be made ahead.) serves 4.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
shortening
egg yolk
vinegar
water
directions:
mix flour, salt and shortening.
add egg, vinegar and water, mixing with a fork until flour is moistened.
this is a crust that you can play with.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg yolks
salt
dry mustard
lemon juice
shot of tabasco
butter
directions:
put eggs, salt, mustard, lemon juice and tabasco in blender and blend for 3 minutes.
heat butter until melted and hot.
do not burn.
add butter, in a steady stream, to blender while blender running.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
brown sugar
light karo syrup
salt
baking soda
vanilla
popcorn
directions:
melt margarine; add sugar, karo syrup and salt.
bring to rolling boil and cook for 5 minutes.
remove from heat; add soda and vanilla.
mix well.
pour over popped popcorn and mix well. place pan in oven at 200° and bake for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
onion
green pepper
salad oil
vinegar
sugar
tomato soup
salt
directions:
cook carrots and cool.
put onion in bottom of bowl.
add green peppers, then place carrots on top of peppers.
combine oil, vinegar, sugar, tomato soup, salt and pepper and cook well.
pour heated sauce over the top.
cover bowl and refrigerate 24 hours. when serving, mix all together and serve cold.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lean ground beef
onions
clove garlic
spaghetti sauce
tomatoes
mushrooms
macaroni shells
sour cream
provolone cheese
mozzarella cheese
directions:
cook beef in 2 tablespoons oil and drain well.
add onions, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
mix and simmer 20 minutes.
meanwhile, cook shells; drain and rinse.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hamburg
dill pickles
oleo
tomato sauce
salt
pepper
onion
directions:
prepare hamburg for patties with salt and a little pepper. make individual patties.
place a slice of dill pickle and a thin slice of onion.
fold patty over and seal.
brown in a little oleo or shortening.
pour the tomato sauce over the patties. simmer 30 to 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork
brown sugar
ground beef
onions
bell peppers
ketchup
grated cheese
worcestershire sauce
bacon
directions:

pour into a large casserole that has been sprayed with vegetable spray.

bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
parmesan cheese
water
red wine vinegar
worcestershire sauce
olive oil
clove garlic
dry mustard
romaine lettuce
croutons
directions:
combine all ingredients together except lettuce in food processor and blend until smooth.
pour over lettuce, tossing well.

yields 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chocolate
salt
hot milk
nutmeg
sugar
boiling water
hot coffee
whipped cream
directions:
in top of double boiler, combine chocolate, sugar and salt. stir in boiling water.
over simmering water, heat until chocolate is melted.
add milk and coffee; stirring.
mix in nutmeg.
top with whipped cream.
sprinkle with instant coffee, if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
strawberry gelatin
pineapple
pecans
bananas
apple
marshmallows
directions:
prepare jello as directed. chill until semi-jelled.
add remaining ingredients.
stir and pour into 6-cup mold. refrigerate until set, about 3 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

flour
margarine
salt
directions:
blend as for pie dough. roll into a 13-inch circle and place in 12 inch pizza pan. crimp edges. prick dough all over w/fork to prevent bubbling. bake at 425° 12-15 min. (for sweeter pizza, you may use prepared or homemade sugar cookie dough.) cool completely.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
country
eggs

cocoa
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
butter
cocoa
vanilla flavoring
water
buttermilk
eggs
soda
directions:
mix sugar and flour.
in saucepan combine butter, cocoa and water.
bring to a boil; pour over sugar and flour.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
flour
soda
salt
cinnamon
oil
pumpkin
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

parsley
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

oil
water

directions:

let cool on wire rack.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

chicken

pepper

flour

frozen broccoli

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

(strips will be crisp when cooled.)

about 1 cup.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

soda
directions:

add eggs and vanilla; beat well. add sifted dry ingredients.

directions:

cut in shortening.
blend in egg, milk and vanilla.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

oven
for about 10 minutes at 350°.
watch them closely.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

gradually
beat
in
1
1/2
boxes confectioners sugar (when mixture gets

refrigerate
until
mixture
is
firm. form into small balls.
melt
over low heat the milk chocolate and paraffin pushed into

the balls in chocolate;

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion

chill.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

vanilla

sift sugar, flour and cocoa.
add eggs and milk.
cook until thick.
add vanilla and butter.
use more flour for pie filling.<|endofrecipe|>

cheddar
tomatoes

yields 4 to 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cocoa
salt
boiling water
butter
vanilla
directions:
combine sugar, cocoa and salt, mixing well.
add boiling water and butter; blend.

beat until of spreading consistency.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cover potatoes with cold water in a pot and bring to a boil.

drain and set aside.

water

salt

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
flour
cornstarch
salt
water
egg yolks
margarine
lemon juice
egg whites
sugar
cream of tartar
directions:
mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat until thickened.
stir constantly.
remove from heat and pour mixture into baked pie shell.
beat egg whites and sugar, adding cream of tartar until stiff.
spread on pie and bake until brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

water

avocado

directions:

ham

cheddar cheese
directions:

can use any meats and cheeses.<|endofrecipe|>

green peppers

pepper
sugar
ginger
water
cornstarch

blend cornstarch with beef bouillon.
add to steak mixture.
cook 10 minutes until thickened. serve over rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

5 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion salt

mozzarella cheese

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion
worcestershire sauce
miracle
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs
green food

directions:
blend to moisten, then beat for 2 minutes.
(optional: a few drops of green food dye for a richer green color.) pour about 3/4 batter into a greased and floured bundt pan.
with remaining batter, add 3/4 cup hershey's chocolate syrup.

(the chocolate batter will fall to the bottom.)

when cool, dust with confectioners sugar.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
butter
milk
cocoa
peanut butter
oatmeal
vanilla
nuts
directions:

panboil 1 minute.

eggs

flour

baking powder
directions:
in bowl, cream the sugars and the shortening.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

reduce heat to low.

remove from heat.
quickly stir in marshmallows, chips, peanuts and vanilla until melted and smooth.

refrigerate until firm.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

o

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
walnuts
unflavored gelatin
water
sugar
vanilla
powdered sugar
directions:
chop walnuts fine.
sprinkle about 1 cup evenly in 9-inch square pan.
set remaining walnuts aside.
combine gelatin and 1/2 cup of the water in measuring cup; set aside to soften.
in 2-quart glass measuring cup with handle, combine remaining 3/4 cup water and sugar.
microwave at high for 5 minutes.
stir well until sugar dissolves.
microwave at high for 7 to 8 minutes or until mixture reaches 234°.
stir in softened gelatin; let stand until slightly cooled (about 130°).
stir in vanilla. empty mixture into large bowl of electric mixer.
beat at high speed until mixture is very fluffy and increased 4 to 5 times in volume, about 12 to 15 minutes.
turn into walnut-coated pan and sprinkle remaining walnuts on top.
let stand at room temperature several hours or overnight until mixture is firm and set.
use a sharp knife dipped in powdered sugar to cut mixture into 1-inch squares. roll sides in walnuts remaining in pan and additional powdered sugar, if desired.
makes about 1 1/2 pounds.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
sugar
applesauce
nuts
raisins
flour
cocoa
cinnamon
cloves
directions:

mix ingredients.
beat and pour into prepared pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

flour
eggs

vanilla
cinnamon
powdered sugar
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

in medium saucepan, melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth.

reserve 1/4 cup cheddar cheese.

bake 15 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
directions:
mix and serve over ice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs.

cook on low heat until

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

take a spoon and make a hole in flour about the size of your fist.

(dough will be sticky and have the consistency of a very thick batter.)
bake in preheated 425° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until bottom of biscuit turns brown. place under broiler for few seconds until tops turn light brown. remove from oven.

good!

no messy hands!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

vanilla

sugars
and margarine.
add peanut butter; mix thoroughly.

eggs
and mix well.

add
alternately
with

and mix well.
drop a heaping teaspoonful for

3

in an electric skillet, heat 1/4-inch oil to 350°.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vanilla pudding
milk
sour cream
condensed milk
bananas
vanilla wafers
directions:
mix vanilla pudding with milk until blended.
add sour cream and sweetened condensed milk.
fold in whipped topping.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

thin apples
sugar
flour
directions:
prepare pie crust as directed on box for 9-inch pie.
line plate bottom with crust.
mix sugar and flour.
mix with apples. fill apples in bottom of crust; add the blueberry filling on top of apples.
cover with top crust.

heat oven to 400°.
bake 10 minutes.
reduce to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brown sugar
flour
dry mustard
water
vinegar
raisins
directions:
combine first 3 ingredients in medium pan; stir well.
add remaining ingredients; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
serve warm over pork or ham.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
eggs
baking powder
cinnamon
salt
raisins
butter
directions:
in a large bowl, soften and cream genesis 18.
slowly beat in isaiah.
in small bowl, beat job well and add to creamed mixture. sift together 1 samuel, 1 kings, exodus and luke.
add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
fold in 2 samuel and genesis 43. grease a 9-inch tube pan with judges.

invert onto serving plate, remove waxed paper and cool completely.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
water
sugar
shortening
directions:
add flour to water a little at a time.
cook until real thick; let cool.
mix sugar and shortening together until creamy.
add flour mixture a little at a time.
beat until smooth and creamy. frosting will not get hard.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
white wine
worcestershire sauce
chicken broth
tarragon
pineapple
honey
directions:
place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
combine worcestershire sauce and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
pour over chicken.
cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
salt
salad oil
green onion
flour
milk
water
catsup
rosemary
chicken flavored
frozen artichoke
green beans
directions:
cut chicken breasts in half.
thaw frozen artichoke hearts and green beans.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
pepper
condensed cream
onion soup
sour cream
lemon juice
fresh dill
mushrooms
paprika
egg noodles
directions:
dip pieces of chicken in melted margarine, then roll pieces in crushed rice krispies.
season to taste.
place in pan lined with aluminum foil.
bake for 1 hour at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
sugar
vanilla
marshmallows
corn
directions:
melt margarine, sugar and vanilla in microwave oven.
add marshmallows and melt, stirring mixture once or twice during cooking.
pour over popcorn.
shape into balls.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
salt pork
milk
white flour
salt
directions:
parboil slices in skillet; drain skillet well before using it for frying.
heat oil in skillet until hot.
dip salt pork in flour mixture; put in skillet and fry until golden brown.
to thicken gravy, use 2 tablespoons of flour used for dredging. blend the flour and fat very well before adding milk.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
water
corn syrup
beef bouillon granules
directions:
mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator.
to use, heat a small quantity to room temperature.
feed kitten with an eye dropper.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mushrooms
vegetable oil
water
sausage
onion
garlic
frozen spinach
parmesan cheese
egg
bread crumbs
directions:
clean mushrooms and pat dry.
then rub with oil.
arrange them in a large 13 x 9-inch pan.
add water.
cook sausage until brown; remove to drain.
reserve drippings to saute onion, garlic and stems.
mix the sausage, spinach, egg, bread crumbs and parmesan. mix well, then stir in onion, garlic and stems.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bermuda onions
swiss cheese
bread
milk
butter
pepper
cream of chicken soup
soy sauce
directions:
simmer onions in butter in heavy pan on low until tender and separated.
stir constantly.
place in a 2-quart casserole. sprinkle with pepper; top with cheese.
heat soup, milk and soy sauce until blended.
pour soup mixture over all; stir gently. butter bread slices on both sides and top casserole, overlapping the slices.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
vinegar
parmesan cheese
italian seasoning
salad oil
garlic salt
directions:
combine all ingredients in a jar.
cover.
shake well.
chill. cook macaroni.
drain and cool.
mix with your favorite vegetables, broccoli, tomatoes, etc. and pour the dressing over and mix and chill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking soda
butter
buttermilk
sugar
baking powder
salt
raisins
butter
directions:
*i never buy buttermilk.
i add 1 tablespoon vinegar to 1 cup milk and let stand 5 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground sirloin
carrot
onion
potato
salt
flour
worcestershire sauce
directions:
make a large patty for each person.
place each patty separately in foil.
sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon worcestershire sauce over meat; dash with salt and pepper.
place slice of onion on top of meat.
place sliced potato on top of onion.
place sliced carrot around meat.
sprinkle with all-purpose flour, seasoning and a little more sauce over vegetables.
wrap tight in foil. bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
serve hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sour cream
mayonnaise
dry mustard
cold
american cheese
olives
directions:
combine dairy sour cream, mayonnaise and mustard.
lay ham slice flat.
spread with some of the sour cream mixture.
lay strip of american cheese on one end of ham slice.
roll jelly roll fashion.
fasten with toothpick topped with olive.
makes 24 rolls.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bacon
onion
brown sugar
cornstarch
mustard
catsup
pork
directions:
fry onion and bacon.
add remaining ingredients. bake in bean pot at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cranberries
raisins
sugar
water
ginger
cinnamon
cloves
celery
apple
directions:
cook until the berries pop the cranberries, raisins, sugar, water and spices.
add celery and apple and continue to cook until mixture thickens and apples are cooked.
makes about one quart.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion
green pepper
margarine
cream of chicken soup
mushrooms
basil

milk
cottage cheese
chicken
shredded cheese
parmesan cheese
directions:
cook and drain noodles.
cook onions and peppers in margarine until tender.
stir in soup, mushrooms, pimento, milk and basil. layer half of noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

if casserole comes from "fridge" add 15 minutes to baking time.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
salad oil
tomato sauce
sugar

salt
shells

mozzarella cheese
parsley
salt
pepper
clove garlic
tomatoes
water

bay leaf
eggs
directions:

add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, sugar, oregano, thyme, the first 1/4 teaspoon salt and bay leaf.
bring to boiling; simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
remove bay leaf.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
water
pineapple juice
ginger ale
directions:
mix kool-aid, sugar and water.
add pineapple juice and chill. (one package cherry kool-aid and one package raspberry kool-aid make a good flavor combination.
for green punch, use lemon-lime kool-aid.)

add chilled ginger ale. serve at once.
makes 50 half cup servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow corn meal
flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
milk
oil
egg
directions:

grease small baking pan.
blend all ingredients about 20 seconds.
beat 1 minute.
pour into pan. bake 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ham
heavy cream
tomato paste
egg yolks
salt
pepper
parmesan cheese
directions:
cook ziti with salt.
cut ham into little squares.
drain ziti.
grease a casserole dish.
then put one layer ziti and one layer of ham into casserole dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

flour
water

parmesan cheese
directions:
melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium heat.
stir in flour until well blended.
gradually stir in half and half, water and chicken bouillon cubes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pina colada sherbet
directions:
put sherbet in punch bowl.
pour in 7-up.
mix well and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cottage cheese
cucumber
onion
mayonnaise
vinegar
salt
directions:
mix all ingredients and serve ice cold on a bed of lettuce.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

chocolate chips
butterscotch chips
shredded coconut
walnuts
condensed milk
rice crispies
directions:
melt 1 stick of oleo in a 9 x 13 pan.
add 2 cups crushed graham crackers on top of oleo.
continue to layer the following: 1-6 oz package chocolate chips, 1 -6 oz package butterscotch chips, 1 cup shredded coconut, 3/4 cup chopped walnuts, 1 can condensed milk--pour over the top.
top with rice crispies or crushed corn flakes (a hand full).
bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
meal
eggs
buttermilk
corn
salad oil
onion
red bell pepper
hot peppers
sharp cheese
directions:
mix all of the ingredients and put into a medium sized baking skillet.
bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cranberry juice
pineapple juice
sugar
almond extract
ginger ale
directions:
mix thoroughly making sure sugar is dissolved.
serve cold. makes 1 gallon.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

nuts
semi-sweet chocolate chips
margarine
condensed milk
vanilla extract
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
prepare brownie mix as package directs. stir in nuts.
spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set.
in heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt chips and margarine with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
salt cucumbers; place in bowl for 2 hours.
wring out moisture.
mix other ingredients together in large bowl.
when cucumbers are ready, add to mixture.
let it sit for an hour; adjust seasoning.

serves 6 to 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

any wine

wash mushrooms and remove stems.
in a bowl, mix clams and wine.
cut a few mushroom stems and add 1/3 to 1/2 cup italian bread crumbs.
spoon stuffing into mushroom caps.

cook in oven 20 minutes at 375°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oil
garlic
salt
pepper
soy sauce
sugar

tomatoes

cornstarch

green onions
directions:
slice steak into narrow strips.
in skillet, brown steak in oil.
combine with garlic, salt, pepper, soy sauce and sugar in crock-pot.
cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
turn control to high.
add bean sprouts, tomatoes and green peppers.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pastry
potatoes
carrots
celery
onions
margarine
flour
chicken broth
pepper
poultry seasoning
chicken
directions:
prepare pastry; set aside.
cook potatoes and carrots until tender in one saucepan.
cook celery and onions in another pan. while vegetables are cooking, make gravy by adding flour to the butter in a small pan.
when blended, add chicken broth, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
bring to a boil.
set aside.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
syrup
sugar
salt
margarine
vanilla
pecans
shell
directions:
blend eggs slightly.
add syrup, sugar, salt, margarine and vanilla.
add nuts.
pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 12 minutes in a 375° oven, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 40 minutes or until pie is set.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter
flour
baking powder
red pepper
salt
directions:
grate cheese.
let butter soften to room temperature.
hand mix cheese and butter until smooth.
mix dry ingredients together, then pour into cheese and butter mixture.
mix with hands until well blended.
press onto cookie sheet (ungreased).

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter

freeze.
soften 1/2 gallon ice cream.
spread over frozen crust.
return to freezer.
in saucepan, melt semi-sweet chocolate; add powdered sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
bring to rolling boil; cool.
spread over ice cream. return to freezer.
keep frozen until just before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lean beef
grated cheese
salt
sugar
pepper
butter
tomato sauce
egg noodles
onion
cream cheese
sour cream
garlic
directions:
brown beef in 2 tablespoons butter.
drain.
garlic to taste. add sugar, salt and pepper.
then add tomato sauce and let simmer on low for 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
raisins
water

cinnamon
cornstarch
salt
vinegar
butter
pastry
directions:
boil raisins in 1 3/4 cups water for 5 minutes.
combine brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
moisten with remaining 1/4 cup water.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
brown sugar
cranberries
butter

directions:
preheat oven to 400°.
butter 2 large cookie sheets.
sift flour into bowl.
mix in both sugars.
add butter and rub in fingertips until mixture resembles coarse meal.
add 1/2 cup dried fruit.
stir in enough cream to form soft, slightly sticky dough. turn dough out onto slightly floured surface and knead until just combined.
gather dough into ball; flatten into disc.
roll out to thickness of 3/4-inch.
cut out rounds using 2-inch round cookie cutter.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
bread crumbs
milk
salsa
directions:
dip chicken in milk and then roll in bread crumbs.
bake chicken at 375° for 30 minutes.
pour salsa on top.
bake for 30 more minutes or until chicken is done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornmeal
flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
egg
milk
directions:
mix dry ingredients. add milk, well beaten egg and melted fat. beat. bake in a shallow greased pan in a hot oven, 375°, for 20 minutes or more.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes
salt
sugar
vinegar
cinnamon
ground mustard
red pepper
mixed spices
cornstarch
directions:
combine tomatoes, salt, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, mustard, red pepper and mixed spices in kettle.
boil hard for 1 hour.
strain. return to stove and thicken with cornstarch, moistened with a little vinegar.
boil for 10 minutes.
very good. i prefer to use only 1 teaspoon red pepper.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
egg
milk
oil
chocolate chips
directions:
heat oven to 400°.
grease or line bottoms of 12 muffin cup tin.
combine first 4 ingredients.
stir in remaining ingredients until dry ingredients are moistened.
(batter will be lumpy.) fill cups 2/3 full.
bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
remove from pan.
serve warm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chuck roast
onion
celery
green pepper
water
clove garlic
salt
ketchup
brown sugar
vinegar
allspice
dry mustard
chili powder
tabasco sauce
bay leaf
garlic powder
paprika
directions:
place roast and vegetables in a large, heavy pot.
cover with water.
cook, covered, for 4 hours. remove meat, cool and shred with a fork.
return meat to 1 1/2 cups of the broth. add remaining ingredients. slowly boil, uncovered, for 1 hour. additional broth may be added, if needed.
when done, mixture should be of spreading consistency.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cold
vanilla instant pudding
instant coffee
chocolate crumb crust
fudge sauce
directions:
pour half and half into large mixing bowl.
add pie filling mix and instant coffee.
beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
let stand 5 minutes.
fold in whipped topping.
spoon into crust.
freeze until firm (about 6 hours).
remove from freezer.
let stand 10 minutes to soften.
top with fudge sauce.
store in freezer.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
butter
salt
mozzarella cheese
flour
egg
bread crumbs
directions:
flatten chicken between sheets of wax paper.
spread butter over each piece and season with salt and pepper.
place 1 slice mozzarella cheese over each piece.
roll up and fasten with toothpicks. roll each in flour, dip in egg and then roll in bread crumbs.
place in a medium size casserole. cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
mustard
horseradish
whole wheat bread slices
velveeta pasteurized process cheese spread
ham slices
parkay margarine
directions:
combine cream cheese, mustard and horseradish, mixing until well blended.
spread approximately 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture onto each bread slice.
for each sandwich, cover one bread slice with process cheese spread, ham and second bread slice. spread sandwich with margarine.
grill until lightly browned on both sides.
makes 4 sandwiches.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sugar
eggs
sour cream
soda
vanilla
bananas
salt
flour
directions:
cream together butter, sugar and eggs. mix sour cream and soda together in bowl and let stand until foamy. add the rest of the ingredients to the above mixtures and mix well. place into 4 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch bread pans or into 12 prepared mini loaf pans. sprinkle lightly with sugar just before baking. bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. note: you may add 1 cup of chopped nuts to the batter if you wish. you may also use egg beaters, low-fat sour cream and margarine. this is a very moist bread recipe which makes a lot and freezes well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lean ground beef
saltine cracker crumbs
eggs
tomato sauce
onions
green pepper
salt
black pepper
marjoram
thyme
directions:
combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl, mix well together. shape into greased loaf pan and bake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
brown sugar
whipping cream
powdered sugar
vanilla
directions:
melt butter in heavy saucepan.
add brown sugar and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
do not boil. remove from heat.
stir in whipping cream.
add powdered sugar and vanilla; beat at high speed until smooth.
frost 1 (10-inch) cake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apple juice
frozen lemonade
frozen limeade
bottles
directions:
put juices and green coloring in punch bowl.
gently add cold 7-up. serves 32 (4 ounces).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow corn meal
flour
sugar
baking powder
egg
milk
liquid oil
directions:
preheat oven to 425°.
sift together corn meal, flour, sugar and baking powder into a bowl.
add egg, milk and oil.
beat with beaters until smooth.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
cocoa powder
sugar
walnuts
salt
unsweetened applesauce
egg whites
vanilla extract
directions:
combine the flour, cocoa, sugar and salt, if desired, and stir to mix well.
stir in the applesauce, egg whites and vanilla extract.
fold in the nuts, if desired.

spread the batter evenly in the pan and bake at 325° for 23 minutes or just until the edges are firm and the center is almost set.
cool to room temperature and cut into square and serve.
(calories:
80, fat:
0.4 g)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hot sausage
sharp cheese
bisquick
directions:
with sausage and cheese at room temperature, mix well with bisquick.
bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.<|endofrecipe|>

mix until blended well. add crisco with pastry blender.
cut crisco into flour until size of small peas.
pour in 7-up (1/2 cup); stir with fork. dough should be kind of sticky.

be sure to prick all over with fork.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

pecans
mayonnaise
onion
clove garlic
strawberry preserves
directions:
combine all ingredients except preserves and mix well.
chill. mold into ring.
(i coat a small jello ring mold with vegetable spray and press ingredients into that before chilling.)
when ready to serve, unmold onto serving plate, fill middle with preserves. can be served as a complement to a main meal or as an hors d'oeuvre with crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
vanilla
eggs
salt
butter
directions:
cream sugar and butter together until all sugar is dissolved. add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly.
sift and measure flour.
add salt and sift again.
add flour to egg mixture; mix carefully.
add vanilla.
bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (grease pan).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
baking soda
vanilla
salt
margarine
white sugar
brown sugar
eggs
coconut
cornflakes
directions:

add coconut and cornflakes (crush them a little bit).

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
baking powder
egg whites
apples
vanilla
apple pie spice
directions:
mix all ingredients and place in pie plate sprayed with vegetable spray.
bake 30 minutes at 350°.
serve with low-fat whipped topping.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
water
mayonnaise
cream of chicken soup
celery
onion
corn flakes
butter
directions:
mix chicken, soup, celery, onions, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter

eggs
sugar

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

vegetable oil
onions

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

until

store
in refrigerator.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

vinegar
sugar
directions:
mix ingredients until smooth.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

all

let beef simmer in its own juice for 1 hour.

simmer for 1/2 hour.
add water, diced potatoes and remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
simmer until potatoes are done; add black pepper.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brown sugar
sour cream
vanilla
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes

italian cheese
olive oil
green peppers
garlic
salt
onions
cloves
bay leaves
allspice
directions:
combine and cook 2 1/2 to 4 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
marshmallows
semi-sweet chocolate
milk
vanilla
nuts
directions:
cut the marshmallows in quarters and put into a very large bowl in double boiler.
melt chocolate.
when melted, add milk and keep mixing until smooth. add the vanilla and stir.

pour over marshmallows and mix.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cherries
pineapple
flour
sugar

bananas
directions:
bring cherries and pineapple to a boil, then add flour and sugar mixture.
when thickened, add jello (dry).

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
raisins
flour
baking soda
baking powder
salt
sugar
butter
buttermilk
eggs
directions:
heat oven to 450°.
mix raisins with sifted flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
cut in butter with a pastry blender until consistency of corn meal.
gradually add buttermilk and eggs.
mix gently until just moistened.
knead lightly until smooth on a floured board and shape into a round loaf.
put dough in a greased round baking pan.
with a sharp knife cut a cross in top of dough.
bake 10 minutes at 450°; reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

slice and dunk in a cup of hot tea.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour

salt
cinnamon
nutmeg
shortening

eggs

oats

directions:

drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hot sausage
extra sharp cheese
bisquick
directions:
mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
bake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red kidney beans

garbanzo beans
oil
lemon juice
sugar
water
directions:
mix kidney beans, green beans, wax beans and garbanzo beans. marinate overnight.
add onion rings just before serving for crispness.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
margarine

baking powder
milk
pie filling
directions:
heat oven to 375°.
mix flour, margarine, powdered sugar, baking powder and just enough milk until dough forms.
if dough seems dry, mix in more milk one teaspoon at a time.
divide dough into 6 equal parts.
shape each part into a ball.
place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
flatten slightly.
make an indention 1 3/4 inches in diameter and about 3/4-inch deep in center of each. fill each indention with about 2 tablespoons pie filling.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shrimp
water
cornstarch
soy sauce
sugar
instant chicken
green onions
frozen pea pods
lemon peel
lemon juice
pepper
cooking oil
mushrooms
stalks celery
green pepper
rice
directions:
thaw shrimp, if frozen and drain well.
peel and devein shrimp.
for sauce, stir together water, cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar, bouillon granules, lemon peel and juice and pepper.
set aside.
preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat.
add 1 tablespoon of the oil.
add mushrooms, celery and green pepper; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
add green onion and stir-fry for 1 minute more.
remove vegetables from wok.
add remaining oil.
add half of shrimp to hot wok.
stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
remove and stir-fry remaining shrimp.
return shrimp to wok.
push from center.
stir sauce.
add to center of the wok. cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
add vegetables and pea pods.
stir to coat mixture with sauce.
cook and stir for 1 minute.
serve over rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oleo
sugar
egg
vanilla
flour
nuts
colored sugar
directions:
in large bowl, mix butter, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla, flour and 1/2 cup nuts.
blend well.
spread in ungreased jelly roll pan 15 x 10-inch.
beat egg whites until frothy.
spread over mix. sprinkle with colored sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
cool and cut into squares or bars.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
wesson oil
flour
sugar
buttermilk
eggs
cocoa
soda
baking powder
vinegar
red food coloring
vanilla
directions:
grease and flour pans.
(makes three (9-inch) layers.) mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground chuck
ground pork
onion
clove garlic
bread crumbs
milk

parsley

eggs
salt
pepper
directions:
soak bread pieces in milk.
combine all ingredients to mixed meat.
form into loaf; place in greased loaf pan.
bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white sugar
brown sugar
salt
milk
white karo syrup
butter
vanilla
pecan halves
directions:
mix sugar, salt, milk and karo syrup in heavy, 3-quart pan and cook to soft ball stage.
add butter and vanilla.
beat until cool.
add pecans and drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
when firm, store in closed container.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
grassy field
pebbles
children
brook
directions:
mix the children and dogs together.
put them in a field, stirring constantly.
pour the brook over the pebbles.
sprinkle the field with some flowers.
spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in a hot sun.
when brown, remove and set to cool in a bathtub.
now, go on with your cooking.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
head lettuce
cauliflower
bacon
mayonnaise
vinegar
sugar
sharp cheese
directions:
layer the first three ingredients in bowl.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter

directions:
saute onion and green pepper in butter.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white

cream of coconut
coconut
directions:

immediately pour the eagle brand milk over hot cake.
let sit until cake is warm.
pour the cream of coconut over cake.
sprinkle with coconut.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

kahlua
containers
directions:
you may cut this recipe in half, it makes quite a bit.
also, you can omit the kahlua!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

vanilla

cinnamon
ground cloves
eggs

nutmeg
pecans

directions:

put in cold oven.
bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
let cake cool some before removing from pan.
while still warm, glaze.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

baking powder
margarine
salt
sugar
vanilla
eggs
directions:
mix all ingredients together.
drop by teaspoon on waffle pizzelle maker.
cook about 30 seconds.<|endofrecipe|>

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

*cool whip can be used, but the whipped cream is so delightful.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

eggs
one
at a time.

seed.
sift
together
the
flour, baking powder and salt into a

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter

garlic powder
directions:
combine in saucepan and bring to boil, mixing thoroughly. pour over chicken and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

bay leaf
parsley stems
thyme
salt
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
blanch bacon in boiling water 3 minutes.
drain, refresh and pat dry.
peel potatoes and blanch for 5 minutes; drain and pat dry.
trim fat from chicken and season.
add butter and oil to large covered casserole and brown chicken over high heat.
remove and set aside.
add bacon to pot and brown; remove.
brown pearl onions; remove.
brown blanched potatoes and remove.
pour off excess fat.
return chicken to casserole.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

celery

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

carrots
nuts

cinnamon
directions:

nuts

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

margarine

's sausage

bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

milk

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

salt
pepper
egg

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mayonnaise
lemon juice
celery
green onion
shrimp
directions:

mix mayonnaise and lemon juice with electric mixer.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

shortening

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

shortening and peanut butter.
gradually add 1/2 cup sugar
and	brown

milk	and
vanilla;
beat
well.

beat eggs in separate container.
mix other ingredients.

cubes

heat.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
olive oil

black beans
water

cayenne
red
brown sugar
sour cream
yellow onions

ground cumin

parsley
sherry

green onions
directions:
soak the black beans in water overnight.
heat oil in a dutch oven.
add onions and garlic and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
drain the beans.
add the beans to the dutch oven.
add the ham bone and the water.
stir in 1 tablespoon of cumin, oregano, bay leaf, salt, pepper, cayenne and 1 tablespoon of parsley.
bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook, uncovered, until beans are very tender and the liquid is reduced by about 3/4.
this will take 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
if it requires a longer cooking time, the beans were probably old.
transfer ham bone to plate and cool slightly.
pull off any remaining meat with your fingers and shred.
return meat to pot.
stir in remaining parsley, red pepper, cumin, sherry, brown sugar and lemon juice. simmer for another 30 minutes.
taste.
correct seasoning and serve very hot.

water

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

brandy
