directions:
unroll crescent roll dough and place triangles on a 12-inch pizza pan, forming a ring with pointed ends facing outer edge of pan and wide ends overlapping.
lightly press wide ends together. combine the remaining ingredients; spoon over wide ends of rolls. fold points over filling and tuck under wide ends (filling will be visible).
bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
yields 6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brown sugar
peanut butter
egg
directions:
preheat oven to 375 degrees. combine all ingredients in bowl of food processor, fitted with steel blade. process until mixture clings together. (you can use a mixer, if desired.) shape dough into balls about 1 inch in diameter. place on an ungreased cookie sheet. press with a fork in a criss-cross pattern. if the fork sticks to the cookie dough, dip it in sugar and then press. bake for 8 to 10 minutes. remove from pan immediately and cool on a rack.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
buttermilk
flour
salt
sugar
soda
directions:
beat egg whites and fold in last.
make small pancakes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
water
sugar
cherry pie filling
pineapple
lemon juice
cold cola
nuts
directions:
combine water and sugar; bring to a boil.
add pie filling and return to a boil.
pour over the jell-o to dissolve.
add rest of ingredients.
pour into 13 x 9-inch pan or mold to set.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
cream of mushroom soup
onion
tortilla chips
ro-tel tomatoes
grated cheese
directions:
brown meat and onion.
chop tomatoes.
mix with soup and meat. in baking dish, arrange layers of chips, meat mixture and grated cheese.
repeat layers, ending with cheese.
bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
nonstick cooking spray
olive oil
onion
garlic
boneless skinless chicken breast
penne pasta
black olives
fresh basil
oregano
parmesan cheese
directions:
liberally spray large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. add oil and heat over medium heat.
add garlic and onions.
heat until soft (approximately 3-4 minutes).
fill large saucepan with 2 inches of water.
place chicken breast in steaming basket or stainless steal saucepan with lid.
bring water to boil and steam chicken for 7 minutes.
remove from heat and let set in steam until fully cooked.
remove chicken from basket and let cool. when cool, cut into 1 inch chunks.
meanwhile, cook penne according to packaging.
drain and keep warm.
add chicken chunks, olives, basil, and oregano to skillet with onions.
turn to medium heat for 5 minutes.
in large bowl, toss chicken with hot penne pasta.
sprinkle top with cheese and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
zucchini
onions
tomatoes
mozzarella cheese
italian seasoning
salt
crackers
directions:
spray 9 x 13 inch pan.
place layers of tomato, onion, zucchini and cheese.
sprinkle with salt and pepper and liberally with italian seasoning.
sprinkle about 1/2 cup crushed ritz over all.
make second layer same as first, beginning with tomato and ending with cheese, top with more seasoning and crushed ritz. cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
remove foil and bake another 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
parmesan cheese
regular
hamburger
ricotta cheese
egg
mozzarella cheese
cheddar cheese
directions:
cook hamburger; drain and add spaghetti sauce.
cook lasagne noodles for 10 minutes in boiling water; drain.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
milk
oleo
peanut butter
directions:
mix sugar, milk and oleo; cook to soft ball stage.
add peanut butter and beat.
pour onto greased plate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
bacon
onion
flour
sugar
salt
celery
pepper
water
vinegar
directions:
boil potatoes with the skins on.
peel and slice thinly.
fry slowly in large skillet the bacon.
drain on paper towel.
saute in the bacon fat until golden the onion.
blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and dash of pepper.
cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
remove from heat.
stir in water and vinegar. bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
boil 1 minute.
stir in carefully the potatoes and crumbled bits of bacon.
remove from heat.
cover and let stand until ready to serve.
makes 6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
shortening
buttermilk
pork sausage
directions:
crumble and brown sausage; drain fat.
cut butter or shortening into flour until coarse crumbs form.
add buttermilk and stir until dough clings together.
knead 10 to 12 strokes on lightly floured surface.
roll out to a 16 x 12-inch rectangle. sprinkle sausage over dough.
roll up jelly roll style, starting with the long side.
slice into 1-inch slices.
place cut side down on ungreased baking sheet.
bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
light bread
onion
green pepper
tomato ketchup
egg
salt
black pepper
directions:
mix together ground beef, crumbled bread slices, chopped onion, pepper, egg, salt and black pepper.
add 1/2 cup ketchup and mix.
place mix in loaf pan and spread remaining 1/4 cup ketchup over the top.
bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onion soup mix
niblets corn
potatoes
salt
directions:
grease casserole, in skillet melt a little margarine.
add beef and stir until meat is lightly browned, season meat and sprinkle with about 2 tablespoons flour.
mix well.
add onion soup mix and slowly add about 1 cup of water and cook until slightly thickened. turn into greased casserole and spread with drained corn. prepare mashed potatoes to make a 2-inch topping.
drizzle a little melted margarine over top and sprinkle a little paprika. bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.
serves about 4 to 6 people.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
pumpkin
oil
water
vanilla
flour
ground cinnamon
salt
baking soda
dates
pecans
directions:
combine eggs and sugar in a large mixing bowl.	stir in pumpkin, oil, water and vanilla until blended.
stir together flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
add pumpkin mixture, stirring until just combined.
fold in dates and nuts.
pour mixture into 4 greased 7 x 3 x 2-inch pans or 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans.
bake in a 350° oven about 55 minutes for small loaves, 65 minutes for large loaves.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
cream cheese
sour cream
whipping cream
butter
salt
green onions
cheddar cheese
bacon bits
directions:
cook potatoes in water until soft; drain. add cream cheese, sour cream, butter, salt, pepper and onions; beat. put into a 9 x 12 casserole dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread
cream cheese
eggs
milk
maple syrup
directions:
mix together and cover dish with plastic overnight.
bake the next morning at 375° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn
margarine
eggs
sour cream
mix
kernel corn
directions:
mix all ingredients together (may blend in blender).
pour into rectangular 2-inch pie pan or casserole dish. bake in a 350° oven 1 hour.
(freezes well.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh peaches
sugar
flour
nutmeg
cinnamon
almond
butter
pastry
directions:
combine peaches, sugar, flour and spices.
set aside until syrup forms.
bring peaches to a boil.
cook 10 minutes or until tender.
remove from heat and blend in almond extract and butter.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
whole kernel corn
frozen lima beans
chicken broth
onion
tomato juice
chicken
salt
pepper
margarine
worcestershire sauce
directions:
combine all ingredients in a 5-quart dutch oven. bring to boiling over medium heat.
reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stir occasionally.
makes 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
graham cracker crumbs
peanut butter
powdered sugar
paraffin wax
chocolate chips
directions:
melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
melt margarine in separate pan.
mix graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar, peanut butter and melted margarine.
mix well.
form into balls or logs with hands, then dip logs into chocolate chip mixture.
lay logs on wax paper until dry.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oleo
white sugar
brown sugar
eggs
lemon
vanilla
flour
soda
chocolate chips
nuts
directions:
cream together oleo or crisco, white sugar and brown sugar. add eggs, pudding and vanilla.
mix good.
add flour and soda. mix.
add chocolate chips and nuts.
bake at 375° for 5 minutes. shift trays and bake 3 minutes more.
freezes very well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bacon
onion
potatoes
water
cream-style
milk
salt
directions:
cook bacon in saucepan until crisp. remove from pan and save for later use. lightly brown onion in bacon fat; add potatoes and water. boil gently for 10 minutes. add corn and cook 10 minutes longer. stir in milk, salt and bacon. heat just until hot. makes 6 (1 cup) servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread
margarine
onion
celery
sage
salt
pepper
chicken broth
eggs
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
cut bread into small cubes.
put into large mixing bowl.
melt margarine in large skillet.
add onions and celery; cook until tender.
add to bread crumbs.
add sage, salt and pepper.
moisten with broth, as desired.
beat eggs lightly.
stir into dressing.
use as stuffing for poultry or other meats or bake, covered, in a one-quart casserole dish for 30 minutes.
equals 1 bread, 1 fat and 1 vegetable.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shell macaroni
milk
green pepper
onion
carrots
vinegar
sugar
mayonnaise
salt
pepper
directions:
cook macaroni; drain and cool.
mix green pepper, onion and carrots in macaroni.
mix remaining ingredients in separate bowl. pour over macaroni.
let set in refrigerator overnight.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
brown sugar
lemon juice
grand marnier
apples
oranges
green grapes
banana
directions:
drain juice from pineapple into 1-cup glass measure.
stir in brown sugar and lemon juice.
microwave on high, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture boils. stir in flavoring. cool. quarter apples and cut into very thin slices.
peel oranges. cut into thin slices.
cut slices in half.
in glass serving bowl, layer half the apples, oranges and grapes. slice banana and arrange over grapes.
top with pineapple chunks. repeat with remaining apples, oranges and grapes.
pour cooled syrup over all. cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
makes about 12 servings, 70 calories each.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
gelatin
water
mayonnaise
celery
bell peppers
olives
cream cheese
cream of tomato soup
onion
nuts
directions:
dissolve gelatin in cool water.
heat cream cheese in tomato soup to mix.
cool.
add balance of ingredients and congeal.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
morton tender quick salt
regular salt
liquid smoke
red pepper
garlic salt
coarse black pepper
directions:
mix all ingredients together.
refrigerate 24 hours.
mix well again.
refrigerate another 24 hours.
shape into small rolls, about 1 to 1 1/2-inches.
place on cookie sheet.
bake at 150° for 8 hours.
turn after 4 hours.
can also use ground turkey.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tater
ground beef
cream of mushroom soup
onion
velveeta cheese
directions:
brown ground beef with small chopped onion and drain.
add 1/2 can soup and 1/2 cup water.
add velveeta (cubed).
pour into casserole dish.
put tater tots on top.
mix 1/2 can soup and 1/2 can water and pour over tater tots.
garnish top with cheese. cover with foil and bake at 425° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brown sugar
sugar
oleo
flour
vanilla
baking soda
buttermilk
egg
nuts
directions:
mix first 5 ingredients to form crumbs.
put aside 1/2 cup of these crumbs.
add soda which has been dissolved in the buttermilk and the egg.
beat well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
sprinkle 1/2 cup reserved crumbs, nuts and chopped heath bars on top.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
salt
black pepper
olive
butter
fresh chives
lemon
brandy
parsley
mustard
chicken broth
directions:
place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper. pound slightly with mallet.
sprinkle with salt and pepper.
heat 1 tablespoon of oil and butter in large skillet.
cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
transfer to warm serving platter.
add chives, lemon juice and brandy (if used), parsley and mustard to pan.
cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly. add broth and continue to whisk.
stir until sauce is smooth. whisk in remaining oil and butter.
pour over chicken; serve immediately.
good served with noodles with tomato sauce.
serves 4 to 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
onion
worcestershire sauce
beef
pickle juice
mayonnaise
directions:
mix all ingredients together, shape into a ball.
refrigerate until ready to serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lamb breast
cooking oil
veal
bayleaf
garlic
salt
fresh ground pepper
potatoes
carrots
onions
flour
directions:
using a stew pot, brown the meat in the oil.
add stock, bay leaf, garlic and seasonings; bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer.
skim away and discard the froth or scum that rises during the first moments of cooking.
cover pot and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour, until meat is quite tender.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mandarin oranges
pineapple tidbits
orange gelatin
cottage cheese
frozen whipped topping
directions:
mix all ingredients together thoroughly and refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
cold half and half
sugar
graham cracker pie crust
vanilla instant pudding
pumpkin
cinnamon
ginger
cloves
directions:
mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
gently stir in whipped topping; spread on bottom of crust.
pour 2 cups half and half into mixing bowl. add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
let stand 3 minutes.
stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
spread over cream cheese layer.
refrigerate at least 2 hours.
garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts, as desired. makes 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
boneless chicken
oil
garlic
green pepper
carrot strips
chicken bouillon
soy sauce
sherry
vinegar
brown sugar
ginger
pineapple
rice
directions:
brown chicken in oil.
add garlic, green pepper and carrots and saute briefly.
add bouillon, soy sauce, sherry, vinegar, sugar, ginger and pineapple with juice.
bring to a full boil. stir in rice.
cover and remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes. stir before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cake
red jello
strawberries
directions:
slice top off cake to make 2 layers.
make jello using 3 cups water for both.
after it sets, add sliced strawberries.
mix in 1 cup cool whip.
top bottom cake with mixture, fill in hole.
put top layer cake over bottom layer.
frost with cool whip. refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sour cream
cream cheese
salsa
tomato
cheddar cheese
head lettuce
nachos
directions:
mix sour cream and cream cheese together and spread over bottom of bowl or pan.
top with tomatoes.
pour on salsa.
then add cheese and finally lettuce.
you're ready to dip.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red potatoes
crisco
salt
margarine
directions:
wash the
potatoes well and dice.
in a large cake pan, pour the
crisco
and
add potatoes. coat potatoes in oil. add salt, pepper,
garlic
salt and onion salt or season to taste. slice the margarine over the potatoes.
cook at 425°, stirring 2 to 3 times for 45 minutes to 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
butter
sugar
brown sugar
vanilla
egg
chocolate chips
pecans
directions:
cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. add egg, mix well, stir in flour, chocolate chips and pecans. spread on lightly greased pizza pan and bake at 350° until brown. cool before cutting. yield: 24 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crescent rolls
cream cheese
mayonnaise
dressing
mushrooms
broccoli
cauliflower
olives
tomato
cheese
directions:
press rolls in 9 x 15-inch pan.
bake at 350° for 10 minutes. spread mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise and ranch dressing onto cool crust.
press chopped vegetables and cheese onto mixture. cut into squares.
this dish freezes well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
graham cracker shells
eggs
lemon juice
sugar
directions:
mix milk with slightly beaten egg yolks.
add lemon juice; mix.
pour into shells.
top with egg whites.
add the sugar.
put into oven and brown.
chill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen broccoli
water
soy sauce
garlic
cornstarch
ground ginger
directions:
in medium saucepan, cook vegetables as directed on package. drain.
in small saucepan, stir together remaining ingredients. cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
pour sauce over vegetables.
toss to coat.
serves 4 to 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground cranberries
oranges
apple
pineapple
raspberry jello
water
sugar
walnuts
directions:
dissolve jello in water and mix remaining ingredients.
chill until ready to serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
green pepper
cocktail onions
sugar
white vinegar
vegetable oil
dry mustard
directions:
cook carrots in boiling water for 15 minutes until tender-crisp.
drain.
combine pepper and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring frequently. pour hot mixture over carrots.
cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
yields 12 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
cream cheese
powdered sugar
vanilla
maple flavoring
directions:
mix together until smooth.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cherry pie filling
pineapple
condensed milk
marshmallows
pecan
directions:
mix all together and freeze.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
catsup
horseradish
lemon
vinegar
worcestershire sauce
directions:
mix ingredients and chill.
serve with shrimp.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
thin spaghetti
onion
butter
tomatoes
salt
mushrooms
olives
butter
flour
whipping cream
milk
parmesan cheese
directions:
cook spaghetti; drain well.
set aside.
saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring until tender.
add tomatoes and salt.
cook, uncovered, over medium heat 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
add mushrooms and olives.
set aside.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake
salad oil
eggs
water
cinnamon
vodka
milk chocolate frosting
directions:
in one bowl, combine all ingredients except frosting.
beat with mixer at high speed for 2 minutes.
grease and flour medium size (9 cup) bundt pan and pour in batter.
(this will give a high cake; larger pans will give a flatter cake.)
bake at 350°.
test at 45 minutes and then every 5 minutes until done.
cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.
if frosted while warm, frosting will melt to sort of a glaze.
equally good frosted when cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cranberry sauce
pineapple
frozen strawberries
walnut pieces
directions:
mix together and refrigerate overnight.
delicious served with roast turkey, chicken or ham.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tart apples
flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
egg
butter
directions:
pare and slice apples, place in a greased shallow baking dish. stir together in a bowl, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. add unbeaten egg, melted and cooled butter or margarine.
blend with fork until well mixed.
drop mixture, by spoonful, over the apples.
sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hamburger
onion
sugar
italian seasoning
egg
parmesan cheese
margarine
cream-style cottage cheese
mozzarella
directions:
brown meat and drain.
add sauce, seasoning and meat; cover and microwave on high 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated. in large bowl, stir together egg, hot spaghetti, parmesan cheese and margarine.
press mixture over bottom and sides of pie plate (microwave) to form crust.
spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
spread heated meat mixture over cottage cheese.
cover with wax paper; cook on medium for 9 to 11 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
sprinkle with mozzarella; let stand 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
makes 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh corn
water
salt
butter
milk
flour
directions:
combine corn, water and salt.
cook for four minutes.
remove from heat.
add butter.
combine milk and flour in shaker.
shake until blended.
stir into corn mixture.
return to heat.
cook four minutes, stirring often.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
artichokes
cheddar cheese
mayonnaise
garlic powder
directions:
combine ingredients and heat at 325° in oven until it bubbles. (can be done in microwave, about 3 minutes.) serve with king sized fritos.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oleo
flour
powdered sugar
directions:
melt oleo.
pour melted oleo over dry ingredients and mix. press into pie plate.
bake at 350° until golden brown.
good with all cream pies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
cherries
condensed milk
pecans
lemon juice
directions:
mix all ingredients, adding lemon juice.
this acts as a thickening agent.
pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mayonnaise
milk
onions
cream cheese
sweet pickle relish
capers
directions:
combine all ingredients until well blended.
makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes
celery
green pepper
onion
salt
white vinegar
black pepper
pickling spice
brown sugar
sugar
directions:
peel tomatoes and place in large pan.
grind celery, green pepper and onion.
mix with tomatoes.
pour salt over mixture and cover with water.
let stand overnight.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lean hamburger
joe
tomato paste
water
macaroni
whole kernel corn
cheddar cheese
directions:
brown ground beef and drain. stir in sloppy joe mix, tomato paste and water; bring to a boil. simmer 10 minutes; stir occasionally. cook macaroni until done; drain. mix all together and add corn and 1 cup cheese. sprinkle the other cup of cheese on top. bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 325°, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
margarine
eggs
lemon flavoring
cream cheese
powdered sugar
directions:
mix by hand the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg until forms soft ball like cookie dough.
press into large sheet-type pan.
(pam greased).
cream together the flavoring, cream cheese and 3 eggs (add one at a time).
add powdered sugar.
spread over top of dough.
bake 45 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
whole wheat flour
white flour
soda
salt
buttermilk
directions:
sift dry ingredients.
add butter.
gradually add buttermilk. spread on baking sheet, 8-inches in diameter.
put deep cross in center with knife.
bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vanilla wafers
bananas
vanilla
sour cream
tubs
directions:
place vanilla wafers in bottom of a 9x13-inch casserole dish. layer bananas on top of vanilla wafers and set aside.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
doritos chips
chicken breasts
cream of chicken soup
cream of mushroom soup
milk
picante sauce
cheddar cheese
directions:
cover a 9 x 13-inch buttered pyrex dish with the doritos chips. cook chicken and cut into bite-size pieces; place over the doritos. mix together soups, milk and picante sauce.
pour over chicken and doritos.
sprinkle grated cheddar cheese on top.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
best made at least 6 hours before serving.
serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sausage
ground beef
onion
chili powder
salt
pepper
whole kernel corn
tomato sauce
milk
corn meal
olives
shredded cheese
directions:
brown sausage in skillet; pour off fat.
add meat and onion; cook and stir a few minutes.
add seasonings, corn, tomato sauce and milk.
simmer 20 minutes.
stir corn meal into meat mixture. add olives.
pour into casserole.
top with cheese.
bake in 325° oven about 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
sour cream
dill
crescent rolls
mayonnaise
monde
garlic
directions:
spray large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan with pam.
slightly roll out 2 rectangles (1 can) pillsbury crescent rolls between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
place on cookie sheet and repeat procedure with second can of crescent rolls.
press dough out with hands to fit.
bake 11 to 13 minutes at 375°.
cool.
spread dip over crust and decorate with chopped or sliced broccoli, mushrooms, zucchini, carrots, celery, cucumbers, black olives, hard-cooked egg, green peppers, shredded cheese, bacon bits and halved cherry tomatoes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crisco
flour
milk
salt
egg
powdered sugar
vanilla
directions:
beat all but egg white 4 to 5 minutes.
add egg white.
beat 5 minutes longer.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
vinegar
sauerkraut
celery
onion
green pepper
directions:
bring sugar and vinegar to boil and let cool.
drain well and cut up sauerkraut.
add rest of ingredients.
pour syrup over and let stand overnight.
very important to stand overnight. delicious.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cereal
semi-sweet chocolate chips
peanut butter
margarine
vanilla
powdered sugar
directions:
measure out ingredients. pour cereal into bowl; set aside. combine chips, peanut butter and margarine in microwave-safe bowl. microwave on high 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. stir until smooth. stir in vanilla. pour over cereal. stir until well coated. pour into a zippered bag with powdered sugar. seal bag; shake until coated. pour onto foil. cool. store in airtight container.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg whites
sugar
vanilla
salt
chocolate chips
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
beat egg whites until stiff.
gradually beat sugar into stiff egg whites.
fold in vanilla, salt and chocolate chips.
drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. put cookies into the oven.
turn the oven off and leave cookies in overnight.
makes about 2 dozen cookies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
baking potatoes
cream cheese
hot milk
garlic salt
butter
parsley
paprika
directions:
put cream cheese out to soften.
scrub potatoes and dry. grease them with butter and salt the skins.
bake at 350° for 1 hour.
remove from oven and cool to handle.
cut them in half lengthwise.
remove cooked potato to bowl, being careful to reserve the skins whole.
mash with cream cheese, hot milk, garlic salt and butter.
pile mixture back into skins.
sprinkle with parsley and paprika and bake 20 more minutes.
makes 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
milk
vanilla
directions:
mix beaten eggs and sugar.
add hot milk and pour into a large pie shell. bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes (until crust is brown).
you may put dots of butter on top and sprinkle with nutmeg.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cheddar cheese
flour
butter
salt
cayenne pepper
directions:
sift salt and pepper with flour; fold in butter.
let cheese be at room temperature and work until smooth.
add to flour; mix until smooth.
roll thin and cut into strips.
bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
tops
wild rice
chicken
boiling water
long grain white rice
pecans
fresh basil
directions:
in large saucepan, melt the butter over moderate heat.
add onions and saute 5 minutes.
stir in wild rice, coating with butter.
pour in stock; bring to boil and stir.
lower heat; cover tightly and simmer, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
add the water; stir in white rice.
cover and steam 20 minutes longer or until both rices are tender.
stir in the pecans and basil. serves 4, easy to double.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of mushroom soup
milk
turkey
macaroni
eggs
butter
bread crumbs
directions:
in a large bowl combine soup, milk and cheese.
add chicken or turkey, macaroni and eggs.
stir in 1/4 cup melted butter. transfer to a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
toss the bread crumbs with remaining butter.
sprinkle over casserole.
bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown. yields 12 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
egg
italian bread crumbs
butter
fresh mushrooms
flour
chicken bouillon
lemon juice
salt
pepper
parsley flakes
directions:
cut the chicken breasts in half. dip in beaten egg, then in progresso italian bread crumbs. brown in oil.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cherry pie filling
cinnamon
almond extract
cake
oleo
nuts
directions:
spread in 13-inch loaf pan.
sprinkle 1 cake mix on top.
put oleo dribbles over top.
put nuts on top.
bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
shortening
sorghum molasses
buttermilk
egg
flour
salt
cinnamon
soda
ginger
directions:
cream sugar, shortening and molasses.
add egg and buttermilk. mix well.
stir in dry ingredients together with vinegar and soda mixture.
divide dough into 6 balls.
press each ball into well-greased 8-inch cake pan.
bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until slightly browned.
remove from pans while warm and set aside to cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
buttermilk
shortening
directions:
make hole in center of flour with knuckles.
put shortening in the mix as in regular biscuits.
then pinch off enough for size of biscuit.
roll up in hand.
place in slightly greased frying pan (on top of stove); continue with rest of dough.
cook on low heat, covered with lid until lightly brown on bottom, then turn over to other side.
let top side brown, uncover about 5 minutes before done.
makes 6 to 8 biscuits.
cooking time approximately 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oil
sugar
eggs
flour
salt
baking soda
cinnamon
apple pie filling
pecans
directions:
beat together first three ingredients.
mix together in separate bowl all dry ingredients.
add oil mixture to dry mixture.
puree apple pie filling and add to mixture along with chopped pecans.
bake at 350° in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
freezes well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
butter
graham cracker crumbs
cream cheese
eggs
vanilla
cherry
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
mix 3/4 cup sugar and butter.
heat. add crumbs.
press into 13 x 9-inch pan and set aside.
beat cream cheese.
add eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
pour fruit mix over crust, then cream cheese mixture.
bake 45 to 50 minutes.
chill thoroughly before serving.
may garnish with whipped cream or small amounts of fruit.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
campbell's cream
milk
salt
onions
directions:
wash chicken thoroughly.
dry with paper towel.
lay chicken pieces in a casserole dish.
sprinkle with salt and pepper. combine half the onions with the soup and milk.
pour over chicken. bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until chicken is done. sprinkle remaining onions over top and return to oven for 5 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pecans
candied cherries
red
candied pineapple
butter
sugar
soda
eggs
flour
grape juice
baking powder
allspice
directions:
mix nuts, fruit and flour until flour covers nuts and fruit good.
add other ingredients and let batter stand 30 minutes, then drop from small spoon onto a cookie sheet.
bake approximately 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange juice
balsamic vinegar
orange zest
mustard
salt
ground pepper
olive oil
romaine lettuce
watercress
sweet onion
oranges
directions:
mix orange juice, vinegar, orange zest, mustard, salt, pepper and olive oil. shake and refrigerate; if possible make a day or two ahead.
toss romaine and watercress with dressing.
arrange small salad plates or use one bowl.
peel and slice the oranges. thinly slice small sweet onion and arrange along with orange slices on top of lettuce.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
overripe bananas
flour
sugar
salt
baking soda
baking powder
eggs
butter
milk
directions:
in mixing bowl, put bananas and beat until smooth; add eggs, butter, salt, baking powder, soda, flour, sugar and milk.
grease three 9-inch aluminum loaf pans.
heat oven to 350°; cook about 45 minutes or until top of bread is brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
your favorite
your favorite beer
sausages
directions:
put everything in slow cooker.
set on low heat until evening, stirring several times.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
regular biscuits
brown sugar
sugar
cinnamon
butter
directions:
mix sugars and cinnamon.
cut each biscuit into quarters and roll each piece in mixture and put in ungreased bundt pan.
pour remaining mixture over biscuits.
melt butter and pour over the top.
bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until it looks done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
whole wheat flour
salt
baking soda
oil
molasses
honey
eggs
boiling water
directions:
mix first three ingredients.
add oil, molasses and honey. mix well.
add 2 eggs and boiling water.
may be hot!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange
ginger ale
orange sherbet
directions:
prepare kool-aid as directed on package. mix in ginger ale. stir in sherbet just before serving. yields 15 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
applesauce
sour cream
salt
onion
worcestershire sauce
directions:
slowly cook applesauce about 5 minutes to evaporate some of the liquid; chill.
combine all ingredients; mix well.
use for any fresh vegetable of your choice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lean stew meat
onion soup
cream of mushroom soup
directions:
lightly brown meat.
put in crock-pot with soups.
cook on low heat about 8 hours.
serve over noodles or rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sugar
brown sugar
almond extract
eggs
nuts
vanilla
applesauce
flour
oatmeal
baking soda
raisins
directions:
cream butter and sugars.
add almond extract, eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
mix well.
blend in flour, oatmeal and baking soda.
if desired, add nuts and/or raisins.
drop by teaspoonfuls onto nonstick cookie sheets.
bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. yield:
3 dozen cookies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
brown sugar
flour
baking powder
salt
milk
rolled oats
raisins
nuts
directions:
cream sugar and shortening.
sift flour, baking powder and salt.
add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
add oats, raisins and nuts.
mix well.
spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
cool; cut into bars.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork tenderloin
soy sauce
catsup
vinegar
pepper
clove garlic
directions:
cut meat lengthwise in half.
mix remaining ingredients in medium bowl.
add meat and turn to coat on all sides.
cover and refrigerate, turning meat occasionally, at least 8 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
flour
corn
butter
salt
milk
directions:
beat together eggs, sugar and flour.
combine with corn, butter, salt and milk.
pour into a greased 1-quart casserole. bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
yields 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
mustard
sugar
cider vinegar
salt
mayonnaise
directions:
cook eggs, sugar, vinegar and salt over double boiler, stirring often, until it thickens.
remove from heat.
add mustard and mayonnaise.
pour over salad.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
popcorn
oleo
brown sugar
white karo
cream of tartar
soda
directions:
boil oleo, brown sugar, white karo and cream of tartar
for 5 minutes; take off heat and stir in soda and popcorn.
pour into loaf pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
stir every 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
wild rice
mushrooms
cream of mushroom soup undiluted
worcestershire sauce
pork sausage
turkey
bread crumbs
butter
directions:
cook rice according to package directions.
meanwhile, in skillet cook sausage until brown, break in bits and pour off fat. stir in mushroom soups, mushrooms, worcestershire sauce and meat. put all together in greased baking dish.
cover with buttered crumbs.
bake for 30 minutes at 375 degrees.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
egg
brown sugar
bread
egg whites
vanilla
nutmeg
sugar
milk
cinnamon
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
spray baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
lay the slices of bread in baking dish in two rows, overlapping them like shingles.
in a mixing bowl, beat together the egg, egg whites, milk, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
pour the egg mixture over the bread.
in a small bowl, stir together the remaining ingredients.
sprinkle mixture over the bread.
bake 30 to 35 minutes until it has browned on top and is firm to touch. makes 9 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
shortening
milk
egg
vanilla
directions:
sift dry ingredients together.
add milk, egg, vanilla and shortening.
mix well.
bake at 375° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
crisco
light brown sugar
white sugar
eggs
milk
vanilla
salt
baking powder
black walnuts
flour
directions:
cream together butter, crisco, brown and white sugar.
add flavoring.
add eggs, one at a time, mix well after each.
mix flour, baking powder and salt.
add dry mix and milk to egg mix, start with dry mix and add milk, end with dry.
stir in walnuts. pour into 10-inch well-greased and floured pan.
bake at 325° for 90 minutes, start in cold oven.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork shoulder
beer
water
rosemary
onions
bouillon
potatoes
carrots
flour/water
directions:
brown pork.
add beer, water and rosemary.
simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
add onions and cook 30 minutes more.
meanwhile, cook potatoes and carrots (salted) together until done.
add these and bouillon to stew pot.
blend flour and water to make a paste and add to stew.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crust
instant chocolate pudding
pecan halves
cold milk
butterscotch ice cream topping
directions:
bring butterscotch to a boil in saucepan, stirring constantly.
pour 3/4 cup butterscotch into crust.
then place a layer of pecans in the bottom.
chill for about 5 minutes so sauce can harden.
meanwhile, mix pudding with milk.
pour into crust on top of pecans.
chill.
right before serving, drizzle a little butterscotch on top of pudding and top with cool whip and sprinkle chopped pecans on top.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornmeal
margarine
sugar
milk
salt
eggs
sugar
yeast
flour
directions:
cook the first 5 ingredients until thick; cool until lukewarm. add the eggs, 2 teaspoons sugar and the softened yeast.
mix well, then add the flour.
knead well; place in greased bowl.
let rise for 1 hour or more.
punch down; roll out.
cut with biscuit cutter.
let rise until doubled in a greased pan.
bake at 365° for 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground chuck
bread crumbs
onion
salt
pepper
milk
your favorite barbecue sauce
directions:
combine first 6 ingredients, stirring until mixture is thoroughly blended. shape mixture into 6 loaves. place loaves on rack of a greased broiler pan. spoon barbecue sauce over loaves. makes 6 loaves.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
deer meat
salt
pepper
garlic
soy sauce
worcestershire
liquid smoke
directions:
cover bottom of pan with meat strips.
liberally salt, pepper and garlic.
sprinkle with soy sauce.
cover with worcestershire sauce.
repeat layers if necessary.
make sure meat is submerged. cover and refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
place foil on oven racks; shape an edge.
lay meat in single layer, edge to edge.
brush with liquid smoke.
dry in 150° to 175° oven until bends, but does not break, about 5 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
condensed cream
milk
mayonnaise
whole kernel corn
pimiento
parsley
directions:
in a sauce pan, heat soup, milk, mayonnaise and corn (with liquid), stirring occasionally.
garnish with pimiento and parsley.
makes 5 servings (1 cup each).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
graham cracker crumbs
condensed milk
semi-sweet chocolate chips
peanut butter
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
top with chips; press down firmly.
bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
cool.
cut into bars.
makes 24 to 36.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
buttermilk
butter
brown sugar
cinnamon
directions:
combine
the
brown sugar and the cinnamon.
divide the mixture
in
half
and
put into two separate bowls.
melt one stick of butter or margarine in small pan over low heat.
tear each
biscuit
into three pieces and roll into balls.
dip the balls in the melted butter and then into one bowl of the brown sugar
and cinnamon mixture.
roll around to coat evenly.
put into an ungreased bundt pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white sugar
milk
butter
cocoa
cooking oats
peanut butter
vanilla extract
walnuts
directions:
combine the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil, cooking 1 minute.
remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
stir and mix well.
drop by teaspoons onto wax paper, letting them stand for 30 minutes before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
butter
tomatoes
celery
soy sauce
cider vinegar
salt
directions:
wash the chicken wings and pat dry.
in skillet, saute chicken wings in melted butter until lightly browned.
arrange in oiled baking dish.
add tomatoes with liquid and celery.
in separate bowl, mix together soy sauce, vinegar and salt.
pour over chicken.
bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until tender. serves 4.
may be doubled to serve 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
onions
mushrooms
scallops
milk
mustard
cream sherry
parsley
freshly ground pepper
directions:
heat the butter in a heavy pot and stir in the onions and mushrooms.
cook them slowly, stirring occasionally for 20 to 25 minutes or until soft.
add the scallops and cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
add milk and meat slowly without boiling. stir in the mustard, sherry and parsley.
sprinkle with freshly ground pepper just before serving.
serve with crusty french bread and chilled frascati wine.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oil
pork
salt
pepper
garlic
cornstarch
directions:
put vegetable oil in frying pan (black iron skillet is best). add pork steaks, sprinkle generously with salt, pepper, garlic powder and brown on both sides.
when browned remove from pan and set aside.
add 2-3 cups of water to drippings in pan, add salt to taste.
bring to a slow boil and add cornstarch which has been diluted with water.
stir until thickened, put pork steaks back in pan with gravy and cover.
simmer about 1 1/2 -2 hours or until real tender.
serve with mashed potatoes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cut rhubarb
sugar
flour
cinnamon
cold water
red food coloring
directions:
pour mixed dry ingredients over rhubarb pieces in a bowl.
add cold water and mix together.
add food coloring.
pour into a greased pan.
cover with topping.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking soda
cinnamon
nutmeg
salt
raisins
water
egg
vegetable shortening
sugar
walnuts
directions:
grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
heat oven to 350°.
boil raisins rapidly in 2 cups water in uncovered medium sized saucepan for 10 minutes.
transfer to large bowl.
cool to lukewarm.
stir in egg, then shortening and sugar.
sift flour and dry ingredients together and add.
add raisin mixture and nuts.
bake for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
cool completely. frost with orange icing.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
butter
powdered sugar
vanilla
pecan chips
chocolate chips
directions:
melt butter; add to flour.
mix well.
add powdered sugar, vanilla, pecan chips and chocolate chips; mix well.
chill for 30 minutes.
roll mixture into small balls.
bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
roll in powdered sugar.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
cocoa
eggs
butter
pet milk
vanilla
pecans
directions:
stir or whisk liquids; add dry ingredients.
pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(middle of pie should shake and not be too firm).
do not overbake!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lean ground beef
green chilies
sour cream
taco seasoning mix
beans
avocado
cheese
tomatoes
green onions
olives
directions:
in skillet, brown meat; pour off fat.
add chilies.
in small bowl, combine sour cream and taco seasoning.
in 8-inch spring-form pan or on large plate, spread beans.
top with meat mixture, sour cream mixture and avocado dip.
cover; chill.
garnish and serve with tortilla chips.
refrigerate leftovers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg
sugar
milk
vanilla
flour
baking powder
salt
dates
nuts
xxxx sugar
directions:
mix together egg, sugar and milk.
add remaining ingredients (except xxxx sugar).
bake in a well-greased pan, 7 x 11-inch, at 350° for 30 minutes.
dust top with xxxx sugar and cut in squares.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cucumbers
fresh red chili
sugar
white vinegar
onion
cilantro
directions:
trim ends of cucumbers and scrape with fork to make a decorative pattern.
quarter the cucumbers lengthwise and remove seeds.
cut them crosswise into thin slices.
put in bowl and add chili.
in small saucepan, combine sugar and vinegar; bring to boil.
cook, stirring, until the sugar has dissolved.
cool to room temperature and pour sauce over the cucumber mixture.
chill and sprinkle with cilantro.
serves 4.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
onion
velveeta cheese
cream of chicken soup
ro-tel
chicken broth
doritos
directions:
cook and bone chicken.
place in casserole dish.
then slice onion on chicken.
slice velveeta on chicken and onion.
in a bowl, mix soup and ro-tel, 1 cup chicken broth and 1/2 of 10 ounce package doritos (whole).
pour mixture over chicken, onion and cheese.
on top, put rest of doritos.
bake 30 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cake flour
baking powder
salt
butter
sugar
eggs
milk
vanilla extract
oil
peanuts
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
set aside.
cream butter and sugar.
add eggs to creamed mixture.
combine milk, vanilla and oil in a measuring cup. alternate flour mixture and milk mixture until batter is blended. process the fruit/nut mixture until small pieces.
fold into batter.
bake in two 9-inch cake pans 35 to 40 minutes or bundt pan 50 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
milk
margarine
flour
baking powder
salt
blueberries
directions:
melt the margarine.
set aside.
beat the eggs.
gradually add sugar to eggs.
add the melted margarine.
add the cup of milk. combine dry ingredients and add them.
mix dough until flour is just blended.
fold berries into dough.
pour into well-greased loaf pan.
sprinkle top with sugar to give a sparkle.
bake for one hour in a 350° oven.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple cake mix
instant vanilla pudding
cold milk
cream cheese
pineapple
directions:
bake cake mix as directed in 3 pans. combine pudding mix, milk and cream cheese.
spread 1/3 of the pineapple on each cake layer, making sure layers are completely cool. spread pudding mixture on top of pineapple on each layer.
stack layers and cover with whipped topping.
a small amount of pudding mixture may be added to whipped topping to flavor.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cherries
pineapple
pecans
yellow cake
directions:
can use apple or any fruit.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tapioca
sugar
water
fruit juice
orange juice
mandarin oranges
peaches
frozen strawberries
bananas
directions:
cook tapioca, sugar and 1 cup of water until white is gone from tapioca.
remove from heat.
add fruit juice (use juice from peaches and oranges), orange juice, oranges, peaches and strawberries to tapioca.
cool until time to serve.
before serving slice and add bananas.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
macaroni
onion
bell pepper
tomato sauce
salt
water
pepper
worcestershire sauce
directions:
cook macaroni, onion and pepper until macaroni is yellow.
add ground beef to skillet along with rest of ingredients and cover. simmer 15 minutes until thick.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
golden delicious apples
golden raisins
brown sugar
ginger ale
directions:
using a melon baller, core apples without cutting through the bottom. stand apples in a baking dish just large enough to hold them. place 1 tablespoon raisins and 1 teaspoon brown sugar in center of each apple. pour in the ginger ale. bake at 350° for 45 minutes, basting frequently, until apples are tender but not mushy. serve warm or chilled, accompanied by ice cream or topped with whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
chilli powder
directions:
cut cream cheese in half long ways. roll into a log and roll into chilli powder covering all ends. serve with crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crawfish tails

butter

cheese.

cheese and lemonade with mixer.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
i

+
+

directions:

punch down dough and let rise another 30 minutes.
punch dough again.

divide into 3 even pieces.
roll each piece jelly roll fashion and place on large greased cooking sheet
2 inches apart seam side down.

let rise, covered, for 30 minutes.
make cuts on top of bread.
beat egg white with cold water.
brush over each loaf.
place pan of
hot water on bottom shelf in oven.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

green onions

directions:
combine and mix well.<|endofrecipe|>

let
stand
5
minutes. then drain and pat dry on paper

topping
directions:
cream the butter and cream cheese together.
add sugar and beat until fluffy.
add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
add vanilla.
gradually add flour, beating until smooth.
slowly stir in dream whip.
pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
chili powder
green chilies
cream of chicken soup
cream of mushroom soup
enchilada sauce
tortillas
cheddar cheese
directions:
brown lean ground beef; drain.
add chili powder and diced green chilies.
set aside.
heat cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and enchilada sauce; mix together.
add 1 1/2 cups of soup mixture to ground beef.
cover bottom of casserole dish with 4 large soft tortillas.
cover with 3/4 of beef mixture, then 4 tortillas, then 3/4 of soup mixture, then 4 tortillas, then the rest of both mixtures.
sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
cover with foil.
bake at 350° for 20 minutes; remove cover.
bake 10 minutes longer.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen pie pastry
green onions
butter
eggs
whipping cream
frozen crabmeat
swiss cheese
cooking sherry
salt
ground red pepper
directions:
prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
bake at 400° for 3 minutes; remove from oven and gently prick with a fork. bake pastry shell an additional 5 minutes; set aside.
saute onions in butter until tender; set aside.
combine eggs and cream in large bowl, stirring well.
stir in onions, crabmeat, cheese, sherry, salt and pepper.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yeast
sugar
soda
salt
flour
dill
butter
onion
egg
cottage cheese
directions:
soften yeast.
add cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill, salt, soda and egg.
alternately add flour.
beat well.
let rise about 1 to 2 hours.
stir dough to decrease bubbling.
put batter into 1 or 2 loaf pans.
let rise 30 more minutes.
bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
brush with butter.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
crisco
brown sugar
white sugar
eggs
soda
salt
flour
vanilla
oatmeal
nuts
directions:
cream and beat well first 4 ingredients.
add other ingredients.
dough will be stiff.
place dough by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
bake at 375° until slightly brown (about 8 to 10 minutes).
dough may be stored in refrigerator for several days.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
vanilla
salt
confectioners sugar
flour
nuts
directions:
cream butter and sugar.
add vanilla, flour, salt and nuts. mix well.
form into dime sized balls or flattened, if preferred. place on ungreased baking sheet.
bake at 250° for 25 minutes. while still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
makes 7 dozen cookies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
green pepper
onion
salt
cracker crumbs
egg
tomato sauce
potatoes
directions:
mix all ingredients except potatoes in large bowl.
shape into a loaf.
grease crock-pot.
wrap potatoes in foil and place in bottom.
(i cut my potatoes in half, but do not peel.)
place meat loaf on top of rack.
to make a full meal, use an aluminum pie pan, one that fits on top, and put in your vegetables.
i add butter and also wrap pie tin in foil.
cook 6 to 8 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white corn syrup
brown sugar
salt
butter
vanilla
eggs
pecans
directions:
combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
add eggs. pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
sprinkle pecans over all.
bake at 350° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
eggs
whipping cream
sugar
cake flour
directions:
in large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
add eggs already beaten.
blend in flour.
add whipped cream.
pour into greased and floured pan.
bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggplant
onion
bell pepper
bread crumbs
sharp cheese
tomatoes
directions:
peel and slice eggplant approximately 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick. salt and pepper and let stand a few minutes.
brown in wesson oil and drain.
in casserole dish, place 1 layer of eggplant, then onion, then pepper, cheese and tomatoes.
repeat if using a deep dish.

bake at 350° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
crisco
baking soda
salt
baking powder
sugar
yeast
buttermilk
directions:
sift dry ingredients together.
cut in crisco until mixed thoroughly.
add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
work together with a large spoon until all flour is moistened.
cover bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use as needed.
when ready to use, take out as much as needed, roll on a floured board to 1/2-inch thickness and cut.
bake at 400° on a cookie sheet or in a shallow pan for about 12 minutes, until brown.
the recipe makes about 6 dozen light flaky biscuits.
this dough will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
mushroom soup
sour cream
paprika
salt
directions:
remove skin from chicken; rinse.
sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
place chicken in a crock-pot.
stir together soup and sour cream; spoon over chicken.
cook on low 8 to 9 hours.
the "natural" gravy is delicious spooned over rice.
(may be cooked on high for half the time, but don't add the sour cream until the last 30 minutes.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oil
onion
noodles
chicken broth
broccoli
milk
velveeta cheese
pepper
directions:
heat onion in oil for 3 minutes.
add chicken broth and heat to boiling.
gradually add dry noodles so it continues to boil. cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
stir in broccoli.
cook 5 minutes more.
add milk, cheese and pepper until cheese melts. stir constantly.
serves 16.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
corn syrup
butter
pecans
directions:
beat eggs.
stir in sugar, corn syrup, melted butter and chopped pecans.
pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until slightly firm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bisquick mix
hot sausage
sharp cheese
directions:
mix all ingredients together.
roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
cook at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef stock
macaroni
salt
mixed vegetables
tomatoes
onion
pepper
directions:
mix all ingredients in a large pot.
chop onion real fine. add more or less salt and pepper.
cook for 1 hour or until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
angel food cake
whipping cream
pudding
pineapple
directions:
make the cake according to box.
cool.
with a bread knife or electric knife, slice into 3 or 4 layers.
whip cream until peaks form.
fold in dry pudding.
then fold in drained pineapple. spread between layers, top and sides.
refrigerate.
can decorate top with mandarin orange slices.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pepper
onion
meal
egg
oleo
graham crackers
lemon jello
boiling water
cream cheese
sugar
carnation milk
vanilla
lemon
directions:
roll crackers and mix with butter.
use one-half for bottom crust and press into a 6 x 12 x 2-inch pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
nondairy creamer
powdered sugar
directions:
mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in airtight container.
dissolve 1/3 cup mix in 1 cup hot water.
contains 120 calories/cup -
no fat.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange juice
water
milk
sugar
vanilla
cubes
directions:
blend all ingredients in blender, adding more ice if needed for consistency.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
velveeta cheese
bread
eggs
milk
salt
pepper
mustard
directions:
place cubed bread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
sprinkle over the cubed spam (may use ham or browned sausage links).
beat eggs; add spices and milk.
mix and pour over bread.

refrigerate overnight.
bake 1 hour at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread
parmesan cheese
green chiles
mayonnaise
directions:
split bread horizontally.
mix all ingredients together and spread
on both sides of bread.
place under broiler until lightly brown and bubbly, approximately 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of mushroom soup
salt
cream of chicken soup
chicken
cheddar cheese
green onions
green chilies
sour cream
flour tortilla
directions:
combine soups, chicken, chilies, sour cream, salt, pepper, and garlic.
simmer for a few minutes.

sprinkle with a few green onions and cheese.
roll tortilla and place in baking dish.
repeat with desired number of tortillas.
pour remaining sauce over tortillas. sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on top. bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
peaches
sugar
baking mix
ground cinnamon
brown sugar
milk
directions:
in a quart shallow casserole, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
in medium bowl,
mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
cut in margarine until mixture is size of small peas.
stir in milk until moistened; drop by spoonful onto peaches.
bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean. let stand 5 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sandies
walnuts
butter
chocolate
sugar
eggs
vanilla
breyers golden vanilla ice cream
directions:
crush pecan sandies and walnuts.
melt butter and chocolate; add sugar.
beat until smooth; add 3 egg yolks and vanilla.
fold in 3 egg whites (beaten stiff).

spread chocolate mixture over this.

spread ice cream over top and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top of this.
crush heath bars.
spread on top.
freeze overnight.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork loin
egg
milk
ground red pepper
garlic powder
italian style seasoned bread crumbs
flour
ground pecans
parmesan cheese
directions:
between 2 sheets of plastic/wax wrap, pound meat to 1/4-inch thickness.
combine egg, milk, pepper and garlic in bowl.
in another bowl, combine bread crumbs, pecans and parmesan.
coat meat in flour.
dip slices into egg mixture, then coat with crumb mixture.
place on greased baking sheet.
bake approximately 30 minutes at 375° or until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg
sour cream
flour
baking powder
salt
oil
cinnamon
sugar
flour
baking soda
nutmeg
golden raisins
sugar
powdered sugar
directions:
in mixing bowl, beat egg. gradually add sugar and beat until very light.
stir in sour cream. combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg and salt. stir in the raisins. add to egg mixture, stirring until smooth. chill dough 1 hour or more. roll out on lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thickness. cut with a round cutter 1 to 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
make an "x" slash on top of each with a sharp knife. fry in hot oil at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden and cooked through the middle. mix sugar and cinnamon. dust the hot cooked puffs with mixture or dust with plain powdered sugar.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork sausage
cheddar cheese
bisquick
directions:
mix by hand.
shape into balls (walnut-size).
bake in 425° oven until brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
butter
powdered sugar
maple flavoring
peanuts
directions:
mix cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and maple flavoring together real well.
put in refrigerator and chill.
form in balls and dip in chocolate.
mix peanuts and chocolate and put a cluster on top of each one.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef

onion
green pepper

tomatoes
spaghetti sauce
salsa
mushrooms
pepperoncini salad peppers
shell macaroni

directions:

sprinkle with half of parmesan and mozzarella cheeses.

bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated; top with remaining cheeses. bake 5 additional minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
buttermilk
butter
eggs
flour
sugar
directions:
cream butter, sugar and egg yolks; add flour.
beat well.
add buttermilk and stir well.

stir enough to mix.
bake as any custard pie in unbaked shell.
tastes very much like coconut custard pie.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
haddock fillets
lemon juice
mustard
worcestershire sauce
salt
pepper
onions
cream
directions:
mix lemon, pepper, salt, mustard and worcestershire sauce.
mix with cream and pour over fish.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
white onion
celery
macaroni
green pepper
salt
tomatoes

chili powder
directions:

use 2 to 3 tablespoons beef fat to saute chopped onion, celery and green pepper.

add hamburger, macaroni and as much tomato sauce as needed.
also, add desired amount of salt, pepper and chili powder (and a few dashes of tabasco sauce, if desired). simmer at least 30 minutes.
(you may need to add additional tomato sauce and/or water.)
no beans!
enjoy!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

vanilla
pecans
chocolate chips

coconut

put in freezer while chocolate is melting.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mixed vegetables
water
directions:

add vegetables, tomato sauce, water, gravy mix and wieners.
cook on medium-high until hot and bubbly.
i double this recipe for my family.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pepper

cheese
flour
butter
salt
milk
eggs
directions:

melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.

add eggs and half of sauce.

pour remaining sauce over top. sprinkle with grated cheese.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg

oil
pumpkin

nutmeg
baking powder
salt
cloves
cream of tartar

cinnamon
shortening
directions:
mix together egg, milk, oil and pumpkin.
mix dry ingredients. cut shortening into dry ingredients.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread
water
eggs
ground beef
parmesan cheese
parsley

garlic powder
pepper
directions:
soak bread in water for 2 to 3 minutes.
add eggs and mix well.
add remaining ingredients.
with wet hands, form meat mixture into small balls.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

stir well. blend in butter and vanilla. stir over double boiler until starts to thicken, then approximately 1 minute longer.

garnish with sliced bananas and whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs

salt

drain.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

white balsamic vinegar
directions:
cook orzo according to directions. drain. add remaining ingredients.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

nuts
margarine
egg whites
sugar
strawberries

heavy cream
directions:
stir together first 4 ingredients and spread evenly in shallow baking dish.

fold in the heavy cream (whipped).

sprinkle remaining 1/3 crumbs over top. freeze overnight. cut into squares.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs

salt
directions:

sauce, 1/2 cup cheese mix, lasagna pasta, 1 1/2 cups meat sauce, 1/2 cheese, lasagna pasta and rest of meat sauce. bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, covered, then 10 minutes uncovered.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
lime juice concentrate
milk
graham cracker crust
directions:
combine first 4 ingredients.
pour into pie crust and chill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
cocoa

butter

nuts
directions:
combine sugar, cocoa, syrup and milk.
stir well.
add salt and butter.
place on medium heat and bring to a rapid boil, as soon as mixture begins to boil, time for 6 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beans
green beans
beans
kidney beans
onion
celery
sugar

salad oil
directions:

chill well. mix cool whip, pecans and pineapple together.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

add 1/4 cup pecans and reserve the rest.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cracklins
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

tomatoes
chili mix
salt

garlic
directions:
brown hamburger and onions, drain fat off.
add other ingredients and cook until done. serve warm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

walnuts
directions:
beat egg whites until fluffy.
gradually add sugar.
beat until very stiff.
fold in chocolate chips and chopped nuts. grease cookie sheet.
drop by teaspoonfuls onto the sheet. preheat oven to 350° (must be a preheated oven!).
place cookies in oven and turn the oven off!
leave the cookies in the oven for 12 hours.
don't open the oven door.
get to make at night and go to sleep.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
lard
salt
egg
milk
directions:
mix flour, lard and salt up good.
beat egg in cup; add enough milk to finish filling cup.
pour egg and milk mixture over flour and lard mixture.

freezes very good.
makes about 7 crusts according to pan size.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pasta
lemon yogurt
mayonnaise
lemon juice
chunk breast of chicken
red grapes
green onions
celery
directions:
cook pasta; rinse in cold water and drain.
in a large bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise and lemon juice.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crescent dinner rolls
cherry pie filling
water
butter
sugar
directions:
cook rolls according to directions.
heat pie filling with water, sugar and butter and spread over a layer of rolls which have been placed in a baking dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
eggs
flour
baking powder
salt
directions:

mix well.
beat egg whites until rounded peaks form.

pepper

fresh parsley
green onions
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mandarin oranges
cherries
pineapple
fruit cocktail
sour cream
marshmallows
sugar
directions:
drain all fruit.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
spread cookie dough on a lightly greased pizza pan.
bake and cool.
combine cream cheese and cool whip.
spread mixture on cool cookie crust.
then top with fruit.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

parsley
directions:
cook the soba noodles according to package instructions. drain. rinse with cold water. drain again. transfer to a large bowl and toss with sesame oil. place the snow peas in a colander and pour boiling water over them. rinse with cold water and drain. add the snow peas, turkey, scallions and parsley to the noodles and toss. gradually add the peanut sauce and gently toss together until well combined. serve the noodle salad chilled or at room temperature. serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
blackberries

directions:
measure blackberries that have been cleaned and washed.
crush well and add an equal amount of sugar in a large kettle.
mix well.

beat
well.	add

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
salt
milk

rum flavoring
directions:
if using blender, cut recipe in half.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

milk

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

pepper
cloves

salt

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes

garlic salt
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brussels
olive oil
garlic
balsamic vinegar
yellow onion
butter
salt
directions:
trim off the stems and remove any limp leaves from brussels sprouts.

oil
