white kidney beans
red kidney beans
butter
tomato paste
italian sausage
onion
oregano
mustard
brown sugar
directions:
cut sausage in bite size pieces and brown in frying pan.
brown onion in sausage juice.
add tomato paste and 1 or more cans of water, salt, pepper, a little oregano, 1/2 teaspoon dry mustard and 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
simmer about 10 minutes.
add drained beans and browned sausage.
mix well.
spoon into casserole or oblong baking dish.
bake 45 to 60 minutes uncovered at 350°.
this recipe may be prepared the night before and baked the next day.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cheddar cheese
broccoli
cauliflower
bacon
onion
tomato
mayonnaise
sugar
vinegar
directions:
in a large salad bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion and tomatoes.
set aside.
in another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix until smooth.
just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.
yields 6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
peanut butter
powdered sugar
vanilla
chocolate chips
paraffin wax
directions:
mix together the margarine, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl with wooden spoon.
refrigerate.
roll into 1-inch balls.
refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
zucchini
sugar
lemon juice
pineapple
apricot jello
directions:
place zucchini in small amount of water and cook for 6 minutes.
add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple with juice and cook 6 more minutes.
remove from heat and add the jello.
stir until jello is dissolved.
place in jars and freeze.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chocolate
vanilla
condensed milk
walnuts
directions:
microwave chocolate and milk in large bowl on high 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time. remove from microwave. stir in vanilla and walnuts. spread in greased 8-inch square pan. refrigerate until firm. cut into squares. makes 4 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn husks
cornmeal
baking powder
chilies
egg
margarine
honey
flour
salt
milk
directions:
mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and 3/4 cup cheese. make a well in the center.
mix beaten egg, margarine, honey and milk.
pour into well in center of mix.
stir just to moisten. grease twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin tins.
place 2 or 3 strips of corn husks in each tin.
fill with batter and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
bake at 375°
for 20 minutes.
these will keep at room temperature for 12 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
any kind blueberries
lemon rind
brown sugar
all-purpose
ground cinnamon
butter
directions:
put berries in dish.
sprinkle with lemon rind (optional). blend ingredients and sprinkle on berries.
bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
celery
bell pepper
garlic
head lettuce
ground cumin
onion
tomatoes
corn chips
ro-tel tomatoes
salt
chili powder
directions:
brown meat.
saute vegetables.
combine the two and simmer. season with salt, chili powder and cumin.
in top of double boiler, melt cheese.
add ro-tel tomatoes.
cut lettuce coarsely and dice tomatoes.
put in large bowl.
add meat and vegetables and mix lightly.
add slightly crushed corn chips and toss.
top with hot cheese mixture.
serve immediately.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
baking potatoes
margarine
parmesan cheese
mozzarella cheese
salt
pepper
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes. place in baking dish.
melt margarine and pour on top of potatoes. add salt and pepper and 1/4 cup parmesan cheese; stir.
place in oven and bake for 1 hour.
halfway through cooking time, add 1/4 cup parmesan cheese and stir.
add mozzarella cheese, if desired, 5 minutes before removing from oven.
great with grilled steaks. serves 4 to 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
zucchini
sour cream
cream of chicken soup
carrot
onion
margarine
eggs
herb stuffing mix
grated cheese
directions:
saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine along with carrot and zucchini.
put half of stuffing in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
combine sauteed vegetables, sour cream, soup and eggs.
pour over stuffing.
place remainder of stuffing on top.
drizzle margarine and add grated cheese.
bake at 350° for 1 hour or until baked through.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mayonnaise
sour cream
italian salad dressing mix
red pepper
green pepper
directions:
mix until well blended.
serve with fresh, raw vegetables or chips.
makes 2 1/4 cups.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg yolks
water
flour
water
chicken bouillon
chicken
directions:
mix eggs with water, add flour enough to it looks like pie crust, roll on floured counter, put flour on top of mixture, roll like jelly roll, cut 1 inch strips and let sit for 1/2 hour to dry a little, using a kettle boil your chicken extra with chicken bouillon and add noodles cook until they float to the top and then turn them to simmer and while they are simmering.
fry up the remainder of the chicken.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
onions
green peppers
stalks celery
thyme
salt
pepper
lemon
water
flour
butter
sherry
directions:
simmer first 9 ingredients until vegetables are tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
add minced clams, juice and all.
cook another 5 minutes.
in blender mix flour, 1/2 quart half and half and melted butter.
add to chowder.
then add rest of half and half.
add 1/8 to 1/4 pound more butter and a dash or 2 of tabasco.
serve with 1 tablespoon sherry (i add more).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shrimp
fresh crabmeat
parsley
oregano
salt
parmesan cheese
bread crumbs
mustard
mayonnaise
directions:
peel and devein shrimp, leaving tail intact.
butterfly and flatten
shrimp.
mix
all remaining ingredients together and stuff shrimp.
bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
serves 4.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apricot halves
butter
brown sugar
slivered almonds
layer
ground nutmeg
frozen dessert topping
directions:
drain apricots, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
preheat oven to 350°.
place butter or margarine in a 9x1 1/2-inch round baking pan.
melt butter in pan in oven while preheating.
remove pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cherry pie filling
pineapple
yellow cake
margarine
coconut
nuts
directions:
spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with pam.
spread ingredients in layers according to way listed; pie filling first and crushed nuts last.
do not stir.
bake 1 hour at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
rhubarb
sugar
water
strawberry jello
pineapple
nuts
directions:
cook rhubarb with sugar and water until tender.
while still hot, add strawberry jello and stir, then add pineapple and nuts. cool and refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornstarch
sugar
o
berries
directions:
mix together cornstarch, sugar and 7-up.
cook to boiling about 5 minutes (until thickens).
add jell-o.
mix and let boil.
put in refrigerator and let cool for about 20 minutes.
add berries and pour into pie shell.
let chill.
serve with cool whip.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pastry shell
pork sausage
onion
green pepper
sweet pepper
cheddar cheese
eggs
flour
parsley
salt
garlic salt
pepper
light cream
directions:
heat oven to 425°.
prepare pastry shell.
bake 7 minutes. remove from oven; reduce oven temperature to 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh mushrooms
butter
onions
bread crumbs
cheddar cheese
walnuts
parsley
salt
black pepper
directions:
rinse mushrooms and pat dry.
remove stems; chop and set aside.
in large skillet, melt butter.
brush mushroom caps with melted butter; place on lightly buttered shallow baking pan.
to remaining butter, add onions and mushroom stems.
saute 2 minutes. add crumbs, cheese, nuts, parsley, salt and pepper; stir.
spoon into mushroom caps, piling high.
bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes
black olives
scallions
clove garlic
salt
freshly ground pepper
fresh basil
olive oil
pasta
directions:
combine all ingredients except pasta.
in a large bowl, let rest covered for at least 2 hours to develop flavor.
toss cooked pasta into sauce and serve at room temperature.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
strawberries
sugar
directions:
put all ingredients into a liquidiser and switch on!
when light and frothy, chill in fridge until ready to eat.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
glycerine
water
directions:
mix ingredients in a jar.
place stems of flowers in the jar. remove jar to a dark spot for 2 weeks (can be left longer if desired).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sugar
soda
eggs
nuts
bananas
flour
salt
directions:
cream butter and sugar well.
beat eggs and add to butter and sugar.
mash bananas well and add to butter and sugar.
add salt and soda to flour.
add to batter and mix well.
add nuts.
bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peaches
butter
flour
sugar
milk
directions:
melt butter in cake pan.
in bowl, mix the flour, sugar and milk. add to melted butter.
pour peaches into mixture.
bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(other fruits can be used.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bananas
lemonade concentrate
orange juice concentrate
pineapple juice
water
lemon-lime soda
club soda
directions:
in blender, combine bananas, lemonade concentrate and orange concentrate; blend for 1 minute or until smooth.
(if blender is unavailable, combine ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer.)
pour into large container (1 gallon size); add pineapple juice and water.
freeze overnight.
(may be frozen up to 6 months.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
marshmallow creme
directions:
mix on low speed until blended.
may be served with sliced apples, strawberries, grapes or fruit of your choice.
makes a good appetizer or party dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sauerkraut
salad dressing
swiss cheese
corned beef
directions:
combine all ingredients in baking dish. bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. serve hot with snack crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
syrup
sugar
margarine
vanilla
pecans
shell
directions:
in a large bowl stir first five ingredients.
pour into unbaked pie shell.
lay pecans on top and bake 50 to 55 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white sugar
peanut butter
brown sugar
salt
margarine
marshmallow cream
vanilla
milk
directions:
cook sugar, butter, milk, salt and vanilla to a soft ball stage; add marshmallow cream and peanut butter just before removing from stove.
then beat by hand until thick and creamy. pour in buttered pan; cool well before cutting into squares.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
oil
sugar
dry mustard
salt
vinegar
celery
directions:
mix all ingredients at once in a blender.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chilled milk
eggs
confectioners sugar
vanilla
orange juice
cracked ice
directions:
blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
sprinkle with nutmeg.
add ice cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
cream cheese
sour cream
vanilla
graham cracker crust
directions:
mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust. add fresh fruit or any canned fruit pie filling on top. refrigerate 2 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apples
raisins
brown sugar
red hots
raisins
directions:
remove core from the apples and take a little slice off the bottom to keep the apples from falling over.
mix up some raisins and brown sugar.
add some red hots or raisins if you want.
stuff inside
the
apples.
bake at 325° until tender. top with cool whip and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of mushroom soup
cream of shrimp soup
cream cheese
tabasco
shrimp
water chestnuts
lump crabmeat
dry mustard
mushrooms
worcestershire sauce
salt
directions:
heat soups; stir in cheese until melted and add remaining ingredients.
leave hot in chafing dish with melba rounds.
serves 75 to 80.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
semi-sweet chocolate chips
water
heavy cream
orange liqueur
directions:
put chocolate chips, water and cream into a sauce warmer. stir over moderate heat on stove until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
remove from heat and stir in orange liqueur.
keep warm over candle and dip in angel cake pieces, strawberries, oranges and the like.
serves 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
mayonnaise
buttermilk
directions:
mix together in a bowl.
fill greased muffin tins half full. bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
makes 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
crisco oil
eggs
orange juice
vanilla
baking powder
salt
baking apples
cinnamon
directions:
beat all ingredients together (except apples). place 1/2 of the batter into a greased tube pan. arrange enough sliced apples to cover. sprinkle with sugar & cinnamon to cover. repeat same process for second layer ending with sugar & cinnamon. bake at 325 degrees for 1 3/4 hours to 2 hours. (make sure a toothpick or small knitting needle inserted into cake is clean when removed.) remove from pan when lukewarm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
instant tea
sugar
cloves
cinnamon
directions:
mix well and keep in
a tight container.
put 2 heaping teaspoons to a cup.
finish filling with hot water (boiling).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
green peppers
bay leaves
lime
peppercorn
salt
vinegar
onions
hot chili pepper
cooking oil
chicken bouillon cube
directions:
clean and cut chicken in half or quarters.
put shredded onion on top.
mix juice from lime, oil, small amount of vinegar, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
pour over chicken and marinate for several hours.
about an hour or so before serving, have a hot charcoal fire with grill ready.
grill chicken, browning on all sides until almost blackened.
in a pot, heat a small amount of oil.
add chicken, green peppers, chili pepper (optional), chicken bouillon and all the marinade ingredients.
cover and cook gently until chicken is tender (about 30 minutes).
serve garnished with sliced tomatoes and lemons.
eat with rice or bread.
very good served with a mixed green salad.
lamb, beef or liver can be used in place of chicken.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bacon
beef shin bone
water
onion
stalks celery
tomatoes
salt
pepper
cayenne pepper
frozen mixed vegetables
mixed soup vegetables
crab meat
directions:
brown beef in soup pot with bacon strips.
add other ingredients, except frozen vegetables and crab meat.
cook 3 hours or until meat is tender.
add rest of ingredients and simmer covered until vegetables are done.
if you want it hotter, add a few dashes of tabasco sauce, or have it available on serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
white karo syrup
water
peanuts
butter
baking soda
vanilla
directions:
combine sugar, syrup and water.
bring to boil.
add peanuts and butter.
cook to 300°.
remove from heat; add baking soda and vanilla.
pour into greased cookie sheet.
should look green when first poured.
let cool.
break into pieces.
store in airtight container.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chocolate cake mix
chocolate pudding
milk
chocolate chips
heath bits
directions:
bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan. place 1/2 of cake in the bottom of a clear bowl or trifle dish. make pudding, using 3/4 cup more milk than is called for. pour 1/2 of the pudding over the cake. sprinkle with 1/2 bag of chocolate chips and 1/2 bag of heath bits over the cake and pudding. repeat layers. top with cool whip.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
caramels
margarine
milk
chocolate cake
pecans
directions:
preheat oven to 350 degrees.
in heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels and margarine.
remove from heat, add milk, mix well. follow package directions for cake mix; pour 2 cups batter into a 9 x 13 inch pan that has been sprayed with pam. bake 15 minutes. spread caramel mixture over cake; spread remaining batter over mixture. top with pecans.
return to oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onions
sirloin steak
green peppers
salt
garlic
soy sauce
directions:
cut steak in strips.
brown in small amount oil. push to one side.
add onion chunks.
simmer until onions are done.
add soy sauce, salt and garlic; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
add green peppers.
cover and simmer 5 minutes.
serve over hot cooked rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread
sandwich pepperoni
provolone cheese
egg
directions:
roll dough out into an oblong shape.
layer pepperoni, american and provolone cheeses alternately.
best if cheeses are layed out first, then pepperoni and then cheeses again.
roll up and seal edges.
brush with egg white.
bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mixed citrus fruit
amount
directions:
wash fruit well.
dry and peel very thinly.
cut the peel into shreds.
holding fruit over a bowl to catch the juice, cut off the pith and remove the seeds, tying them in cheesecloth bag, then slice the fruit thinly.
measure the fruit and juice and put in a large bowl with 3 times quantity of cold water, the pith and seeds and the shredded fruit.
let stand for 24 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
strawberry glaze
strawberries
cream cheese
frozen pie shells
directions:
bake pie shells until brown.
let cool.
mix sugar, cool whip and cream cheese together and spread in pie shells.
slice strawberries and mix in glaze.
spread on top of pies.
makes 2 pies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
powdered sugar
almond flavoring
milk
nut halves
candied cherries
directions:
place defrosted bread in oiled bowl and cover with tea towel. let rise in warm place 3 to 4 hours.
punch down (do not knead). stretch onto an oiled cookie sheet to approximately 8 1/2 x 12-inch rectangle.
spread with soft butter or oleo.
sprinkle with brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon, raisins, ground nuts and candied fruits.
roll like a jelly roll.
wet hands and pinch ends together securely, making a large ring.
cut with scissors every 1/2-inch around the ring.
using hands, twist each section to lay flatter and hide the cookie sheet.
let rise until almost double in warm place.
bake 1/2 hour at 350° until lightly browned.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sweet potatoes
butter
brown sugar
marshmallows
directions:
pour yams into casserole dish.
sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
cover with marshmallows and bake until marshmallows melt to a golden brown. make sure oven is preheated.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peanut butter
vegetable shortening
milk
egg
vanilla
light brown sugar
flour
salt
baking soda
directions:
combine peanut butter, shortening, sugar, milk and vanilla. beat until well mixed.
add egg and beat.
combine flour, salt and baking soda and add to the mixture.
mix.
drop by spoonful on baking sheet.
bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
fruit pie filling
flour
sugar
milk
directions:
melt the margarine in bottom of pan. pour the pie filling over margarine. mix the flour, sugar and milk. pour over top. bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
cream of tartar
soda
salt
shortening
sugar
eggs
sugar
cinnamon
directions:
sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
add shortening and sugar; beat at low speed.
add eggs.
batter should be dough-like; chill in refrigerator.
roll into balls.
bake at 350° for 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
wild rice
chicken broth
celery
green pepper
butter
flour
salt
curry
pimento
onion
carrot
clove garlic
mushrooms
white pepper
directions:
rinse rice with cold water; drain.
cook rice in chicken broth until tender.
saute celery, green pepper, onion, mushrooms, carrot and garlic in butter until tender.
add flour and cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
add broth, rice, salt, pepper, curry and pimento.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
margarine
flour
egg
brown sugar
margarine
pecans
almond extract
vanilla
salt
white syrup
directions:
mix cream cheese, margarine and flour.
roll into ball. chill for 1 hour or overnight. pinch out 8 balls.
press balls into muffin tin with fingers, working up to the top.
set aside. in a separate bowl, beat egg.
add brown sugar and mix well.
add margarine, vanilla, almond extract, white syrup, salt and chopped pecans.
put 1 tablespoon of the mixture into each cup.
bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
crisco
vinegar
water
egg
salt
directions:
cut crisco into flour and salt.
mix together vinegar, water and egg.
add to flour mixture and mix.
may be stored in refrigerator for several days.
makes 3 or 4 crusts.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
mushroom soup
american cheese
stuffing mix
margarine
directions:
layer ingredients in casserole in order given.
bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
serve over pasta shells.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen
onion
cottage cheese
butter
eggs
salt
cornbread mix
directions:
mix all ingredients except the cornbread mix.
add last.
pour into a greased 9 x 13 casserole dish.
bake for 15 to 25 minutes at 400°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green beans
mint flakes
butter
salt
directions:
in medium saucepan, heat green beans and mint flakes to boiling.
drain; toss with butter, then salt and pepper to taste. serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
vanilla instant pudding
vanilla
nutmeg
eggs
sugar
directions:
combine sugar, milk, pudding, egg yolk, vanilla and nutmeg until well blended.
beat egg whites until stiff with sugar.
fold into egg nog mixtures.
chill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
potatoes
egg yolks
cream
beets
onions
capers
salt
white pepper
paprika
butter
directions:
mix minced beef with mashed potatoes and egg yolks; gradually stir in cream.
add diced beets, onions and capers.
stir carefully and season with salt, paprika and white pepper.
shape into round, flat cakes about 1-inch thick and fry in hot butter over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
serve with fresh vegetables.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green tomatoes
salt
sugar
vinegar
cinnamon
mace
cloves
butter
unbaked pie shells
directions:
slice
tomatoes
into unbaked pie shell.
mix remaining ingredients;
pour over tomatoes.
cover with top crust; flute edges and
make
several slits in the top.	bake at 375° about 35 to 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
bananas
apples
maraschino cherries
coconut
pecans
directions:
combine all ingredients and mix well.
pour cooled dressing (amount according to personal preference) over all and stir well. makes about 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lean ground beef
garlic
picante sauce
tomatoes
black
whole kernel corn
ground cumin
chili powder
green onions
flour tortillas
picante sauce
shredded cheese
directions:
brown
ground beef with
minced
garlic.
add
1/2
cup picante sauce, tomatoes, beans,
corn, cumin and chili powder. mix well.
cook, uncovered,
stirring
frequently 5 minutes or until most
of the
liquid
has
evaporated.
stir
in
green onions. spoon about 1/3 cup
of
mixture
down
the center of each flour tortilla; roll up.	place
seam-side
down	in 13 x 9-inch baking dish sprayed
with vegetable spray.
spoon 1 cup picante sauce evenly over
enchiladas.
bake, covered, at 350° for 15 minutes or until
hot.
top
with
cheese and return to oven 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
top with sour cream and additional picante sauce, if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sugar
eggs
swans
lemon flavor
lemon juice
directions:
in large bowl cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. add eggs one at a time and mix well after each egg.
add flour, 7-up, flavor and juice.
mix until flour is blended in, then blend until smooth about 3 minutes at high speed.
pour batter into bundt cake pan.
bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes. remove from oven.
cool 10 minutes in pan and remove to cake plate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
applesauce
baking soda
butter
sugar
ground cinnamon
ground cloves
ground nutmeg
all-purpose
cherry preserves
pineapple preserves
pecans
directions:
combine applesauce, soda and butter in saucepan; heat on low and let cool.

mix together.

cook it on the grill on low for approximately 30 minutes.
once the potatoes are done, open the packet (be careful of the steam), put slices of the cheese on the potatoes and close the packet up so it can melt.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yeast
water
yellow cake mix
flour
salt
butter
directions:
dissolve yeast in water, add cake mix, flour and salt. mix and let rise for 1 hour. punch down and roll out into oblong. cover with butter, sugar, cinnamon and nuts. roll up and slice about 2 inches thick. place on cookie sheet, let set about 20 minutes. bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
clove garlic
butter
tomato sauce
mushrooms
olives
oregano
sugar
salt
white pepper
parmesan cheese
directions:
place fish in greased baking dish.
saute onion and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
add tomato sauce, mushrooms, olives, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper.
heat through.
pour over halibut and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
serves 4 to 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
butter
salt
rice
cream of mushroom soup
cream of chicken soup
cream of celery soup
directions:
dip the chicken pieces in melted butter or brush with butter and season with salt and pepper.
mix rice with soups and spread in a shallow, buttered casserole.
top with chicken breasts and bake at 300° for 2 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread
regular butterscotch pudding
light brown sugar
walnuts
cinnamon
butter
directions:
let frozen dough thaw until pliable.
grease a 12-cup bundt (tube ) pan.
sprinkle 1/2 cup of the brown sugar on bottom of pan.
top with walnuts and set aside.
in small bowl, combine pudding mix, remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
cut thawed dough into 24 pieces (rolls do not need to be cut).
dip each piece in melted butter, then roll in butterscotch mixture. arrange dough balls on top of nut mixture in pan.
the pan should be filled at least half-way with dough.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
cheddar cheese
chicken
onion
milk
eggs
bisquick baking mix
salt
pepper
directions:
heat oven to 400°.
grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches). rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw; drain.
mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese, chicken and onion in plate.
beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth.
pour into plate.
bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes. top with remaining cheese.
bake just until cheese is melted. makes 6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
beef gravy
mushrooms
catsup
sherry
sour cream
noodles
directions:
in a saucepan, brown hamburger and drain.
stir in gravy. stir in undrained mushrooms and catsup.
add 1 cup water.
cover; bring to boiling.
simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
stir in wine. gradually blend 1 cup beef mixture into sour cream dip.
return to saucepan.
heat through.
do not boil.
serve over noodles. sprinkle with paprika.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
long grain rice
onion
broccoli flowerets
tomato soup
cheddar cheese
salt
green
directions:
butter a large casserole.
cook broccoli and green onion in a small amount of water with dash of salt for 5 to 6 minutes.
drain well.
mix soup and half and half in bowl.
in casserole, layer rice, broccoli, green onions and ham.
pour soup mixture over; top with shredded cheese.
bake at 375° for approximately 35 minutes or until cheese is melted and light brown.
serve hot from oven with salad and rolls.
makes 4 to 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange jello
boiling water
orange juice
pineapple
oranges
instant vanilla pudding
cold milk
directions:
blend well the jello and boiling water.
add the next three ingredients and let it gel.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
crisco
eggs
baking powder
flour
milk
vanilla
directions:
add, in the order listed, and mix well.
pour into oblong baking pan or dish.
bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
cool and add fresh strawberries and milk, if so desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
rice
oleo
onion
beef broth
water
mushrooms
directions:
saute rice, spices and butter. add other ingredients and cook, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
vanilla
cake flour
baking powder
salt
milk
butter
directions:
combine first 3 ingredients and beat well, then add dry ingredients which have been sifted together. scald milk and add butter. combine the 2 mixtures and beat well.
pour into square, flat pan and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. remove from oven and add frosting, then return to hot oven for frosting to brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hamburger
onion
potatoes
directions:
layer 1 pound hamburger, onion, potatoes and 1 pound hamburger.
cook 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
drain and cover with a 10 ounce package of cheddar cheese.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pasta
bacon
onion
garlic
oregano
black pepper
red pepper
tomatoes
red wine vinegar
salmon
heavy cream
parmesan cheese
directions:
cook pasta according to package directions; drain and keep warm.
in 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
drain, reserving 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
add onion, garlic, basil, oregano and peppers.
cook 5 minutes.
add tomatoes and vinegar; cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until slightly thickened. stir in salmon and cream; heat through.
serve over hot pasta and garnish with parmesan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
sugar
egg
milk
flour
baking powder
salt
nutmeg
blueberries
directions:
cream shortening and sugar.
then add egg and milk.
beat until smooth.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
head cabbage
frozen peas
salt
black pepper
oil
ginger paste
garlic
turmeric
directions:
in a bowl, microwave peas for 4 minutes, covered. heat oil in a 10-inch skillet. add ginger and garlic. add peas and cabbage. stir-fry on medium-low heat until crisp-tender. add salt and black pepper. (do not overcook when cabbage is soft.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crackers
sugar
pecans
egg whites
sugar
vanilla
directions:
mix the first 3 ingredients together in small bowl.
set aside.
put egg whites in a large mixing bowl and beat until it forms peaks.
slowly add sugar, then vanilla.
add first bowl of dry ingredients and fold together gently with large spoon.
pour into 9-inch pie plate.
bake at 325° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
margarine
flour
hamburger
salt
pepper
garlic salt
mushrooms
condensed cream
sour cream
directions:
brown hamburger, onion and garlic salt; drain off fat.
add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms (juice and all).
cook for 5 minutes.
add soup; simmer for 10 minutes.
add sour cream; heat through.
serve over hot buttered noodles.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
semi-sweet chocolate
butter
cashews
pecans
walnuts
directions:
melt chocolate in double boiler; add butter and stir.
stir in nuts.
drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
refrigerate until hard.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bean dip
cream cheese
taco mix
sour cream
cheddar cheese
directions:
mix bean dip, cream cheese, taco mix and sour cream with a hand mixer.
pour into a casserole dish.
grate cheese and sprinkle on top.
garnish with peppers.
bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
serve hot with nacho chips.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
velveeta cheese macaroni
water
mixed veggies
cheese
directions:
kids love this; with your help, they can prepare dinner.
make macaroni and cheese according to directions.
steam veggies and drain.
fluff tuna with fork in small bowl or big bowl if children are doing it.
mix first three ingredients together and sprinkle with cheese.
bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
italian style
milk
onion
garlic salt
pepper
mozzarella cheese
pizza sauce
shredded lettuce
mushrooms
directions:
combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion, salt and pepper; mix well.
cover each cube of cheese with about 1 tablespoon of meat mixture, carefully sealing all around.
place meatballs in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
tomato sauce
sugar
olive oil
red wine vinegar
salt
dry mustard
worcestershire sauce
pepper sauce
onion
green pepper
whole kernel corn
celery
directions:
boil carrots in water or cook in small amount of water in microwave just until tender; drain and place in 2-quart covered casserole.
add onion, green pepper, corn and celery.
combine the remaining ingredients; heat 3 minutes in the microwave on high. stir and pour over vegetables.
cool, cover and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
makes 12 servings.
this salad will keep in the refrigerator at least one week.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
confectioners sugar
eggs
flour
lemon extract
vanilla
directions:
cream together the butter and confectioners sugar.
add the whole eggs, one at a time, beating each in well.
gradually add the flour, beating continually.
add lemon and vanilla extracts and mix thoroughly.
put batter in greased bundt pan and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread cubes
water
chicken
onions
stalks celery
chicken
salt
poultry seasoning
celery salt
eggs
margarine
directions:
place bread cubes in large mixing bowl and add enough water to soak and soften (about 1/2 pint).
in a cup of warm water, soak 8 chicken bouillon cubes.
into another bowl, mix onions cut fine and celery cut into medium pieces.
add chicken steaks, salt, poultry seasoning and savory or celery salt.
beat eggs and mix with broth from stakes and add to the mixture.
now add the mixture to the softened bread crumbs.
melt margarine; add and mix well.
pour into well-greased casserole dish.
bake about 2 hours at 350° or until golden brown.
can be served with mushroom sauce, if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
cream of mushroom soup
cream of chicken soup
stove top stuffing
frozen peas
directions:
cook and debone chicken.
in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine soups.
lay chicken on top of soups.
put in frozen peas. mix stuffing by directions on box; spread over chicken mixture. cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
good to make ahead and freeze.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking soda
cinnamon
ginger
cloves
salt
egg
butter
light molasses
hot water
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
grease a 9 x 9 x 1-inch pan.
sift flour with soda, spices and salt.
set aside.
in large bowl, beat eggs, butter, molasses and water until mixed well.
add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
pour into pan; bake 30 to 35 minutes.
cool partially in pan on wire rack.
serve warm.
it's a very good cake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
sugar
baking powder
salt
flour
peaches
sugar
corn starch
salt
directions:
mix together margarine, 3/4 c. sugar, baking powder, salt, and flour.
put fresh peaches in bottom of 9x9 baking dish.
put batter on top of peaches.
mix together sugar, cornstarch, and salt, and put over batter.
pour in 1 c. boiling water.
do not mix.
bake 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg
condensed milk
rum flavoring
ground nutmeg
whipping cream
directions:
beat eggs until foamy in top of a double boiler; stir in condensed milk.
cook over hot, not boiling, water 10 minutes. stir rum flavoring and nutmeg; fold in whipped cream.
serve hot or cold over fruitcake or ice cream.
yield:
about 2 cups.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
light brown sugar
banana
baking soda
butter
eggs
vanilla
directions:
combine baking soda, flour and salt with wire whisk. cream butter and sugar together. add eggs, banana and vanilla; beat until medium thick. add flour mixture. blend on low speed until combined. bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
duncan hines lemon cake mix
lemon jell-o
water
oil
eggs
directions:
mix together first four ingredients.
add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
pour in bundt pan that has been oiled and floured.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
powdered sugar
cream cheese
vanilla instant pudding mix
chocolate instant pudding
milk
whipped cream
pecan halves
shell
directions:
cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese; set aside. mix vanilla and chocolate pudding mixes with milk.
spread cream cheese mixture on bottom of cooled pie shell.
spread the pudding over this layer.
top with whipped cream.
arrange pecan halves on the whipped cream.
refrigerate until ready to serve.
serves 6 to 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn bread
broccoli
eggs
sharp cheese
fresh green onions
butter
salt
milk
directions:
chop
onions.
cook broccoli; drain well. combine onions, broccoli, eggs, margarine, salt, corn muffin mix and milk. pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. bake for 35 minutes at 350°. sprinkle cheese over top and return to oven until cheese is melted.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
onion
all-purpose
salt
pepper
paprika
flounder
lemon juice
worcestershire sauce
watercress
lemon wedges
directions:
about 45 minutes before serving, in 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine in large skillet, saute onion until tender.
remove to platter; keep warm.
meanwhile, combine flour with salt, pepper and paprika.
in it lay sole or flounder fillets, halved crosswise.
turn until coated.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
butter
lemon extract
lemon juice
eggs
flour
baking powder
salt
milk
grated rind
pecans
directions:
combine sugar, butter, extract and juice.
beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
in a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
stir in the wet ingredients alternately with the milk.
add the lemon rind and pecans.
pour batter into a greased 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch loaf pan.
bake for about 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cabbage
lean ground pork
onion
rice
egg
butter
salt
pepper
tomato soup
cream of mushroom soup
water
directions:
preparing cabbage:
remove core and place head in a large pot of boiling water.
cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
separate leaves and cut out heavy ribs.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork sausage
swiss cheese
cheddar cheese
eggs
milk
onion
green bell pepper
directions:
line pie pans with pie shells.	in bowl, combine sausage and cheeses.
place half of mixture in each shell.
combine eggs, milk, onion and peppers. pour half over sausage in each shell. bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
let stand 5 minutes before cutting.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
head lettuce
cauliflower
onion
bacon
directions:
cut up lettuce.
chop cauliflower and onion.
fry bacon until crisp.
crumble into bits.
sprinkle over lettuce mixture.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
eggs
oil
orange juice
vanilla
flour
salt
baking soda
cinnamon
apples
coconut
nuts
directions:
beat together sugar and eggs until fluffy. add oil, juice and vanilla. beat well. mix dry ingredients together and stir into egg mixture just until blended. do not beat. stir in apples, coconut and nuts. pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done in the center. pour the following glaze over cake while cake is still warm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
meal mix
milk
onion
egg
directions:
mix all together well and drop by small balls into hot oil. fry only a few at a time, until golden brown.
drain on paper towels.
serve hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tapioca pudding
orange jello
cold water
pineapple
mandarin oranges
marshmallows
directions:
combine tapioca pudding and orange jello with 3 cups cold water.
cook until clear or until boiling stage over medium heat. cool.
drain the crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
fold cool whip, miniature marshmallows, crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges into the cooled mixture.
place in 9 x 13-inch pan or jello mold and refrigerate until set.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
molasses
shortening
flour
water
soda
ginger
cinnamon
directions:
dissolve soda in hot water.
mix all ingredients and add enough flour to stiffen.
roll on a floured board.
cut in desired shapes and place on a greased cookie sheet.
bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
cornbread stuffing
margarine
mushroom soup

directions:

cool chicken and cut into large pieces.
mix cornbread stuffing in melted margarine.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
mushroom soup
eggs
mayonnaise
onion
crushed cheese
worcestershire sauce
salt
pepper
grated cheese
directions:
cook broccoli until done;
drain.
mix eggs, mayonnaise, soup, onion, worcestershire sauce,
salt and pepper.
pour over broccoli in a greased casserole
dish.
top with cheddar cheese and crushed ritz crackers.
place
in
oven, preheated to 350°. bake about 30 minutes or until firm.
serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brown sugar
margarine
eggs
flour
salt
baking powder
chocolate chips
directions:
cream together sugar and margarine or butter.
add eggs, one at a time.
sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
add to mixture.
add chips.
bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg whites
sugar
crackers
pecans
baking powder
salt
vanilla
almond extract
vanilla ice cream
directions:
generously butter and flour an 8-inch pie pan; set aside. preheat oven to 300°.
beat egg whites until foamy, then gradually add the sugar and beat until stiff.
fold in remaining ingredients.
pour into the prepared pie pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
cool completely.
serve topped with scoop of ice cream or whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bouillon cube
margarine
onion
season
water
directions:
bake at 400° until begins to brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
salmon
eggs
bread crumbs
onion
mayonnaise
horseradish
pimientos
salt
pepper
butter
kaiser rolls
lettuce leaves
directions:
combine the first 9 ingredients; mix well. shape into 4 patties. in a skillet over medium heat, cook patties in butter until browned, about 6 minutes on each side. serve on rolls with lettuce. yield: 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg whites
cream of tartar
sugar
unsweetened cocoa
directions:
preheat oven to 275°.
beat egg whites until foamy.
add cream of tartar and beat until soft peaks form.
gradually beat in sugar, a few tablespoons at a time.
beat until stiff.
fold in cocoa.
spray a baking sheet with a nonstick vegetable spray. drop batter by level teaspoon onto baking sheet.
bake 18 to 20 minutes.
cool before removing from baking sheet.
store in tight container.
makes 8 dozen cookies.
per cookie:
calories-9, fat-o grams, sodium-2 milligrams, cholesterol-0 milligrams.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
sugar
lemon gelatin
cream cheese
apples
nuts
celery
topping
directions:
in saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil. boil for 3 minutes; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
add cream cheese.
stir; cool.
fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
pour into 9-inch pan.
chill until firm (2 hours or so).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
molasses
shortening
flour
baking soda
ginger
salt
directions:
heat to boiling point the molasses.
pour it over shortening. sift together and stir this into the flour, baking soda, ginger and salt.
shape 1/4 the mixture at a time, keeping the rest of the dough in the refrigerator until you are ready to cut it out.
roll as thin as possible; cut with small, round cutter.
bake at 350° until crisp and dry (8 to 10 minutes).

keeps well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peach halves
cinnamon
whole cloves
allspice
white vinegar
directions:
put peach syrup in a saucepan, add spices and vinegar.
bring to a boil then simmer for 5 minutes.
pour over peaches, cover and refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yeast
oats
bread flour
salt
molasses
vegetable oil
water
directions:
place ingredients in bread machine.
select "white bread" setting.
yield:
1 large loaf.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen italian style vegetables
parmesan cheese
muffins
pizza sauce
mozzarella cheese
directions:
prepare vegetables according to package directions, omitting water.
stir in parmesan cheese.
spread pizza sauce on each muffin half.
top with vegetable mixture and mozzarella cheese. broil to melt cheese or microwave on high (100%) for 2 minutes. makes 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
eggs
water
italian bread crumbs
oil
sauce
mozzarella cheese
directions:
pound chicken breasts until tender.
mix eggs and water in a bowl.
pour bread crumbs onto a plate.
dip chicken into egg mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
brown the breaded chicken in skillet of oil; drain.
place chicken in ungreased casserole dish. cover with spaghetti sauce and top with cheese.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
cold shortening
milk
sugar
directions:
cut in shortening.
stir in milk quickly and knead lightly for a few seconds, using as little flour as possible on board.
roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with floured cutter.
cook in lightly greased hot skillet over very low heat until biscuits are brown on underside and raised to height of 1-inch.
turn and brown on other side.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
swiss cheese
cream of chicken soup
white wine
margarine
directions:
spray pam on a 9 x 13 pyrex dish. place cheese on top of each chicken breast. mix soup and white wine and pour over chicken. sprinkle herb seasoned bread crumbs over the top and pour margarine over crumbs. bake, uncovered, at 350° about an hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
white sugar
brown sugar
eggs
flour
salt
baking soda
potato chips
directions:
cream shortening and sugars; stir in eggs and mix well. combine together flour, salt, baking soda and chips and add to creamed mixture.
shape into little balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
press down with floured fork.
bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
onion
bell pepper
celery
black pepper
salt
water
cream of mushroom soup
long grain rice
directions:
turn oven to 350° to heat.
put whole chicken in big baking dish along with onion, bell peppers, celery, salt and black pepper. then add the four cups of water.
then let chicken bake for 35 minutes.
then add mushroom soup and long grain rice.
bake for another 30 minutes.
please cover rice and chicken while baking. take out of oven.
serves 10.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
butter
salt
cream of mushroom soup
chicken bouillon cubes
warm water
cooking sherry
directions:
put chicken in oblong dish or pan, skin side up.
bake, uncovered, at 400° for a few minutes.
dissolve bouillon in water. stir in soup and sherry.
pour over chicken.
cover with foil and cook at 250° for 4 hours.
serve over rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
onions
bell pepper
celery
garlic
parsley
crawfish tails
bread
salt
tabasco sauce
egg
bell peppers
directions:
saute onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic in butter or oleo until light brown.
add parsley, crawfish tails and french bread that has been soaked in water and squeezed out.
add salt and tabasco sauce. blend thoroughly. remove from heat. add egg and blend.
remove seeds and membranes from bell pepper halves and cook in boiling salted water about 5 minutes. drain.
pile crawfish mixture into pepper shells. garnish with whole crawfish tails, if desired.
bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
pistachio instant pudding
nuts
marshmallows
directions:
mix pudding mix and pineapple.
add nuts, marshmallows and cool whip.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crab meat
lemon juice
tabasco sauce
light cream
onion
garlic
cream cheese
mayonnaise
chives
salt
worcestershire sauce
directions:
pour lemon juice over crab meat and let drain.
combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and add crab.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter
mushrooms

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
yeast
salt
sugar
milk
margarine
directions:
dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water (warm to touch) with 1 teaspoon sugar.
set aside.
measure unsifted flour into the mixing bowl.
set aside.
combine remaining sugar and salt.
set aside. bring milk to boil over medium heat.
remove from heat and add sugar and salt.
stir well.
simmer until warm.
add eggs and yeast.
stir well.
pour into flour, a little at a time.
after mixing, add shortening.
mix well.
(dough will be sticky.)

add flour to smooth out stickiness.
knead for about 5 minutes.
let stand in covered pan until it has risen until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours at room temperature.
roll out into rolls or cut out shapes.
place rolls on a greased pan, then let them rise again (2 hours).

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
you may drain yogurt, using any one of several different methods:<|endofrecipe|>

n

a meal in one with your favorite veggies.<|endofrecipe|>

until

the
flour and sugar several times (4).
then mix rest of	ingredients together with flour.

for 20 minutes.

out. fill

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cake mix
oil
eggs
vanilla
directions:
combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix.
drop by teaspoonful.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
brown sugar
pecans
eggnog
sugar
pumpkin
heavy cream
unflavored gelatin
ground cinnamon
ground ginger
ground nutmeg
eggs
cream of tartar
bourbon
directions:
bake pie shell at 450° for 15 minutes.
while shell bakes, cream butter and brown sugar; stir in pecans.
spread in bottom of partly baked pie shell.
bake 5 minutes longer until shell is golden and nut mixture is bubbly.
cool on wire rack.
combine 1/2 cup sugar, gelatin, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg in a medium size saucepan; beat in egg yolks and eggnog.
heat slowly, stirring constantly, just until gelatin is completely dissolved.
stir in pumpkin; pour into a large bowl.
chill, stirring often, just until mixture mounds when spooned.
beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy white in a medium-size bowl.
beat in remaining 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until meringue stands in firm peaks. fold meringue and 1 cup of whipped cream into mixture.
blend in bourbon.
spoon into crust.
chill several hours until firm.
just before serving, garnish with remaining cream and extra pecans.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
cocoa
water
buttermilk
eggs
sugar
flour
vanilla
peanut butter
warm oil
directions:

in a bowl, combine next 3 ingredients; add to the other ingredients.
bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
let cool. prepare peanut butter and oil.
mix together and spread over cooled cake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vegetable oil
long
onion
clove garlic
tomato
broth

peas
carrot
cilantro

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

water

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mushrooms

directions:

if a round baking stone or pizza pan (greased) is used, separate into triangles and pinch seams together.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mix
all
together
except
the

pour well mixed sauce over all and cook 2 to 3 minutes until chicken is done and vegetables are crisp and tender.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lemon jell-o
water
mayonnaise
cottage cheese
onions
celery
corned beef
directions:
dissolve jell-o in hot water. stir in mayonnaise and let cool. mix remaining ingredients. refrigerate until set.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

flour
milk

directions:

cabbage
with
very
little
water until tender;

alternate a layer of cabbage, layer of
cheese
and a layer of white sauce.
top with a layer of
cheese
and
sprinkle with corn flake crumbs. bake in a 350° oven until cheese is brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
butter
brown sugar
vanilla
brown sugar
brown sugar
eggs
pecans
butter
directions:
combine flour and 3 tablespoons of brown sugar.
cut in 1/2 cup of butter for a coarse crumb consistency.
pat into an ungreased 11 x 7 pan.
bake at 375° for 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork
barbecue sauce
white raisins
brown sugar
onion
tart apple
bacon
directions:
mix all ingredients, laying strips of bacon on top.
bake at 350° for 1 hour.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
molasses
shortening
eggs
sour cream
baking soda
flour
ginger
cinnamon
salt
cloves
directions:
mix together sour cream and baking soda.
sift together last 5 ingredients.
mix all ingredients and drop onto greased cookie sheet.
bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken-rice
artichokes
mayonnaise
curry powder
black olives
water chestnuts
scallions
directions:
prepare chicken-rice mixture according to package directions. set aside.
mix reserved marinade, curry and mayonnaise.
add to rice with all other ingredients.
chill overnight.
serve on bed of lettuce with tomato garnish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork chops
brown sugar
lemon juice
dry mustard
directions:
marinate pork chops 2 hours, turning once.
grill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion soup
margarine
salt
corn
directions:
combine dry onion soup mix, margarine and salt.
mix well. spread each ear of corn with 1 tablespoon mixture.
wrap tightly in foil.
grill over hot coals for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender. serve with additional margarine, if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
celery soup
chicken broth
margarine
flour
milk
onion
directions:
boil the chicken with onion and salt until done.
remove from bones and cut in bite size pieces.
place chicken in casserole dish.
pour soup and chicken broth over chicken.
mix flour, milk and 1 stick melted margarine and pour on top. bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cocktail franks
pineapple
directions:
combine the first 4 ingredients in a pan and heat until jelly is melted.
pour into a crock-pot.
add franks and slow cook until franks are heated.
add pineapple at serving time.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crust
eggs
sugar
salt
butter
corn syrup
directions:
beat with rotary beater and add 1 cup pecan halves.
pour into unbaked pie shell.
bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of potato soup
cream of chicken soup
chicken broth
ground black pepper
bisquick
milk
mixed vegetables
chicken
vegetable cooking spray
directions:
preheat oven to 425°.
spray 9 x 13-inch baking with cooking spray.
drain vegetables in colander.
mix cream of potato soup and cream of chicken soup in mixing bowl.
add chicken broth, pepper, vegetables and chicken pieces and mix well.
pour mixture into baking pan.
in a mixing bowl, add bisquick and milk and mix until combined (the mixture will still be a little lumpy).
pour the bisquick mixture over the chicken.
bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
allow to cool for 5 minutes.
serves 6 to 8 people.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
crisco
egg
vinegar
cold water
directions:
can use a mixer to blend flour, salt and crisco.
add egg, vinegar and water, mixing lightly with a fork.
pour on plastic wrap.
press dough to oblong shape and wrap and let stand a few minutes.
cut in 4 even shapes and roll out each one.
bake shells 10 to 15 minutes.
prick with fork before baking in a 425° oven. makes 2 double crusts or 4 single.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cakes
butterfinger
powdered sugar
butter
egg yolks
directions:
mix the powdered sugar, melted butter, cool whip and egg yolks together.
place in a large bowl in layers the cake, filling and butterfingers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
curry powder
oysters
parsley
pecans
directions:
mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
this mixture may have to be refrigerated for a few minutes to make it easier to handle.
roll ball in additional chopped pecans, then roll lightly in additional finely chopped parsley.
chill.
serve with assorted crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
strawberry
duncan
dream whip
vanilla instant pudding
cold milk
vanilla extract
directions:
dissolve jell-o in 3/4 cup boiling water.
add 1/2 cup cold water and set aside.
mix and bake cake as directed on box.
when cake is done, let cool 20 to 25 minutes.
poke holes in cake (i use a large, 2-pronged fork that we use for barbecuing).
pour jell-o slowly in holes.
put cake in refrigerator.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
garlic
salad oil
zucchini
tomatoes
mushrooms
tomato paste
olives
oregano
parsley sprigs
directions:
in 1 1/2 quart casserole, cook onion, garlic and oil on high, covered, 4 to 4 1/2 minutes in microwave.
cut zucchini lengthwise in half, then crosswise in 1/4 inch slices.
add onion mixture with next 3 ingredients.
cook covered on high 10 minutes.
stir once.
add olives; cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes, until tender. sprinkle fish steaks with oregano.
moisten 2 paper towels; place fish steak on each towel.
twist corners together.
cook on high 2 1/2 minutes, just until outer edges of fish are opaque.
serve sauce and fish on plate with garnish.
makes 2 main dishes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
flour
vinegar
shell
sugar
vanilla
eggs
directions:
mix ingredients well.
pour into pie crust and bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hamburger

chicken/mushroom soup

directions:
brown hamburger meat and chopped onion in pan.
in 9 1/2 x 13-inch cake pan, pour 3 cans soup (no water), 1 small jar picante sauce, the meat and crushed chips.
mix well together.
bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
shred cheese on top; melt in oven for 5 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

garlic

chili powder
tomato sauce

paprika
water

directions:
brown onion and garlic in bacon drippings; add meat and cook until gray.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs
flour

nuts
directions:
cream margarine and sugar.
beat eggs and add and beat well. add flour.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

add bread crumbs, salt, pepper and sherry.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar

flour

directions:

let stand 1 hour, stirring often.
(frozen pears may be used for fresh ones.)

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar

peanut butter
directions:
note:
if you want chocolate peanut butter, add 4 tablespoons of cocoa.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

bananas
nuts

mix all together.

directions:

cook until tender. transfer to bowl of cold water and cool this.
drain.
add pasta to the same water and boil until tender, but still firm.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

nuts
directions:
put juice and rind (grated) of one orange in a cup; finish filling cup to 3/4 full with wesson oil.

chop 1 cup onions and 1 cup sweet pickles.

directions:

add eggs and beat well.
sift flour, baking powder and soda together.

this cookie can be frosted, if desired. quick and easy!
yum.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

water
salt

directions:

add sugar and vinegar.
mix with some water; add remaining water.
mix again slightly.
cook over low burner so it does not curdle.
if it should curdle, beat.
you can use 3 eggs or two eggs and then thicken with flour or cornstarch, 1 tablespoon to an egg.<|endofrecipe|>

allow cheese to soften to room temperature.
combine cheese, butter and paprika.
mix well into flour by hand until pieces of cheese disappear and mixture is smooth and deep yellow in color.

pinch off small pieces of dough (about 1 teaspoon) and flatten in palm of hand to a circle about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.

place on ungreased cookie sheet; chill 10 minutes in refrigerator.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

heat 1/4 cup butter and soup, sour cream, onion and cheese.

beat the eggs slightly and combine with the milk, then add to the dry ingredients.

add thyme and shallots to skillet; cook 2 minutes.
pour in broth and vinegar.

pour sauce over chicken.
serve with new potatoes.
makes 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
crackers
eggs
pecans
cream
directions:
combine vanilla, sugar, ritz crackers, eggs and 1 cup crushed nuts.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour

black coffee

mix all ingredients together thoroughly.

golden grahams
marshmallows
directions:
grease rectangle 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
heat syrup, margarine and morsels to boiling, stirring constantly.

directions:

let simmer over very low heat for at least 45 minutes to one hour.
makes a serving for at least 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn

directions:

cool slightly.
butter hands; shape mixture into 3 - inch balls and place on waxed paper.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

flour

ginger
salt

roll in sugar.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
you will also need bags (zipper lot).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
mix ingredients together.

berries

place all ingredients in a blender.

nuts
directions:
mix all ingredients together. bake at 300° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
mix well. drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

directions:

combine all ingredients.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
celery
garlic
tomatoes

tomatoes

salt
pepper

heat olive oil in a pan.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

worcestershire sauce
water

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

ingredients
in
a

a

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

and

add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.

well.

1/4

of

batter.

directions:
trim excess fat from meat; reserve trimmings.

place onions atop and around meat.
cover; bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours. remove bay leaves; discard.

pour over meat.

cover; continue baking 30 to 45 minutes more or until meat is tender. serve with hot cooked noodles.

directions:
this is a very sweet way to start your morning.<|endofrecipe|>

4

wow how good.<|endofrecipe|>

thickened,

fruits and nuts.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
slice, strip, chunk, halve or crinkle cut; whichever you want. pack quart jars fairly tight.

fill jar with cider vinegar to cover.
apply tops.
no need to sterilize.
just be new and clean.
that's the easy part!
now, put away for 5 to 6 months, even a year.
the curing process doesn't take that long actually.
they are ready when rusty green.
to make off:
turn jars upside down in sink (top removed) to drain.
drain 5 to 6 hours or longer.
invert jars; fill with sugar (right out of the bag) as much as jar will hold. apply tops and shake, shake, shake until sugar dissolves.
you will need to do this approximately 3 times until enough syrup to completely cover cucumbers.
when this is accomplished, add per quart, 1 teaspoon celery seed and 1 teaspoon whole allspice.
apply tops and shake, shake.
that's it.
let sit a few days.
simply delicious.<|endofrecipe|>

without sugar

water

worcestershire sauce

onions

pepper
amount of water

tomatoes
bread
directions:

first	7 ingredients and dash of pepper. shape into 8 oval

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

salt
pepper

vanilla

cottage cheese
bacon

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs

bananas

salt

flour

onion
broccoli
cottage cheese
cheddar cheese
butter

nuts
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mushrooms
eggs

directions:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

rice
margarine
cream of mushroom soup
water
onion soup
directions:

x
13-inch
pan or dutch oven pan. sprinkle rice in the
pan.
place
fryer
on top of rice.
mix soup, water and soup
mix.

cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
remove cover and allow chicken to brown.<|endofrecipe|>

directions:

directions:

nuts
directions:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

honey

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

red pepper
bread crumbs
tomato ketchup

pepper

onions

tomato ketchup
mustard
brown sugar
directions:
combine all ingredients and form into a loaf.

when done, top with:<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

vinegar
water
sugar
pepper

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

pepper

heat.

teaspoon

blend

directions:
break eggs into a large deep bowl and beat well.
add the sugar and beat.
add oil and beat until blended.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vegetable cooking spray
green pepper
peppers
water
ground red pepper
mustard
bite size cooked chicken breasts
bite size cooked chicken thigh

directions:

add onion, green pepper, jalapeno peppers and saute 5 minutes.
add chili powder, cumin and oregano; cook 2 minutes. add chicken, 1 cup water, red pepper, black pepper, worcestershire sauce, mustard, stewed tomatoes, chicken broth, and chili sauce and bring to a boil.

directions:
cream sugar and butter well. add eggs, one at a time. alternately add flour, sour cream and soda. add vanilla.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cheddar

directions:

spread about 3 tablespoons of mixture on top of each ham slice.

eggs

pecans
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
in a large bowl, mix together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat with a whisk until creamy smooth. in a separate bowl, combine flours, baking powder and salt.
add to egg mixture, beating just until well blended.
fold in apples and nuts.
fill greased muffin tins about 3/4 full.

turn out on wire rack and cool slightly before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
butter
pecans
powdered sugar
directions:
mix in 9 x 13 pan and press out crust.
bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.
let cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
eggs
oil
sugar
syrup
butter
pecans
directions:
combine yellow cake mix, 1 egg, and oil. press into 13 x 9-inch greased pan and bake at 300° for 20 minutes. while cake is cooking mix 4 eggs, sugar, karo syrup, butter, and chopped pecans. pour mixture over cooked cake and bake 45 minutes on 300°. since oven temperatures vary, during the last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking check closely. do not over cook. (better than pecan pie if you can believe it.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cucumbers
sugar
salt
turmeric
dill
garlic

directions:
put in bottom of quart jar the sugar, salt, mustard seed, turmeric, dill heads and garlic cloves.

do not process. shake them when cold to mix spices.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake
pineapple
bananas
cream cheese
milk
sugar
vanilla pudding

directions:
prepare yellow cake mix according to directions.
bake in sheet cake pan; cool.
mix cream cheese and sugar; add pudding mix, milk and remaining pineapple juice.
blend until creamy. slice bananas onto cooled cake.
spread cream cheese mixture over bananas.
place the pineapple onto mixture.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
combine squash, eggs, onion, seasonings and cracker crumbs; mix well.
drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
cook until golden brown, turning once.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs

add in milk and add to grits mixture. pour total mix into 2 1/2 casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
nuts

cornflakes

vanilla

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
rice
margarine
boiling water
cinnamon
turmeric
salt

directions:
stir rice and margarine into boiling water in a saucepan.
add cinnamon stick, turmeric, salt and bay leaf.

water

directions:
in mixing bowl, beat bananas and butter until creamy.
add eggs and beat well.
combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
add to banana mixture alternately with water, beating well after each addition.

spoon into a greased 9-inch square pan.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

cheddar cheese
green onions

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

garlic powder

directions:
preheat oven to 350°. crush crackers to fine crumbs.
in 2 qt bowl, mix together crumbs, parsley flakes, oregano, garlic powder, and red pepper, stir in butter.

sprinkle with paprika. bake 15 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
turkey
pineapple
carrot
celery

cheddar cheese
worcestershire sauce
salt
bread crumbs
butter
directions:
place sausages on a rack in a baking pan.
bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. cut into 1-inch pieces.
set aside.
in a skillet, saute peppers in oil for 3 minutes. place in 3-quart casserole.
add the sausages and the next 8 ingredients. combine bread crumbs and butter. sprinkle on top of casserole. bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
yields 6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
salt
egg

directions:
mix all ingredients together.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

brown sugar
salt

directions:
melt butter in heavy 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
add brown sugar, salt and corn syrup; mix well.
add condensed milk gradually, stirring constantly.
cook until mixture reaches 245° on candy thermometer, firm ball stage.
remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
let stand until cool.
cut into squares.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
all-purpose
shortening
sugar
salt
vinegar
water
directions:
mix together the first four ingredients with fork or pastry blender until thoroughly mixed.
in a small bowl, beat remaining ingredients.
combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all is moist.
with your hands, mold into balls.

dough can be kept in refrigerator for up to 3 days or wrapped tightly in saran wrap and frozen until ready to use.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
flour
baking powder
salt
vanilla
fruit
cream

directions:
beat eggs until light; add sugar and beat until thick.
add the vanilla.
sift flour with baking powder and salt and fold carefully into the egg mixture until well combined.
line a jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
butter it very well and sprinkle it generously with granulated sugar.
spread the batter evenly in the pan and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 20 minutes or until the cake is just set.
turn out onto a clean tea towel that has been well dusted with confectioners sugar and roll up while still hot. cool slightly, then unroll and remove from the towel.
when it has cooled, spread the inside of the roll with the jam and whipped cream.

may use fresh strawberries and cool whip inside, but make sure jelly roll is cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
gelatine
orange juice
sour cream

walnuts
bananas
strawberries
sugar

heat orange juice; add gelatine and sugar, then sour cream and triple sec.

add remaining ingredients.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onions
kidney red beans
beans
tomatoes
salt
directions:
cook ground beef and onions until done.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour

salt

directions:
add enough water to syrup to make 2 cups and then 2 more cups water.
put flour, crisco and salt in large bowl.
cut together until mixed good.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

put all in saucepan and cook until thick.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

salt

directions:
cream butter and sugar.
add eggs and beat until light.
add juices alternately with dry ingredients.

fold in strawberries with juice.
add drained pineapple, nuts and bananas, all at once.

water

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vodka

mix over ice in glass.<|endofrecipe|>

thyme

directions:
in a medium saucepan of boiling water, cook onion for 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.

gradually beat in a little at a time all of the sugar and a pinch of salt.

marshmallows
directions:
mix pineapple (not drained), cheese and marshmallows together. fold into cool whip.

cream-style corn

allspice
cinnamon sticks

directions:
simmer the cider, brown sugar, cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks.
strain and add the lemonade and orange juice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crisco
white sugar
brown sugar
eggs
salt
soda
water
vanilla
flour
chocolate chips

with pastry blender or fork, cut crisco, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
add salt, soda, water and vanilla.

milk
strawberries

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sausage

onions
green pepper
celery
garlic powder
salt
rice
water
directions:
mix all ingredients and cook in large rice cooker.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
onion
celery

parsley
salt
sage
poultry season
chicken bouillon
turkey steaks
all-purpose
butter
paprika
lemon slices
lime slices
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
in large skillet, melt butter.
add onion and celery and cook until tender.
add bread cubes, parsley, seasonings and bouillon (adjust seasonings to taste).

in pie pan, place flour; dip turkey rolls in flour and dip in melted butter.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apple juice
orange juice

cloves
allspice
nutmeg
sugar

slice potatoes and fry until brown on both sides.

add diced onion.
put bell pepper and diced onion in skillet with potatoes.
beat eggs and pour over the potatoes, bell pepper and onion until it forms into a pie.

peaches

directions:
drain juice from peaches.

put juice in saucepan and bring to a boil.
put juice in bowl and add jello; dissolve.

fold into mixture (after refrigerated).
pour into baked pie shell. refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
pecans
butter
cream cheese
powdered sugar
milk
directions:
mix and pour evenly on cool whip layer.<|endofrecipe|>

directions:

chop pecans and cherries and add to crumbs.
add raisins.
melt oleo and chopped marshmallows in top of double boiler and add to crumb mixture.
mix well.
pack into loaf pan and set in refrigerator for at least 6 hours before slicing.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oil
onions
worcestershire sauce
oregano
pepper
potatoes
carrots
browning sauce
venison stew meat
garlic
bay leaf
salt
water
flour

directions:
heat oil in a dutch oven.
brown meat.
add onions, garlic, worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, oregano, salt and pepper.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
butterscotch topping
regular
directions:
bake cake as directed.
while cake is hot, punch holes in cake (use wooden spoon handle).

chicken breasts
ham
