salt
directions:
wrap half of boned chicken breasts with slice of bacon. secure.
make a bed of smithfield ham
or chipped beef.
mix a can of cream of mushroom soup and
1
cup
sour
cream.
place chicken on ham.
pour sour	cream
mixture	over
chicken
and bake, uncovered, about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
zucchini
spaghetti
mozzarella cheese
directions:
slice zucchini into pickle type slices.
layer in microwave-safe baking dish.
top layers with prepared spaghetti sauce.
microwave zucchini and shift sauce until zucchini is tender, approximately 10 minutes.
sprinkle top with mozzarella cheese and microwave until melted.
serve hot!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
onion
rice
consomme
water
directions:
melt margarine and add chopped onion and rice.
stir constantly until brown.
put in covered casserole.
add consomme and bake 1 full hour at 375°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
turkey
butter
white wine
beef broth
parsley
garlic
lemons
cornstarch
thin
directions:
dip turkey slices in seasoned flour.
saute in butter and olive oil two minutes on each side.
remove.
add wine, beef broth, chopped parsley, garlic, grated lemon peel and juice.
let come to a boil and add cornstarch, dissolved in 1 tablespoon water.
add to thicken.
simmer gently.
add lemon slices and simmer two minutes.
return turkey and serve over noodles.
can use the lemon slices to decorate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of mushroom soup
peas
onion
worcestershire sauce
tuna
american cheese
directions:
if you enjoy turkey, but dislike wondering what to do with leftovers, this is the perfect solution.
a good bargain when turkey is cheap, also.
have butcher cut in half a 10 to 12 pound turkey (fresh or frozen).
wrap halves separately and freeze until needed.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
water
flour
pumpkin
marjoram
nutmeg
onion
chicken
milk
salt
thyme
pepper sauce
directions:
put bouillon cubes in water to dissolve.
in medium size saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender.
remove from heat. add flour; stir until dissolved.
add milk; cook until thick sauce is formed, stirring constantly.
add mashed pumpkin, water, chicken, salt, marjoram, thyme, nutmeg and pepper sauce.
heat soup to serving temperature.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shell macaroni
ground chuck
tomato paste
tomato sauce
cottage cheese
cheddar cheese
directions:
cook macaroni and drain.
prepare seasoning mix with ground chuck, tomato paste and sauce and 1 1/4 cups of water as package label directs.
preheat oven to 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn bread
hamburger
onion
tomatoes
salt
worcestershire sauce
chili powder
garlic salt
pinto
directions:
simmer hamburger, onion, tomatoes, salt, worcestershire sauce, chili powder and garlic salt about 15 minutes.
add cooked pinto beans or kidney beans.
place in baking dish; cover with 1 cup corn bread batter and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pecans
egg whites
salt
sugar
corn flakes
directions:
lay typewriter or smooth brown wrapping paper on baking sheet; don't grease.
start oven 10 minutes before baking; set to slow (300°).
chop nuts.
put whites into 2-quart mixing bowl; add salt and beat with rotary beater until stiff enough to hold soft rounded peaks.
add sugar in 4 portions, beating until shiny peaks that curve at tips form.
remove beater; use fork.
fold nuts in gently, then corn flakes until just distributed.
drop about heaping teaspoonfuls from fork 2 inches apart onto prepared sheet.
bake 25 to 30 minutes or until just golden brown and dry enough to hold shape.
remove at once from paper to cake rack to cool.
store no longer than a day.
makes 10 1/2 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
shortening
mushrooms
green pepper
tomatoes
onion
water
directions:
fry chicken in shortening for 1 hour on low heat.
use electric skillet.
do not coat chicken with flour.
mix mushrooms, green pepper, tomatoes, onion and water.
pour over chicken.
simmer 1/2 hour, basting often.
serve with potatoes or noodles and salad.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
fresh milk
eggs
sugar
salt
vanilla
sugar
directions:
melt 3/4 cup sugar in a pan until golden brown; let cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
eggs
shortening
vanilla
milk
salt
flour
baking powder
baking soda
directions:
put all in a bowl and beat with the electric mixer.
bake at 400° about 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
salt
butter
sugar
pumpkin pie spice
eggs
vanilla
bananas
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
in a medium bowl, cream the butter, sugar and pumpkin pie spice until fluffy.
beat in eggs one at a time; add vanilla.
add 1/3 of the flour mixture alternately with 1/3 cup of bananas; beat until smooth.
repeat with remaining flour and bananas.
pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
bake about 55 minutes or until cake tester inserted into center comes out clean.
makes one loaf.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
milk
salt
ham
cheddar cheese
onion
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
grease an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
beat eggs, milk and seasoned salt.
add ham.
stir in cheese and onion. pour into prepared dish.
bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until omelet is set and top is golden brown.
serves 4.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
sour cream
cream of chicken soup
chicken broth
crackers
butter
directions:
boil chicken and take off bones.
place in casserole dish.
mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
mix ritz crackers with 1 stick melted butter.
put on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
artichokes
spinach
chicken
cream of chicken soup
mayonnaise
lemon juice
curry
sharp cheese
bread crumbs
butter
directions:
cook chicken breasts in seasoned water (celery, salt and pepper).
remove from bone and skin.
pull from bone.
in buttered casserole (11 x 7 x 2-inch), layer artichokes, spinach (which has been thawed, drained and squeezed) and chicken pieces evenly distributed in bite size pieces.
combine soup, lemon juice and curry powder and spread on top.
sprinkle cheese over and top with bread crumbs.
dot with butter.
bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbles and heats thoroughly. serve with rice cooked with consomme or bouillon, fruit or tossed salad.
serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
shortening
eggs
flour
cocoa
salt
vanilla
nuts
marshmallows
directions:
cream sugar and shortening.
add eggs and beat by hand.
sift flour, cocoa and salt.
add to creamed mixture and mix well.
add vanilla and nuts.
pour into greased and floured pan.
bake for 35 minutes at 300°.
remove from oven and pour marshmallows over top. return to oven for 10 minutes at 350°.
cool cake for 1 hour, then add icing.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mushroom soup
cheese
eggs
crackers
milk
directions:
cut eggs and asparagus into pieces.
crumble 3 crackers in casserole.
add all ingredients in layers with crackers and cheese on top.
add milk and asparagus juice.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

apples
pecans
directions:
place sugar in a bowl.

pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it tests done.
serve warm and top with ice cream or cool whip.
yields 15 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
vanilla
sweet milk
margarine
directions:
beat together
eggs,
sugar and vanilla.
warm together milk and margarine.
mix
together; pour in 10-inch pie shell. bake at 375° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
butter
sugar
pecans
directions:
mix together ingredients for crust.
press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

stir well.
add eggs and beat with electric mixer for 2 1/2 minutes.
add salt, milk and vanilla.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour

directions:
mix together and drop by tablespoonfuls in boiling water or broth.

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

directions:

heat on low 1 hour.

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

oleo

sugar

nuts
cocoa
peanut butter
directions:
bring to boil in a large saucepan the oleo, milk, sugar and salt.

turn off and add oatmeal, vanilla, nuts, nestle quik and peanut butter.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

celery
onion
mayonnaise
worcestershire sauce
corned beef
directions:
dissolve jell-o and bouillon cube in boiling water.

to serve, cut into 1/4-inch slices.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cool, then add vanilla.
next crush graham crackers and add melted butter.

pat half of mixture into a square pan.

put a layer of this mixture over bananas, then a second layer of bananas and a second layer of cream mixture. sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.

tater

joes

water

brown meat and drain.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

macaroni
bread
parmesan cheese
water
directions:

add tomatoes, seasoning mix, water, macaroni and bouillon cube; stir to mix. simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
ladle into 6 serving bowls; top with toast and sprinkle with cheese.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion
egg

salt
margarine
cider vinegar
brown sugar
cloves
bay leaves
flour
directions:

add meat and next 4 ingredients and mix well.
shape into two loaves and brown on both sides in margarine in a skillet.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

bananas
eggs
flour
vanilla
salt
crisco oil
baking soda
baking powder
walnuts
directions:
heat oven to 350°.
use two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans or 1 large loaf pan. spray with pam.
bake 60 minutes.
cool for 10 minutes.
remove from pan.
place on rack to cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
okra

dill
alum
garlic
vinegar
water
salt
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

roll out and cut. bake at 350°.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

return to pan.
add cornstarch mixture and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

in the morning, drain and rinse in cold water.

fill jars.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

tortilla chips
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eye roast

directions:
rub the rib eye all over with pepper and place it in a shallow pan. preheat the oven to 500°. when the oven is hot, put the roast in the oven and close the door. do not open the door for 2 hours, then the roast is ready to serve. the roast should be cooked 5 minutes a pound at 500°, then the heat should be turned off. if the roast weighs 8 pounds, you cook the roast 40 minutes and turn the oven off. from the time you start the roast until it is ready to slice the time is 2 hours. pour part of the fat out of the pan and add some water and salt for a delicious natural gravy. the roast will be pink in the middle every time. you may want to cook your roast for 6 minutes per pound if you do not like it quite as pink.<|endofrecipe|>

o

1 twist.<|endofrecipe|>

(do not boil.)

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs

directions:
turn grill on and bring temp to medium high (approx. 20 minutes). meanwhile, mix stubbs pork marinade, molasses, soy sauce and ground pepper in a bowl or large cup. set aside. wash tuna steak with tepid tap water and place in flat bottom dish with sides (will be holding marinade, too). fresh tuna should not smell fishy. add marinade. cover and set aside for 15 minutes or so. turn tuna with tongs and let set for another 15 minutes. when grill is ready, place marinated tuna steaks on grill to sear side one. pour part of the marinade on tuna. cook on this side approximately 2 or 3 minutes with grill covered. turn tuna over using flat spatula by quickly shoving under tuna while pressing down on grilling surface. this will help keep tuna intact. reduce heat to low, pour on the rest of marinade and close lid. tuna will continue to sear on higher heat and cook while temp. goes down. turn once more after 4 or 5 minutes. check tuna often during this stage. remove from grill and let set for 5 minutes or so. slice in half and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

beat egg, vinegar and water in large bowl.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

remove.

egg

extra sharp cheese
salt

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

directions:

and

put 2 cans of soup and velveeta cheese in top of double boiler and melt. break macaroni into small pieces and cook as directed on box. grease baking dish.

(use 3-quart casserole dish.)
serves 14 to 16. can be frozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
noodles
onion
margarine
mushroom soup
pimento
chili pepper
chicken
salt
cheddar cheese
directions:

cook onion in margarine in skillet until soft, then stir in soup, pimento and chili pepper.

layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 the chicken and season with salt and pepper.
top with half the soup mixture and half the cheese.
repeat layers.
bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chocolate cake
coconut
nuts
oleo
cream cheese
powdered sugar
directions:
spread a 9 x 13-inch pan with pam.
mix nuts and coconut together.
spread in bottom of pan.
mix cake mix according to directions.
pour over coconut and nut mixture.
mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
spoon over batter and swirl around.
bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
turn upside-down onto a plate while hot.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
graham cracker crumbs
butter
cream cheese
milk
powdered sugar
pecans
cherry pie filling
directions:
mix graham cracker crumbs and butter. press into bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. beat together cream cheese, milk, powdered sugar, pecans and cool whip; mix well. spread on top of crust. refrigerate until it sets, then spread on cherry pie filling.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
bitter chocolate
salt
sugar
milk
vanilla
directions:
heat butter and chocolate over simmering water in double boiler until melted.
stir in salt, then the sugar in four or five portions, being sure to blend thoroughly.
the mix becomes very thick.
now stir in milk, very slowly.
then cook 5 to 6 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
remove from heat and stir in vanilla. store in refrigerator in a container with tight fitting lid.
to use hot, set jar in warm water for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crescent dinner rolls
lite cream cheese
vegetables
cheddar cheese
directions:
on cookie sheet, press out flat crescent rolls.
fill in holes and bake according to directions.
combine cream cheese, sour cream and dressing mix and spread on cooled bread.
mix up vegetables and press into mixture. top with cheese, cut into squares and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tortilla chips
black olives
beans
hamburger
onion
green onions
tomatoes
cheddar cheese
sour cream
directions:
brown ground beef and drain.
finely chop yellow onion (possibly 1/2 the onion) and add to ground beef.
dice black olives, green onion and tomatoes.
grate the cheese.
heat up refried beans on medium heat.
preheat oven to 350°.
in 9 x 13-inch pan, add tortilla chips on bottom, layering ingredients as follows:
beef, beans, green onion and cheese on top.
bake at 375° approximately 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
add remaining cold ingredients (black olives, tomatoes and sour cream).
serve hot.
feeds 4 to 6 people.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
salt
baking soda
baking powder
egg
fruit cocktail
brown sugar
cocktail juice
directions:

add egg, fruit cocktail and juice.
put in greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
pumpkin
vegetable oil
water
flour
sugar
baking soda
salt
nutmeg
cinnamon
yellow raisins
walnuts
directions:
beat together eggs, pumpkin, oil and water.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

tomato
macaroni

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
oil
milk
eggs
anise
directions:
do not use anise seed.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
water

sugar
cucumbers
onion
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornmeal
flour
onion
egg
sugar
milk
directions:
combine cornmeal, flour, onion and sugar.
add egg.
gradually beat in milk.
drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mushrooms

directions:
cut cheese up and add milk.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

vanilla
pecans
directions:

heat to boiling.

pie

onion
garlic

water

directions:

, washed

in a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
gradually add sugar.
while beating, slowly pour in oil; add vanilla.
combine dry ingredients; add alternately with the sour cream to the egg mixture.
gently fold in blueberries.
spoon into greased muffin tins.
bake at 400° for 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
elbow macaroni
onion
green pepper
tomato sauce
salt
chili powder
worcestershire sauce
directions:
cook beef until meat loses red color.
remove from skillet and cook macaroni, onion and green pepper until macaroni is yellow. return meat to skillet with tomato sauce, salt, pepper, chili powder and worcestershire sauce.
cover with water.
cover pan and simmer 25 minutes until macaroni is tender.
add water, if necessary.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
spinach
eggs
sour cream
milk
parmesan cheese
onion
salt
pepper
cheese
spaghetti
parmesan
directions:
cook spinach; drain.
combine eggs, sour cream, milk, 4 tablespoons parmesan cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
add cheese and mix.
add spinach and cooked spaghetti.
put into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
bake, covered, at 350° for 15 minutes, then continue baking, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
sprinkle with remaining parmesan cheese before baking.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red kidney beans
salt pork
onion
garlic
celery
ham
tabasco sauce
salt
bay leaf
thyme
rice
directions:
soak beans in water overnight.
drain.
in a dutch oven, brown salt pork.
add onions, garlic and celery and saute for 3 minutes. add beans, stock, tabasco sauce, salt and herbs.
simmer 3 hours or until beans are tender.
add water when necessary during cooking; water should barely cover beans at end of cooking. remove 1 cup beans and mash to paste.
add mashed bean paste back to beans; stir until liquid is thickened.
serve over hot rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cold milk
chocolate sandwich cookies
directions:
pour milk into large bowl; add jell-o mix.
beat until well blended.
let sit for 5 minutes.
stir in cool whip and 1/2 of crushed cookies.
place 1 tablespoon cookies into the cups.
fill cups with pudding mixture.
top with remaining cookies. refrigerate 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
egg yolks
baking powder
milk
margarine
egg whites
vanilla
salt
directions:
sift flour once.
measure.
add baking powder, sugar and salt. combine milk and egg yolks and add to flour gradually, beating to a smooth batter.
add shortening.
fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla.
pour this in hot buttered frying pan.
brown on both sides.
alternate six of these pancakes with rum sauce.
cut this stack in four portions and top with lots of rum sauce and when ready to serve, bake in hot oven for 3 minutes.
serve one stack to person with whipped cream on side.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
powdered sugar
chocolate chips
butter
brown sugar
pecans
directions:
mix all ingredients except for the chocolate chips and pecans until smooth. when smooth, add chocolate chips. shape into a ball and roll in pecans. serve with chocolate or honey graham crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange
brown sugar
orange rind
raisins
nut meats
baking powder
sugar
baking soda
shortening
eggs
flour
milk
directions:
mix together brown sugar and orange juice, set aside.
chop orange rind, raisins and nuts in chopper or processor.
set aside.
cream together sugar, baking soda and shortening.
add eggs to creamed mixture, one at a time; mix well.
sift flour and baking powder; add alternately to creamed mixture with 1 cup milk. add raisin-nut mixture.
bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
remove from pan immediately and pour juice/brown sugar mix slowly over top.
cool before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef bouillon
onions
butter
salt
sugar
flour
parmesan cheese
directions:
pour bouillon or stock in crock-pot.
cook onions slowly in large skillet in butter.
cover and let cook about 15 minutes. uncover and add salt, sugar and flour.
stir well.
add to stock in crock-pot.
cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (high 3 hours). before serving, top with grated cheese.
recipe may be doubled for 5-quart pot.
if you have ovensafe bowls, place finished soup in individual bowls.
place slice of italian bread and slice of mozzarella cheese on top and place bowl under broiler until cheese melts.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vinegar
bottles
barbecue sauce
red ground pepper
pepper
black pepper
salt
directions:
combine all ingredients and bring to a good boil.
can also be used for chicken.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cheddar cheese
olives
miracle
onion
curry powder
halves
directions:
mix all together and spread on muffins. place on a cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
oil
eggs
salt
baking soda
vanilla
baking soda
cinnamon
flour
full size zucchini
directions:
grate the zucchini (skin and seed also); let stand.
mix sugar, oil, eggs, baking soda, vanilla, baking powder, cinnamon and flour.
mix well.
add zucchini and nuts (optional).
bake in 2 greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
sugar
potato chips
nuts
flour
vanilla
directions:
cream margarine and sugar, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
drop by tsp. on greased sheet.
bake 15 min. at 350°. roll in powdered sugar or cinnamon if desired when cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
sugar
egg
sorghum molasses
flour
soda
ginger
cinnamon
cloves
salt
sugar
directions:
mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses together.
sift and add to mixture the flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and salt. mix well.
shape into 1-inch balls.
roll in sugar.
bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
makes approximately 5 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn
mayonnaise
butter
cheese
red pepper
salt
directions:
boil and drain corn.
add mayonnaise, cheese, and butter. stir and add salt & crushed red pepper to taste.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
mayonnaise
canisters crescent rolls
carrots
broccoli florets
red onion
yellow crookneck
directions:
all veggies are raw and can substitute red or green peppers or any colored veggie.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk powder
egg
pineapple juice
cinnamon
salt
nuts
butter
pineapple
flour
baking powder
dates
directions:
cream milk powder and butter; add egg, pineapple juice and flavoring.
mix well.
combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, salt, dates and nuts.
stir into creamed butter mixture and mix well.
bake in an 8-inch square pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. top with pineapple topping.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of mushroom soup
mozzarella cheese
pepper
mushrooms
onion
tomato wedges
eggs
basil
margarine
fresh parsley
fresh basil
directions:
in medium bowl with wire whisk, beat soup until smooth. gradually blend in eggs, 1 cup of cheese, basil and pepper.
in 10-inch oven-safe omelet pan or skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook mushrooms and onion until mushrooms are tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring occasionally.
pour mixture into skillet.
reduce heat to low.
cook 6 minutes or until edges are set 1-inch from edge.
do not stir.
remove from heat and serve. for garnish, use tomato wedges, chopped fresh parsley or fresh basil leaves.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

oleo
milk
onion
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hamburger
rice
salt
onion
pepper
tomato soup
water
directions:
combine first five ingredients.
shape into balls. put into skillet.
combine soup and water; pour over meatballs.
cook until done, about 45 minutes.
may add more water if necessary.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
olive or
cider vinegar
garlic powder
ground cumin
salt
pepper
kidney beans
mexicorn
black beans
red onion
directions:
in a bowl, combine the first six ingredients; mix well.
add the beans, corn and onion; stir to coat.

yield: 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cucumbers
salt
onion
sugar
turmeric
alum
vinegar
celery
directions:
put salt over cucumbers and onion.
let set for 3 hours. drain off.
mix all ingredients together.
put pickles in large jar and pour mixture over pickles.
put in refrigerator.
use as needed.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mayonnaise
sugar
bacon
cheddar cheese
directions:
layer ingredients in order given in a shallow serving dish. vary amounts and size of dish to suit your needs.
sliced black olives can be added.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mustard

celery
pepper
directions:

heat until mixture thickens.

cook 30 minutes and put in jars and seal.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs
margarine
milk
pineapple
directions:
mix all ingredients thoroughly.
put in 3 quart baking dish (oblong shape is best).

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
stir flour and sugar together until smooth. add milk, egg yolks and flavoring. heat but do not let any egg yolks cook. layer vanilla wafers and bananas in a long dish starting and ending with vanilla wafers. pour hot mixture over bananas and wafers. prepare meringue for topping.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mayonnaise
whipping cream
green onions
fresh parsley
anchovy
t
lemon juice
directions:

cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sausage
cheddar cheese
bisquick
milk
directions:
mix well.
roll into balls (small).
bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen strawberries
confectioners sugar
lemon zest
heavy cream
directions:
blend berries, sugar and lemon until almost smooth.
with blender running, pour in heavy cream.
puree about one minute. serve immediately.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion

carrots

directions:
melt butter in skillet; brown onion.
add soup, cheese and carrots.
mix well.
pour mixture in greased casserole pan.
top with bread crumbs, optional.
bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
orange juice
orange rind
directions:
cook over hot water in double boiler until thick. cool. fold in 1 cup whipping cream which has been whipped. serve over slices of angel food cake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
butterscotch instant pudding
eggs
oil
water
brown sugar
nuts
cinnamon
directions:
preheat oven to 325°. in mixing bowl with electric mixer, blend cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and water. spread 1/2 of the mixture in a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn

taco seasoning mix
tortilla chips
directions:
put popped corn in a large bowl.
add melted margarine. sprinkle with taco seasoning.
toss until combined.
add tortilla chips.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
cheddar cheese
bell pepper
onion
pimento
black pepper
red pepper
salt
worcestershire sauce
directions:
mix all ingredients together into a firm ball and roll on pecans.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

chicken
cream of chicken soup
green pepper
american cheese
eggs
milk
directions:
combine ingredients; refrigerate overnight.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar

eggs

salt

raisins
nuts
directions:
mix together.
bake at 350° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

take out and stir in pineapple, marshmallows, oranges and coconut.
pour into mold.
(i use a bundt pan sprayed with pam.)

when ready to serve invert onto plate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

put in ziploc bag and refrigerate. saute butter, noodles, sunflower seeds, almonds and sesame seed. pour on paper towels and cool.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

salt

directions:

grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
sift dry ingredients together.
add shortening, half of buttermilk and 1 egg.
beat 2 minutes.

pour all batter at once time into pan.

muffin tins, bake 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
soda crackers

nuts
directions:

boil butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
pour over crackers.
bake in oven (400°) for 3 minutes until bubbly.
remove and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
smooth over with knife after melted.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
mash shrimp.
combine with softened cream cheese and onion. place on serving dish forming smooth mound.
mix ketchup and horseradish to taste.
cover shrimp and cream cheese mixture. when ready to serve, pour ketchup and horseradish over mound. serve with crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter
flour
chicken broth
mustard
directions:

remove chicken to a warm platter.
blend flour into pan drippings; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
gradually stir in broth and half and half; cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.

add chicken; cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
yield:
2 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cereal
powdered sugar
directions:

pour over the chex cereal; toss.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

pork

carrots

stalks celery

directions:

brown meat alone.

add rice, then bean sprouts.
simmer 30 minutes.
(optional:
add 6 to 8 tablespoons sweet and sour sauce.)
serve with pineapple jell-o mold or fruit salad.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shrimp
lemon pepper
bacon
lemon juice
directions:
note:
will also need 6 to 7 skewers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
all-purpose
sugar

salt
eggs
carrots

pineapple
pecans
vanilla extract
confectioners sugar
milk
directions:
in a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
in another bowl, beat eggs.
add carrots, oil, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until loaves test done.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cauliflower
bell pepper
olives
radishes
tomatoes
american cheese
marinade
directions:
combine chopped cauliflower, bell pepper, olives, radishes and tomatoes.
stir in cheese.
marinate overnight in dressing.
salad reaches its full flavor 1 to 3 days after preparation.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
egg
milk
walnuts
biscuit mix
directions:
mix together sugar, egg, milk and walnuts.
add biscuit mix. beat hard for 30 seconds.
spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

cool thoroughly before cutting.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
cream of tartar
baking soda
salt

margarine
vanilla
eggs
egg yolk
chocolate
powdered sugar
milk
nuts
directions:

add eggs and chocolate; beat 1 minute.
turn into a 9-inch tube pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour 10 minutes.
just before serving, spoon powdered sugar into top of cake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sharp cheese
flour
cayenne pepper
salt
directions:
mix all ingredients together.
pinch into balls and roll into straws.
bake at 375° to 400°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oil

anchovy
onion
tuna
parsley sprigs
directions:
blend 1/4 cup oil, egg yolk, and 2 tbsp. lemon juice.

beat into egg mixture.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
bacon
ground beef
garlic powder
parsley
salt
pepper
tomato juice
celery
carrot
directions:
fry onion and bacon until tender.
add beef; fry until done. drain off grease.
add the rest of the ingredients, except spaghetti, and simmer for 30 to 60 minutes.
cook spaghetti and serve meat sauce over spaghetti.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sweet italian sausage
ground beef
onion
grated mozzarella
cheese
tomato paste
oregano
basil
thyme
salt
olive oil
lasagna noodles
directions:
brown onions.
add sausage and brown.
add ground beef and brown.
add seasonings and tomato paste.
(adjust seasonings to individual taste).
mix well and simmer while preparing noodles. cook noodles in salt water with a little olive oil in it.
after noodles are cooked, cool in water with a little olive oil.
line a cake pan with foil and grease it with olive oil.
layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and mozzarella.
repeat, ending with sauce and cheese (not noodles).
bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen broccoli
chicken breasts
milk
grated cheese
cream of chicken soup
mayonnaise
garlic
directions:
mix the soup, mayonnaise, milk and garlic powder.
pour over the chicken and broccoli that is mixed together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

bake at 350° for 25 minutes. can be heated in the microwave.
(you may want to double the sauce.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
condensed milk
chocolate pudding
cold water
whipped whipping cream
directions:
in large mixer bowl, combine eagle brand condensed milk, pudding mix and water; beat until well blended.
chill 5 minutes. fold in whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs
tomato

butter
parmesan cheese
directions:

pour into plate.
top with tomatoes; sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

green onions

chicken breasts
eggs
milk

grated cheese
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter
eggs
vanilla
salt
cream cheese
sugar
flour
baking powder
almond extract
nuts
directions:
melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter; cool and set aside. cream remaining butter with cream cheese; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
blend in 1 egg and 1 tablespoon flour.
add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; set aside.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
meal
water
eggs
oil
salt
pepper
nutmeg
directions:

refrigerate one hour.
form into balls and drop into soup or 1 1/2 quarts of boiling water to which salt has been added.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

hot sauce

fettucine

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork
red kidney beans
onion
mustard
vinegar
brown sugar
catsup
ground beef
directions:
brown onion and meat.
drain.
add remaining ingredients and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
tomato sauce
parsley flakes
oregano
cottage cheese

egg
parsley flakes
basil
noodles
mozzarella cheese
parmesan cheese
directions:
crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
cover loosely and microwave for 3 minutes on high.
break up and stir.
cover and microwave until very little pink remains, 2 to 3 minutes longer; drain.
stir in spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, 1 tablespoon parsley and oregano.
cover tightly and microwave on high to boiling, 3 to 4 minutes.
spread 1 1/3 cups meat sauce in baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches).
overlap 4 lasagne noodles on sauce.
add 1 cup cheese filling and 1 cup mozzarella cheese (reserve 1 cup mozzarella for top after cooking).
repeat layers with 1 1/3 cups meat sauce, remaining noodles and cheese filling.
top with remaining meat sauce.
cover tightly and microwave on high for 10 minutes.
rotate dish 1/2 turn.
microwave on medium until noodles are tender, 22 to 28 minutes longer.
sprinkle with remaining cheese and parmesan cheese.
let stand 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
cream of chicken soup
mushroom soup
onion
velveeta cheese
directions:
cook broccoli and drain well.
spray a casserole dish with pam to prevent sticking.
place broccoli in dish.
chop the onion evenly over broccoli.
blend soups and place on broccoli.
cover with cheese.
place in oven at 375° until all blends well (will get bubbly).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beans
sour cream
taco
shredded lettuce
tomatoes
salsa
cheddar cheese
nacho chips
directions:
layer in pan:
refried beans, taco mix and sour cream (mixed together), lettuce, tomatoes, salsa and cheese.
serve with nacho chips.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mushrooms
onion
green pepper
garlic
olive oil
kidney beans
olives
pepper
flour tortillas
nonfat sour cream
chunky salsa
cheddar cheese
directions:
cook mushrooms, onion, green pepper and garlic in olive oil in a large, nonstick skillet over medium high heat, stirring constantly until tender.
remove from heat; drain.
combine cooked vegetables, drained kidney beans, olives and pepper.
spoon about 1/2 cup bean mixture evenly down center of each tortilla. top with 1 tablespoon sour cream, 1 tablespoon salsa and 1 tablespoon cheese; fold opposite sides over filling.
coat a large nonstick skillet or griddle with cooking spray.
heat over medium-high heat until hot.
cook tortilla, seam side down, 1 minute on each side or until thoroughly heated.
top each tortilla with 1 tablespoon salsa.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oil
brown sugar
eggs
cooking oats
baking powder
salt
milk
vanilla extract
cinnamon
walnuts
directions:
mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 9-inch pan. bake at 350° for 30 minutes. makes 6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bunches broccoli
bacon
miracle
vinegar
cheddar cheese
onion
vinegar
dill
directions:
mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
can be made a couple of days ahead to marinate well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef tamales
hominy
chili
onion
bell pepper
cheddar cheese
directions:
cut up tamales in squares and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
drain hominy and add to tamales.
add onion and bell pepper to dish.
pour chili over all and top with cheese. bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
serves 4.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
coconut
butter
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
combine coconut and melted butter in large bowl.
press mixture on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate. bake in oven about 20 minutes or until golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking soda
salt
cinnamon
sugar
frozen strawberries
eggs
vegetable oil
pecans
directions:
mix dry ingredients together.
add remaining ingredients. stir carefully.
turn batter into loaf pans.
bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
cool in pans 10 minutes, then put on cooling racks.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
sugar
eggs
vanilla
flour
soda
baking powder
milk
nuts
directions:
cream or mix well the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
mix well.
drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
makes 6 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cauliflower
head lettuce
bacon
garbanzo beans
onion
mayonnaise
sugar
parmesan cheese
directions:
layer in dish with lid (tupperware kind):
lettuce, cauliflower, garbanzo beans, bacon, onion and mayonnaise spread over top.
sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise and then sprinkle parmesan cheese over all.
cover.
refrigerate overnight.
toss right before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
vanilla
pineapple
flour
soda
salt
directions:
to make cake, beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
add vanilla and pineapple with juice.
add flour sifted with soda and salt. pour into large greased and floured pan.
bake 45 minutes at 350°. batter should not be more than 1 inch thick.
ten minutes before the cake is done, begin icing.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red beans
onions
garlic
sausage
rice
directions:
soak beans several hours and drain. put in large pot leaving room for plenty of water. chop onion and garlic; add to beans. slice sausage thin and add to beans the last 45 minutes of cooking. cook rice by package directions.
serve beans over rice. this recipe will fill a 48-quart cooler.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread
milk
sugar
eggs
raisins
nutmeg
directions:
beat the eggs and add sugar, milk and nutmeg.
butter a baking dish.
arrange the bread in dish and pour liquid over it.
let stand until bread has been thoroughly soaked.
add raisins.
bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crescent rolls
cheese
apricot
directions:
press crescent roll dough together, making it like a pie crust.
assemble this in a pie plate. spread bottom with apricot jam, thinly.
place brie cheese in the middle and pull crust around and on top to cover.
bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
serve with plain crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
warm water
yeast
sugar
instant vanilla pudding
margarine
eggs
salt
flour
directions:
combine water, yeast and sugar; stir until dissolved.
set aside.
mix instant pudding according to package directions.
mix margarine, eggs and salt and add to pudding, then add to yeast mixture.
add flour and knead until smooth.
place in a greased bowl.
cover and let rise until double.
punch down; let rise again.
roll out and spread with 2 tablespoons melted margarine. sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
roll up and cut in about 1-inch slices.
place in greased pans and let rise until double again.
bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes
onions
green peppers
red hot pepper
stalks celery
garlic salt
bay leaves
olive oil
sugar
salt
oregano
tomato paste
directions:
flavor is enhanced when vegetables are chopped in food processor.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
milk
pineapple
instant vanilla pudding
cream cheese
directions:
prepare cake as directed on package.
pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
do not use 9 x 13-inch pan.
bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
when cake is cool, blend in bowl milk, pudding and cream cheese until thick.
pour over cake and let set. spread pineapple over pudding mixture.
top with cool whip. garnish with cherries, nuts and coconut if desired.
keep refrigerated.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
marshmallows
butter
peanuts
semi-sweet chocolate chips
crisp rice cereal
directions:
in a saucepan over low heat, cook and stir marshmallows, chips and butter until marshmallows are melted
and mixture is smooth. remove from heat and stir in peanuts and cereal; mix well. drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto wax paper; cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
oil
green bell pepper
red bell pepper
chicken
pineapple ice cream topping
sugar
ground ginger
vinegar
soy sauce
cornstarch
rice
cashews
directions:
saute the peppers in the butter and oil until tender but not mushy. remove from pan and set aside.
add the chicken to the skillet.
if needed, add a little more butter and oil. cook until the chicken is lightly browned and tender.
add peppers back to skillet along with the ice cream topping, sugar, ginger, and vinegar.
stir to mix well.
combine the soy sauce and cornstarch in a small bowl and stir until blended.
add to skillet, mixing well.
serve over rice and sprinkle the toasted cashews over the top. makes 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
butter
sweet milk
baking powder
eggs
coconut
cinnamon
cloves
raisins
directions:
add together first 6 ingredients.
take half of recipe and put coconut, cinnamon, cloves and raisins in.
bake other half plain.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
milk
nutmeg
apples
bread crumbs
salt
directions:
peel, core and chop the apples finely; add the bread crumbs, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
beat the eggs well and use them with the milk to moisten the pudding.
turn into greased mold; cover closely and steam 2 hours.
serve with a hot sweet sauce.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
spaghetti
italian dressing
cucumbers
bell peppers
onions
tomatoes
directions:
prepare spaghetti as directed on the box.
drain and cool. add vegetables, italian dressing and seasoning mix to taste.
toss and refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
dressing
chicken broth
onion
cream of celery soup
cream of chicken soup
sage
directions:
take a stick of oleo and melt in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
use 1/2 of dressing and spread evenly over oleo.
sprinkle chicken over dressing.
combine both soups and chicken broth.
mix well.
add chopped onion and sage to mixture and pour over chicken.
take other half of dressing and sprinkle over top. bake 35 or 40 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen broccoli
onion
cream of mushroom soup
mayonnaise
grated cheese
cracker crumbs
directions:
mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
top with some of the cheese and ritz crackers.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh cranberries
sugar
pineapple
pineapple juice
mandarin oranges
pineapple
banana
sour cream
coconut
directions:
combine cranberries and
sugar.
mix to dissolve sugar. heat pineapple juice.
add
jell-o
and	stir until dissolved. add to cranberries; stir well.
stir in fruits, sour cream and cool whip. chill until firm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
all-purpose
salt
crisco
very cold milk
directions:
adjust oven rack to lowest position.
preheat oven to 350°. in food processor with steel blade, combine flour, salt and crisco; pulse about 6 seconds, until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
add milk and process until dough forms a ball.
continue processing 2 minutes.
on floured surface, roll dough into rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
fold dough in half, pressing lightly. with a 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter, cut out dough and place on cookie sheet.
re-roll scraps and repeat, cutting more biscuits. prick each biscuit with a fork.
bake 30 to 35 minutes, until pale golden.
turn off oven, leave biscuits in oven for 35 minutes. makes about 2 1/2 dozen.
contains 100 calories each.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mayonnaise
nonfat yogurt
water chestnuts
onion
parmesan cheese
ground pepper
country bread
directions:
drain spinach in a fine sieve, pressing to squeeze out as much water as possible.
transfer drained spinach to a medium bowl. add remaining ingredients except bread.
slice about 2 inches off top of bread.
hollow out loaf, leaving a 1-inch wall to create a bowl.
to serve, spoon dip into bread bowl.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
roll chocolate chip
miniature reese's
directions:
cut a small amount of cookie dough and put in a small, greased tart pan or pans sprayed with pam.
(this would be 1/2 slice approximately.)
cook at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
the cookie dough will only be partially baked.
after taking off paper around reese's cups, place one on top of partially baked cookie dough. push down slightly. bake 2 more minutes. cool slightly before removing.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
sugar
crisco
salt
eggs
flour
yeast
directions:
scald milk and pour over sugar, crisco and salt.
beat eggs and add to mixture.
measure 2 1/2 cups of flour into another bowl (gallon crock) and add yeast.
pour lukewarm mixture and mix.
add rest of flour gradually.
takes about 4 pounds.
knead about 10 minutes.
grease bowl.
cover and let rise.
punch down and let rise again.
punch down and shape into loaves, rolls or cinnamon rolls.
bake at 325° until lightly browned.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beet jelly
sugar
raspberry
lemon juice
directions:
bring jelly and sure-jell to a hard boil.
add sugar, jell-o and lemon juice.
boil 8 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
margarine
carnation
semi-sweet chocolate pieces
marshmallow creme
nuts
vanilla
directions:
combine the sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly. continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
add marshmallow creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
cool at room temperature.
cut into squares.
makes approximately 3 pounds.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pie crust
cream cheese
amount milk
fresh strawberries
crushed strawberries
cornstarch
sugar
whipped cream
directions:
bake the pie crust.
moisten the cream cheese with a small amount of milk or cream; spread on pie crust.
arrange 1 pint small strawberries on the cheese.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onion
tomatoes
worcestershire sauce
salt
potatoes
flour
corn
beans
bell pepper
cheddar cheese
directions:
in a bowl combine browned and drained beef, onion and tomatoes with liquid, worcestershire sauce and salt. spoon into a greased 3 quart casserole. layer the potatoes, flour, corn, lima beans and green peppers on top. cover and bake at 375
for 45 minutes. sprinkle with cheese and continue baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lemons
sugar
condensed milk
whipping cream
cake
directions:
combine juice, sugar and milk. add whipped cream.
tear cake into small pieces and line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
pour mixture over the cake and mix together a little. chill for 24 hours before serving.
serves 8 to 10.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
water
raisins
applesauce
eggs
corn oil
baking soda
flour
cinnamon
vanilla
salt
sugar
directions:
cook raisins in water until soft; drain off water.
mix applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil very well.
add baking soda and flour.
add remaining ingredients and stir in the raisins.
bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. makes 1 large cake or 2 dozen cupcakes.
one cupcake equals 1 fruit and 1 fat.
sprinkle with chopped walnuts or "no sugar" coconut before baking if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chickpeas
kidney beans
pasta shells
tomatoes
olive oil
garlic
onion
carrots
zucchini
vegetable stock
green beans
green pepper
salt
black pepper
oregano
tarragon
ground rosemary
basil
tomato puree
red wine
directions:
saute garlic and onion in olive oil until translucent.
add salt, pepper, basil, oregano, tarragon, rosemary, carrots and wine.

add green pepper, stock, puree and beans.
cover and simmer 30 minutes.
add chopped tomatoes, cooked pasta and zucchini and simmer for another 15 minutes.
makes 6 quarts.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground cooked ham
bread crumbs
egg
chili sauce
ground carrots
milk
green pepper
directions:
combine all ingredients
and
mix
well.
shape
into a loaf and place in loaf pan, greased.
bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
onion
water
flour
sugar
vinegar
salt
bacon
directions:
peel potatoes and slice.
simmer onion in bacon drippings and add flour, vinegar, sugar, water and seasoning.
mix well all ingredients together and serve warm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange juice
maple
orange marmalade
carrots
directions:
combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
add carrots.
return to a boil. reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes.
serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bananas
egg
sugar
vegetable oil
milk
flour
poppy seed
salt
baking soda
baking powder
directions:
preheat oven to 400°.
fill 12 cupcakes tins with paper liners. mash bananas with a fork.
in large bowl, mix egg, sugar and vegetable oil.
add and mix milk and mashed bananas.
in a small bowl, stir flour, poppy seed, salt, baking soda and baking powder. add flour mixture all at one time to the liquid mixture.
using a wooden spoon, stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
using a metal or plastic measuring cup.
pour batter into cupcake liners until they are half full.
bake 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cold milk
instant chocolate pudding
chocolate sandwich cookies
gummy worms
directions:
pour 2 cups cold milk into bowl.
add pudding mix.
beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 2 minutes.
let pudding stand 5 minutes.
stir whipped topping and 1/2 the crushed cookies into pudding with the rubber scraper until mixture is all the same color.
place about 1 tablespoon of the remaining crushed cookies into bottom of each paper or plastic cup.
add gummy worms to pudding mixture.
fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture. top each cup with the rest of the crushed cookies.
chill about an hour.
decorate the tops with plastic flowers!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
eggs
sugar
salt
rice
raisins
vanilla
nutmeg
directions:
scald milk in top of double boiler.
combine beaten eggs, sugar and salt in 1 1/2 casserole dishes.
gradually stir in scalded milk.
add cooked rice, raisins and vanilla.
sprinkle with nutmeg and place in oven.
bake at 325° for 50 minutes, or until set.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breast
walnuts
craisins
salad dressing
honey
nutmeg
ground ginger
directions:
combine chicken, craisins, walnuts in one bowl.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chuck roast
oil
green pepper
onions
tomatoes
tomato paste
worcestershire sauce
bay leaves
basil
pepper
directions:
brown meat on each side in a pot with oil.
remove meat; saute peppers and onions in pot.
return meat to pot.
add remaining ingredients.
simmer at least 3 hours, all day, if possible. serve over noodles.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
noodles
corned beef
cream of celery soup
water
dressing
sauerkraut
swiss cheese
directions:
place in a greased lasagna pan.
put noodles on bottom, then sauerkraut, followed by soup mixed with milk, then russian dressing, then meat.
top with cheese.
bake at 350° until cheese melts.
serves 10.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
cream cheese
flour
directions:
mix together margarine and cream cheese; add flour.
chill 2 hours, then press into miniature cupcake pan and fill with filling.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onion
green chilies
salt
tsp.pepper
taco seasoning
hominy
tomatoes
kidney beans
pinto beans
water
directions:
brown ground beef with onion and green chilies.
stir in remaining ingredients, bring to a boil.
simmer 30 minutes on low. yields 10 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking soda
salt
ground cinnamon
butter
sugar
brown sugar
eggs
vanilla
oats
butterscotch chips
directions:
combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in small bowl. beat butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy. gradually add in flour mixture. stir in oats and morsels. drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. bake in preheated 375° oven 7 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9 to 10 minutes or crispy cookies. let stand 2 minutes. remove to wire rack to cool completely. makes about 4 dozen cookies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomato puree
boiling water
salt
brown sugar
fresh white bread crumbs
butter
directions:
put tomato puree in a pan and rinse the tin with the cup boiling water. add to puree. heat to boiling and add the salt and brown sugar. place the white bread crumbs in a greased baking pan. pour the melted butter over the bread crumbs and then add the tomato mixture. cover dish tight and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
flour
fruit
sugar
milk
directions:
melt margarine in pan.
blend flour, sugar and milk together. pour over margarine.
add fruit.
do not stir! bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
optional: remove from oven and sprinkle sugar over crust.
return to oven for 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
biscuit mix
sesame seed
water
margarine
margarine
biscuit mix
onion
salt
chicken broth
milk
chicken
mixed vegetables
directions:
combine the 1 1/2 cups biscuit mix, sesame seed, water and the 3 tablespoons margarine.
pat into an 8-inch square or a 9-inch round pan; set aside.
melt the 1/3 cup margarine; stir in the 1/2 cup biscuit mix, onion and seasonings.
cook over low heat until bubbly; remove from heat.
stir in chicken broth and milk.
heat to boiling and boil 1 minute.
stir in chicken and mixed vegetables.
turn into ungreased 8-inch square baking dish or 9-inch pie plate.
place dough over top.
cut several slits in top and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 425° or until golden.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
boiling water
jell-o
philadelphia cream cheese
walnuts
directions:
drain pineapple, reserving juice.
add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
stir in measured liquid.
pour 2 cups of the gelatin into medium bowl.
refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened (spoon drawn through leaves a definite impression).
stir in pineapple.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
boiling water
blueberries
sugar
cream cheese
raspberry jello
sour cream
pecans
directions:
drain pineapple.
keep juice.
dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in pineapple juice.
chill.
stir in pineapple and blueberries.
pour in 10 x 6-inch pan.
chill.
combine sour cream, cream cheese and sugar.
mix until smooth and well blended. spread over salad.
top with pecans.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
olive oil
garlic
shrimp
parsley
white vinegar
butter
white wine
spaghetti
salt
directions:
heat oil and vinegar in skillet.
add garlic until heated. add vinegar, wine, salt and pepper to taste.
then add shrimp. cook shrimp 5 to 7 minutes (don't overcook).
boil water.
cook spaghetti until done.
drain.
serve shrimp and sauce over pasta.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
boneless roast
cooking oil
onions
garlic salt
mushrooms
cream of mushroom soup
sherry
directions:
brown meat in oil.
slice the onions in rings and cook with the meat.
combine soup, sherry, garlic salt and liquid from mushrooms.
pour over beef and onions.
pour in mushrooms.
let boil and then simmer for at least one hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
wine vinegar
sugar
parsley
pepper
cucumbers
onions
directions:
in a large bowl, combine 1/4 cup of water with all ingredients. peel cucumbers and cut very thin slices.
add to bowl and toss very well.
refrigerate, covered, for at least 3 hours before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fryer
cream of chicken soup
milk
chicken broth
onion
dressing
directions:
boil chicken in very lightly salted water until tender.
make sure enough water is included to yield 3 cups of broth.
remove chicken from bones and cut in pieces.
cook onion in chicken broth until tender.
mix milk and soup well.
place cut-up chicken in casserole dish which has been lightly greased with butter.
pour milk and soup mixture over chicken.
add onion.
place dressing on top of this and pour melted butter over all.
bake in moderate oven, 350°, until dressing is brown and casserole is bubbly.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
cereal
water
layer
eggs
orange juice
vegetable oil
directions:
heat oven to 350°. microwave butter in small microwavable bowl on high for 30 seconds or until melted. stir in cereal and sugar; set aside. beat cake mix, eggs, orange peel, orange juice and oil in a large bowl with electric mixer on low speed just to moisten. beat on medium speed 4 minutes. pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. bake 20 minutes or until beginning to rise. sprinkle with cereal mixture. bake 20 minutes or until done. cool 15 minutes; remove from pan. cool on wire rack. drizzle with glaze.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
stone ground rye flour
stone ground corn meal
stone ground
baking soda
baking powder
salt
molasses
milk
raisins
directions:
grease well two 1 pound coffee cans.
place a rack or trivet on the bottom of large pot.
fill pot with water; bring to boil.
in large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
combine molasses and milk; add to dry ingredients.
stir in raisins.
fill coffee cans 2/3 full; cover with foil and secure with rubber band.
place cans on trivet in kettle.
(water should come 1/2 up sides of can.)
put lid on pot; keep water at simmer and steam bread 3 hours.
remove from pot; remove foil covers.
place cans in 300° oven for 10 minutes to "dry."<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
cabbage
zucchini
soy
onions
water
wine
mushrooms
directions:

brown sliced onions and set aside.

add at the end also.
serve over brown rice with soy sauce as a condiment. remember to cook vegetables only until lightly cooked.
crispy zucchini gives a lovely texture compliment to other vegetables and undercooking retains vitamins.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

dissolve soda in hot water.
add to sugar mixture.

mix in flour, cream of tartar, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
chill and roll out.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

milk
fruit pie filling
directions:

spread half on the crackers. put another layer of crackers and rest of pudding mix. put a third layer of crackers and top with the pie filling.
chill well before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

flour
lemon juice
salt
sugar
eggs
milk
directions:
cream oleo and sugar.
add egg yolks.
stir in lemon juice, milk and salt.

unsalted butter
vanilla

topping

cinnamon
directions:

milk,
sugar, butter and vanilla in a large saucepan.

reduce heat and keep at a
low
simmer
for

until
room temperature;

plump
raisins
in

container
of whipped topping and apricot preserves.	serve in	glasses topped with whipped topping and sprinkled with cinnamon.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green beans
canning salt
sugar
vinegar
directions:

bring to a boil.
cook for one hour.
put in jars to seal.

sugar
pecans
milk
salt
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

ham
pineapple
directions:

put about 2 tablespoons of pineapple in the center. wrap bacon around it and put a toothpick into it to hold the roll together.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

add 4 cups water, orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
add bananas (mix a small amount of the juice mixture with bananas to mix well).	after all ingredients are mixed freeze contents!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
walnuts
brown sugar
cinnamon
butter
flour
lemon juice
flour
baking powder
baking soda
salt
butter
sugar
vanilla
eggs
sour cream
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
grease 9-inch spring-form pan. combine 1 cup nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
for topping, cut 1/4 cup butter and 1/3 cup flour for coarse crumbs.
stir in 1/4 cup of nut mixture.
set both mixtures aside.
toss pears with lemon juice and set aside.
mix the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
in large bowl beat the 1/2 cup butter, sugar and vanilla.
add eggs one at a time.
add flour mixture and sour cream alternately to batter.
beat on low speed after each addition.
spread 2/3 mixture in prepared pan.
sprinkle with nut mix and layer pears on top.
spread with rest of batter and sprinkle topping.
bake 10 minutes and sprinkle with 1/2 cup more walnuts.
bake 50 minutes more.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
taco
fry bread
tomato
onion
cheddar cheese
sour cream
salsa
directions:
brown beef in a skillet, crumbling.
drain grease, then add taco seasoning according to directions on the envelope.
spoon over a piece of fry bread and top with any of the following desired: lettuce, tomato, onion, cheese, sour cream, salsa.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen hash browns
sour cream
cream of chicken soup
cheddar cheese
oleo
onion
directions:
set aside greased 9 x 13-inch pan. thaw hash browns.
saute onion in oleo.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brown sugar
white sugar
butter
cream
confectioners sugar
marshmallows
directions:
cream until smooth, then spread on cake.
you can add more powdered sugar, if needed.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar

water
oleo
salt
pecans
vanilla
directions:
mix together sugar, karo, buttermilk and hot water with soda. add to ingredients the oleo and salt.

stir until creamy, then drop by spoonful on buttered dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

boiling water

apples
nuts
directions:

mix all ingredients well.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onions
pork
worcestershire sauce

salt

brown beef and onions; drain fat.
add the other ingredients. mix well.
put in casserole dish.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
egg yolks
flour

milk

directions:
beat yolks and milk.
add to dry ingredients.
beat lumps out. cook until thick.
cool.
put in already cooked/cooled pie shells. beat egg whites and spread on top. brown in oven.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
vegetable oil
egg yolks
cold water
vanilla
lemon rind
egg whites
cream of tartar
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
make a well and add in order: oil, egg yolks, water, vanilla and rind.
beat with spoon until smooth.

pour egg yolk mixture over egg whites, gently folding with a rubber spatula just until blended.

bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes more.
let it hang until cold.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
milk
salt

vanilla
marshmallow cream
directions:

bring to a boil. boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. remove from heat.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beans
ham
onions
basil
bay leaves
ground pepper
worcestershire sauce
directions:
soak 2 cups of beans (i use 5 or 6 different kinds) overnight. drain water and place beans and fresh water in crock-pot with 2 quarts of water.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

slice onion, olives and water chestnuts.

(good.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

melt 2 sticks margarine; mix with some of the chicken broth.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

pour in baking dish.
mix sugar, flour and milk.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

's ketchup

angel

mix well.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
salt

flour

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
eggs
oil
zucchini
vanilla
soda
cinnamon
salt
pecans
directions:

add oil, sugar, vanilla, grated zucchini and nuts. set aside.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion
butter

rice
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

corn syrup
milk
vanilla
salt
butter
candied fruit
nuts
directions:

cook to soft ball stage.
remove from heat.
cool; beat until stiff.

pour into buttered dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

peanut butter
crackers
sugar
directions:

add peanut butter and cream well.

brown sugar

soda
salt
sugar
eggs
vanilla
flour
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar

butter
chocolate
eggs
vanilla
flour
baking soda
salt
nuts
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
celery
onion
chablis
butter
sugar
dill weed
directions:
combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
bring to a boil.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

chicken
cream of chicken soup
mushroom soup
bell pepper
onion
pimentos
ro-tel tomatoes
grated cheese
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shell
tuna
swiss cheese
onion
eggs
mayonnaise
milk
directions:

pour into baked pie shell.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
cheddar cheese
american cheese
green pepper
salt
pecans
white pepper
onion
pimiento
worcestershire sauce
soy sauce
tabasco sauce
directions:
grate cheese.
mix with other ingredients.
form into large ball.
wrap in foil.
store in refrigerator for 2 or more days to age.
roll in pecans just before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
grater
sugar
salt
pepper
eggs
flour
baking powder
directions:
mix squash or corn, sugar, salt, pepper and eggs. mix well, causing mixture to become juicy. add flour and baking powder. drop (like pancakes) into hot oil. cook about 10 minutes on each side.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
onion
flour
beef stock
milk
grated cheese
paprika
directions:
melt the butter in a pot.
add the onion and cook slowly until limp.
stir in the flour and continue to cook for 3 minutes, stirring.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
stewing beef
oil
onions
tomatoes
tapioca
clove garlic

parsley flakes
bay leaf

potatoes
celery

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
directions:

while this is setting add sugar to a gallon container. pour tea over sugar and stir until it is dissolved.

onion
sugar
salt

celery
vinegar
directions:

recipe can be cut down 1/2 or 1/4.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter
directions:
melt 1 stick of butter.
pour melted butter over cake mix; mix thoroughly.
spread pie filling on the bottom of an 8-inch round baking pan.

bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes, or until light golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tostitos
chili
directions:
heat, mix, and serve with your favorite chips!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peaches
soy sauce
chicken
directions:

combine juice with soy sauce, and pour over chicken.
put in oven at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
turn chicken
over and bake 30 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
egg
vanilla
flour

oats
directions:

and
sugars
until fluffy.

beat.
add
flour, soda, salt and spices.

oats.

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar

directions:

(add tabasco only if you like spicy dip and mix.)

325° oven for 15 minutes or until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

melted.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
average
bell pepper
onion
vinegar
sugar
salt

dry mustard
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

generous

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mix flour, 1/2 cup chopped pecans and butter and press in baking pan.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter
salt
onion
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

nuts

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

tomatoes

onions
green pepper
garlic
chili powder
pepper
directions:
in large saucepan, mix all ingredients.

cover the pan tightly with foil.
refrigerate all day or overnight.
just before baking, spread with soup and mushrooms. bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 300° to 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

baking soda
prune puree

directions:

mix well.

drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough on sheet.
bake at 350° for 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

evenly cover the bottom and sides of a 9 inch deep dish pie plate with the ready to bake brownies, forming a crust.

eggs

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion
green bell pepper

milk
noodles
cheddar cheese
directions:
brown hamburger and drain off grease.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
each jello
sour cream

combine sugar and milk.
heat until sugar is dissolved.
mix knox gelatine and water and heat until dissolved.

directions:
try to get a possum that has been dead no longer than 3 days and doesn't have any tire marks on his back.
add that rascal to a pot of boiling water, along with the pepper pods, salt and butter. cook him 3 to 6 hours.
if he ain't tender, you'll know you got an old possum.

remember to stir constantly, so he won't cling to the pot.
if he sticks to the pot, pry him off.

egg
milk

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

celery
mustard

pepper

apple cider vinegar
directions:
stir all ingredients together.

egg

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

tomato soup
sugar
oil
vinegar
salt
dry mustard
onion
green pepper
pepper
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

to
