stir in sherry, salt, pimentos, crab, pepper, 2 tablespoons parsley and the dissolved gelatin.
pour into a 3-cup ring mold.
refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
to serve, turn out on plate.
garnish with the remaining parsley.
place parsley sprigs in center.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
water
rice
salt
marshmallows
maraschino cherries
whipped cream
directions:
drain tidbits; mix the syrup and water.
boil.
add rice and salt.
reduce heat; cover and cook.
cool.
fold in pineapple, marshmallows, cherries (quartered) and whipped cream.
chill. serves 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
water
packets washington brown seasoning broth
stalks celery
potatoes
onion
frozen soup vegetables
clove garlic
cabbage
pasta
directions:
can add 1 can of kidney beans, pinto beans or green beans.
add more water, if needed.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
water chestnuts
chicken soup
sour cream onion
rice
buttered cornflake crumbs
directions:
mix all ingredients in very large bowl; pour into greased casserole dish.
sprinkle with buttered cornflake crumbs.
bake at 325° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
semi-sweet chocolate bits
butter
colored marshmallows
pecans
directions:
melt chocolate and butter or margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
remove from heat and cool.
stir in marshmallows and 1/4 cup nuts.
divide mixture in half and shape each into 6-inch long log, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
roll each in rest of nuts and chill.
when chilled, slice into 1/2-inch pieces.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pack cream cheese
milk
cheddar cheese
green onions
directions:
beat cream cheese and milk in a small bowl until smooth. add cheese and green onions. mix well. cover and chill 1 hr. shape into 1 inch balls. place pretzel stick in them and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sugar
eggs
flour
baking soda
baking powder
vanilla
directions:
preheat oven.
cream the butter and sugar.
gradually add the other ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
bake at 350° for 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mashed ripe bananas
nectar
low-fat milk
directions:
place all ingredients in blender.
cover and blend about 30 seconds or until smooth.
serve at once over ice cubes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
bread crumbs
pepper
milk
pork sausage
onion
chili powder
cream of mushroom soup
water
cream of celery soup
milk
directions:
combine the first 7 ingredients and shape into balls.
brown, cover and cook for 10 minutes.
set aside.
in a 2 1/2-quart casserole, add the remaining ingredients.
heat until steaming. add meatballs and top with biscuits.
bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yeast
water
butter
milk
sugar
salt
flour
directions:
dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; put milk, butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan and bring to a scald (do not boil), letting butter melt.
stir.
put milk mixture in a large bowl; add yeast mixture and stir together.
sift in the 5 cups of flour gradually until dough is formed.
cover and place in warm place to rise. let rise 15 minutes.
knead dough down and roll out on a floured surface to cut into rolls.
place rolls on a greased pan, touching each other.
cover with wax paper and let rise about 15 minutes. bake in 450° to 475° oven for about 12 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
brown sugar
white sugar
vanilla
eggs
flour
soda
salt
directions:
cream shortening and sugar together.
mix eggs and other ingredients.
add m&m's.
bake at 350° for 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
all-purpose
baking powder
regular vanilla pudding
margarine
egg
milk
peaches
cream cheese
sugar
syrup
directions:
drain peaches.
reserve 3 tablespoons of syrup.
blot peaches with paper towel.
beat first 6 ingredients until smooth.
pour into greased pie pan.
arrange sliced peaches on top of batter mix.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
milk
margarine
cocoa
oats
nuts
peanut butter
vanilla
directions:
combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a heavy saucepan. bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring and let boil 1 1/2 minutes. remove from heat. stir in oats, nuts, peanut butter and vanilla, mixing well. drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. makes about 3 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork sausage
bread crumbs
broccoli
mushrooms
cheddar cheese
eggs
milk
miracle
flour
mustard
basil
salt
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
brown sausage; drain.
add bread cubes, broccoli, mushrooms and cheese.
mix lightly.
spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole.
pour combined eggs, milk, dressing, flour and seasonings over bread mixture.
cover and refrigerate one hour or overnight.
bake, uncovered, for 1 hour. makes 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
applesauce
lemon flavor
pineapple
directions:
mix ingredients in the order written.
refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef brisket
salt
black pepper
garlic powder
onions
directions:
line a 13 x 10-inch pan with 1 large sheet of foil to cover meat completely later.
put in brisket, season beef and arrange onion slices on top.
bake at 350° for 1 hour.
when onions brown slightly, then cover (seal) beef tightly with foil.
add 1 cup of water to pan (may have to add more water).
reduce heat to 300°. cook 2 more hours.
keep sealed.
after 3 hours, open and check. if fork-tender, it's cooked long enough.
make gravy from the juices.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
cooking oil
catsup
water
vinegar
dry mustard
pepper
frankfurters
rice
directions:
saute onion in oil until tender.
stir in catsup, water, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
place frankfurters in a 1-quart baking dish.
pour sauce over.
bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
if desired, serve over toast or rice.
makes 5 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
sugar
eggs
mashed ripe bananas
lemon juice
flour
baking powder
salt
nut meats
directions:
grease loaf pan.
mix shortening and sugar together.
beat eggs and add.
mix bananas and lemon juice together.
add to mixture. sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to mixture. add nuts.
bake in loaf pan at 375° for 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
steak
ketchup
onions
garlic
salt
water
directions:
brown round steak.
quarter onions and add water.
add seasoning.
simmer approximately 3 hours.
add ketchup to taste, approximately 8 to 12 ounces.
simmer 1 hour more.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peaches
chicken
oil
margarine
brown sugar
vinegar
allspice
stove top stuffing chicken flavor
directions:
drain peaches, reserving syrup.
add water to make 1 cup.
set aside.
brown chicken in hot oil in skillet.

reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn
whole kernel corn
eggs
sour cream
onion
margarine
green pepper
sugar
salt
cheese
corn muffin
directions:
mix all ingredients, except cheese.
bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
spread cheese on top and bake 30 minutes more, until knife comes out clean.
serves 15 to 20.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chocolate cake
sugar
milk
coconut
marshmallows
pecans
sugar
milk
butter
chocolate chips
directions:
make cake according to directions and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan. boil 1 cup sugar with 1 cup milk over medium heat.
stir in marshmallows, coconut and pecans.
pour over warm cake.
bring 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup milk and butter to a boil.
stir in chips to melt.
spread on cake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sugar
eggs
baking powder
milk
vanilla
nuts
graham crackers
directions:
cream butter and sugar.
add egg yolks.
beat thoroughly. combine with graham cracker crumbs, rolled fine, and baking powder. add flavoring, milk and nuts.
mix thoroughly.
fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
pour into well-oiled, shallow pans.
bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
serve with whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen hash browns
cream of chicken soup
sour cream
oleo
onions
salt

shredded cheese
directions:
mix ingredients together in a large bowl by hand.
spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
bake 1 hour at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
vanilla wafer crumbs
pecans
chocolate chips
coconut
milk
directions:
melt margarine in bottom of baking dish.
layer the vanilla wafer crumbs, chocolate pieces, nuts and coconut.
dribble the eagle brand milk over the top.
bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
cool and cut in desired size squares.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
wings
onion
soy sauce
sugar
vegetable oil
ground ginger
poultry seasoning
directions:
mix all ingredients and pour over wings.
marinate overnight. bake at 350° for 15 minutes on each side.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sour cream
vanilla
sugar
eggs
roll
cinnamon
directions:
spray 13 x 9 x 2 pan with a little pam, take a paper towel and wipe the pam around the pan.
beat first 4 ingredients together, then beat in 5 eggs, one at a time; after each beating until well mixed.

pour ingredients on top of crescent rolls sprinkle top of mixture with cinnamon before baking.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

water
lemon juice
sugar
syrup
nutmeg
margarine
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white bread
bacon
salt
cheddar cheese
eggs
milk
directions:
grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
in dish, layer bread, bacon and cheese.
beat together eggs, milk and salt; pour over bread, bacon and cheese layers.

cut in squares.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork chops
salt
onion
beef consomme
sour cream
flour
directions:
rub chops on both sides with salt, pepper and sage.
brown chops in a large skillet.
place onion slices on top of chops. add consomme. cover and simmer 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apples

flour
cinnamon
salt
margarine
lemon juice
water
directions:
mix brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt until crumbly. place apples and mixture alternately in greased baking dish.
add 2 teaspoons of lemon juice to 1/2 cup water and pour over all. cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
meal
eggs
wesson oil
sour cream
cream-style
directions:
mix well and pour into an 8-inch lightly greased pan.
bake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
cooking oil
potatoes
onion
cream of mushroom soup
directions:
cut meat into serving pieces; salt and dip in flour.
brown in skillet in hot oil.
place vegetables on top of meat.
add mushroom soup.
cover skillet; turn heat to simmer (when steam escapes freely).
simmer 50 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

green pepper
onion
marinade sauce
directions:
slightly freeze roast to cut into thin slices.
add marinade sauce.
follow directions on back of marinade sauce package.
when meat is almost done, add onions and peppers.
when done, put in shell.
add shredded cheese, sour cream, black olives, onions, lettuce and tomatoes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cherry jello
water
sugar

orange

celery
pecans
directions:
dissolve jello in hot water.
add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
chill.
add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until set.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

pepperoni
peppers
onion
cream of mushroom soup
sausage
directions:
layer in baking dish, saving some cheese for the top.
bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter

vanilla

directions:

melt butter.
add sugar and dissolve.
pour water with cornstarch into butter and brown sugar mixture and bring to a boil.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

in 3-quart saucepan, heat cranberries, sugar, vinegar, and water to boiling over high heat, stirring frequently.
reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, until most of cranberries pop, about 10 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vinegar
water
worcestershire sauce
mustard
tomato catsup
directions:
heat and let come to boil.
salt and arrange chicken in pyrex, greased well.
pour sauce over chicken.
sprinkle heavily with flour and dot with butter and pepper.
cook at 400° until bubbly. then turn to 300° to 325° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours, according to size of chicken pieces.
turn good side up first and turn over about halfway through.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour

baking powder
baking soda
salt
eggs
sugar
oil
vanilla
summer
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
mix dry ingredients, except sugar, thoroughly.
beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
beat until lemon colored, about 3 minutes.
stir in squash.
add dry ingredients; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
pour in loaf pan.
bake for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.

remove from pan after 10 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
pumpkin
milk
salt
ginger
cold water
pie shell
directions:
to slightly beaten egg yolks, add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk, salt and spices.
cook until thick in a double boiler. pour water into a bowl and sprinkle gelatin on top of water.
add to hot pumpkin mixture.
mix thoroughly and cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

chicken broth
chicken
peas
crust
mushrooms
carrots
salt
directions:
in saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
add onion and celery and cook until soft.
stir in flour and cook until thickened.
add pepper and nutmeg.
gradually stir in broth, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
mix in chicken, peas, mushrooms and carrots.
season to taste.
pour chicken mixture into a 9-inch baking dish, 2-inches deep.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
salt
eggs
nabisco vanilla wafers
flour
milk
vanilla
bananas
directions:
combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. stir in milk.
cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
cook, uncovered, 15 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
beat egg yolks.
gradually stir in hot mixture. return from heat and add vanilla.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
cream of mushroom soup
mayonnaise
eggs
onion soup
cheddar cheese
directions:
cook broccoli.
mix soup, mayonnaise and soup together.
add broccoli and eggs; cover with grated cheese.
bake uncovered at 325° for 45 minutes or until hot and fluffy.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sweet peas
cream of mushroom soup
yellow onion
ground sirloin
potatoes
garlic
directions:
cook ground sirloin in skillet; drain fat.
while meat is cooking, peel and quarter potatoes.
place in large pot of water and boil for 25 to 30 minutes.
drain the potatoes and mash using small amount of milk, butter, salt and pepper.
dice onion.
add onion to meat after it has been drained.
cook a little longer and add the soup and sweet peas.
mix altogether in skillet.
put meat mixture in casserole dish.
place mashed potatoes on top of meat. do not mix.
place in broiler to brown tops of mashed potatoes. enjoy.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
butter
salt
pepper
cream of chicken soup
onion
flour
clove garlic
mushrooms
sour cream
parsley
noodles
directions:
in a large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender. stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms. cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. stir in soup; heat to boiling, stirring constantly. reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. stir in sour cream and heat through.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
corn tortillas
cream of chicken soup

green chili salsa
milk
onion
grated cheese
directions:
salt chicken; wrap in foil and bake 1 hour at 400°.
cool and cut into bite size pieces.
break 6 tortillas in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
spread half of the cut up chicken over the tortillas.
mix the rest of the ingredients (except the cheese) together and pour half the mixture over the chicken and tortillas. repeat layers and cover with shredded cheese.
refrigerate overnight.
remove from fridge and let it come to room temperature.
bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
powdered sugar
sour cream
lemon juice
orange rind
directions:
mix all ingredients together.
refrigerate.
serve with any fruit.
may also be used as a dressing for fruit salad.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
sugar
vanilla
o
boiling water
graham cracker crumbs
margarine
directions:
mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine together.
put in pan and pat in place.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pretzels
margarine
sugar
cream cheese
sugar
strawberry jello
boiling water
frozen strawberries
directions:
combine pretzels, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar in bowl; mix well.
press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
cool.
beat cream cheese, whipped topping and 1/2 cup sugar in mixer bowl until well blended.
spread over cooled crust.
dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
spoon over cream cheese mixture.
chill until firm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
blueberries
sugar
water
bread
whipped cream
directions:
boil sugar and water until it thickens as syrup.
add blueberries and boil 3 to 4 minutes.
butter a casserole dish. place a slice of bread, a layer of berries, alternating and ending with berries on top.
chill in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
serve with whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornmeal
egg
flour
milk
sugar
mayo
directions:
mix all dry ingredients first.
add milk, mayo and egg, gradually, stirring well.
preheat oven to 475 degrees.
bake about 25 minutes or until browned.
i recommend using a small iron skillet-reserving it for cornbread only.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg whites
powdered sugar
cake flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
vegetable oil
lemons
fresh squeezed lemon juice
directions:
in a large bowl using electric mixer, whip egg whites with powdered sugar until fluffy, but not dry.
set whites aside.
in another bowl, sift flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt.
scoop out a well in the center of the flour and add oil, lemon rind and juice.
with medium speed on mixer, beat until well blended and smooth.
fold the batter into the whites.
spread solid shortening on bottom and sides of 9-inch tube pan and dust with flour.
pour batter into pan and bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
(should spring back to touch.)
cool cake right side up in pan for 5 minutes. invert onto wire rack and lift off the pan.
cool completely and ice, if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green peas
potatoes
onions
celery
garlic
leaf marjoram
oregano
chicken bouillon
water
chicken stock
salt
directions:
cook peas 1/2 hour in water to cover.
add remaining ingredients.
cook until tender.
put in blender and blend smooth. it may be thinned with more stock, if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breast
water
bouillon
oil
poultry seasoning
salt
pepper
parsley
carrots
celery
onions
directions:
add all ingredients into a 3-quart pot.
cook until vegetables are tender and chicken is done.
then remove chicken, cut into small pieces and return back into pot.
simmer 10 minutes, then serve with noodles.
makes 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cranberries
sections
lemon jello
directions:
add 1 cup
water
to
jello.
add 7 ice cubes and stir. put in refrigerator
until
it
starts to congeal.
add cranberries and grapefruit sections (cut up).
put in pyrex dish. chill well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground suet
molasses
milk
flour
salt
nutmeg
baking soda
cream of tartar
cinnamon
cloves
raisins
currants
citron
directions:
combine suet, molasses, and milk.
sift flour.
measure. reserve 1/4 cup for dredging the fruits.
sift remainder of flour with salt, spices, cream of tartar and baking soda.
combine with first mixture.
add dredged fruits.
mix thoroughly.
fill well oiled 1 pound pan 2/3 full.
cover.
steam 3 hours.
serve hot with any desired pudding sauce.
makes 12 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
roll
cream cheese
powdered sugar
fresh fruit
directions:
spread dough in a pizza pan or jelly roll pan.
bake as directed.
whip together cream cheese and powdered sugar until desired consistency is reached.
spread on top of cooled cookie dough.
on top of cookie, arrange a variety of your favorite fresh fruits, sliced or cut up (strawberries, kiwi, blueberries, bananas, peaches, etc.).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cake flour
baking powder
salt
butter
sugar
vanilla
lemon oil
eggs
buttermilk
lemon peel
lemon juice
pecans
granulated sugar
lemon juice
directions:
preheat oven to 350°. grease and flour a 10-inch fluted tube pan. set pan aside.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
milk
salt
pepper
pancake mix
directions:
let chicken soak in milk for 1 hour.
drain and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
roll in pancake mix until well coated.
fry in deep fat until done and floats, 5 to 7 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
cheddar cheese
pepper
green olives
worcestershire sauce
lemon juice
directions:
mix cream cheese and cheddar cheese together.
add remaining ingredients.
scoop into a ball in the bowl.
refrigerate 1/2 hour.
remove from bowl and form a more shapely ball.
roll in crushed walnuts, or cracker crumbs of your choice.
serve with assorted crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
sugar
eggs
milk
vanilla
flour
salt
baking powder
directions:
cream shortening; add sugar and continue creaming until fluffy.
add eggs.
beat until light.
sift flour; measure.
add salt and baking powder and sift twice more.
add vanilla to milk. add dry and liquid ingredients alternately to creamed mixture. beat until thoroughly blended.
bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°. makes 2 (8-inch) layers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fryer

onion
chicken broth
directions:
boil fryer and debone.
mix soup, tomatoes, onions and broth in a separate bowl.
layer ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan in following order:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

coat chicken.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
cauliflower
water chestnuts

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs

beat eggs and sugar until thick and creamy. add flour and baking powder. beat.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs

directions:
prepare eggs.
prepare white sauce and add cheese.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
here is the butterscotch version of the meringue recipe you call forgotten cookies.
they are also called simple simons.<|endofrecipe|>

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

chicken noodle
cream of mushroom soup
eggs
bread
butter

directions:
mix all together, except butter and cracker crumbs.

mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.

directions:
heat oven to 350°.
grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
in large bowl, combine
cake mix, 6 tablespoons of margarine and 1 cup rolled oats;
mix	until
crumbly.
reserve
1 cup crumbs for topping. to	remaining
crumbs,
add
1 egg; mix well.
press into
pan. pour
pie filling over crust.
to reserved crumbs, add
remaining 1/4
cup rolled oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, nuts
and

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
peel sweet potatoes and mix sweet potatoes, flour and sugar; separate egg whites and mix eggs in the mixture.

enjoy.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
milk
cornflake crumbs
parmesan cheese

pepper
directions:
pull skin and fat from chicken.
pour milk over chicken.
let set 15 minutes.
combine remaining ingredients.
roll chicken in mix.
place on cooking sheet.
spray with cooking spray.
bake for 45 minutes at 375°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

choice

mix all ingredients together.
chill until firm.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork
water
baking soda
salt
firewood
wash
handle
flats
paper
friends
liquid
directions:
put wash pot on hot fire.
pour water into pot.
put pork fat into pot.
the water will all boil out, but it keeps the fat from sticking to the pot.
the pot should be stirred with axe handle every 5 to 10 minutes throughout the cooking.
remember, keep the fire hot.
the lard will boil out of the meat during the cooking. when the lard covers the meat, add the baking soda.
don't use very much baking soda or pot will foam over.
the cracklin's will begin to float and the skins will bubble up.
it is very important to have a hot fire at this point.
when the lard stops bubbling and boiling, the cracklin's are just about done.
they should be golden brown and the skin should appear puffed up.
dip the cracklin's out and put them in the paper lined cardboard flats.
salt to taste. let them cool about 15 minutes.
the lard may be saved for frying, but check with your doctor first.
approximate time required:
2 1/2 hours.
serves about 20 to 25.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

anise
anise seed

add 2 eggs and flavoring.
stir in flour mixture and mix well.
add nuts to batter.
chill well (about 2 hours).

brush top with egg white from third egg.

this dessert is in layers.

and

10

the night before:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
can use chocolate bars instead of mixing paraffin.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
realemon juice
water
bouillon
garlic
pepper
chicken pieces
directions:
in plastic bag, combine all ingredients, except chicken.

cover.
marinate in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.

heat marinade thoroughly.
grill or broil chicken, basting frequently with marinade.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white bread
ham
cheddar cheese
eggs
milk
onion salt
salt
directions:
in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan layer half of the bread, chopped ham and cheese; repeat.

cover and refrigerate overnight.

a good sunday morning brunch.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

bacon
green onion
cream cheese
nuts
directions:
fry bacon and crumble.
in a large mixing bowl, combine cheddar cheese, cream cheese, green onion and bacon.
squish it all together with hands until everything is evenly mixed.
form into balls, whatever size you prefer.
roll the ball in chopped nuts or parsley.
keep chilled in refrigerator, until ready to serve, so it becomes firm.
serve with your favorite crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef stew meat
onions
carrots
potatoes
peas

cream of celery soup
bay leaf
salt
liquid from peas
directions:

just put it in the oven and wait.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pie crust
sugar
flour
butter
peaches
nutmeg
directions:
mix the sugar, flour and butter to make streusel mixture. sprinkle 4 tablespoons streusel mixture in bottom of pie crust. peel and cut peaches in half.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground deer
onion
chili beans
tomatoes
chili powder
directions:

in pan put rest of ingredients.
bring to boil and then add meat.
cook until done. add 2 tablespoons brown sugar.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
salt
pepper
bread crumbs
catsup
brown sugar
mustard
pork
directions:

shape into balls, brown and pour off the fat.
add all but beans.

add beans and bake 25 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bran
all-bran
boiling water
sugar
shortening
flour
eggs
buttermilk
salt
soda
directions:
mix salt
and soda with flour.
pour boiling water over bran and
set aside.
mix other ingredients and add bran.
mix all thoroughly
and refrigerate.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
lemon
green onions
worcestershire sauce
chachere
mayonnaise
baby shrimp
directions:
blend lemon and cream cheese.
add other ingredients and mix. refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
serve with chicken in a biskit crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
avocado
lemon
onion
tabasco sauce
garlic
fritos
directions:
mash meat of 1 very, very, large avocado with a fork.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
oleo
sugar
graham crackers
pecans
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
cover bottom of cookie sheet with graham crackers.
melt butter and oleo over medium heat; add sugar.
bring to a hard boil, stirring continually.
boil 2 minutes.
pour over graham crackers covering completely. sprinkle with pecans.
bake 10 minutes.
watch that it doesn't burn around to edges.
remove from oven and let cool 2 to 3 minutes.
remove from pan to cooling rack.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
brown sugar
vegetable oil
vanilla
egg
flour
baking soda
salt
semi-sweet chocolate chips
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
mix sugars, oil, vanilla and egg in a bowl with a spoon until smooth.
stir in flour, salt and baking soda.
spread dough into a greased square or round (8 or 9-inch) cake pan.
sprinkle with chips.
bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
cool. cut into squares or wedges.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
dressing
green peppers
cornflake crumbs
chili powder
onion powder
directions:
combine 1/2 teaspoon chili powder with bread crumbs.
combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken breasts which lay in buttered casserole.
cover with bread crumb mixture.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
cooking oil
flour
each soda
eggs
vanilla
apples
pecans
directions:
cream sugar and oil.
sift remainder of dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with 1 well beaten egg at a time. add vanilla, apples and nuts.
pour into greased and floured bundt pan.
bake 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hamburger
bacon
onion
brown sugar
sugar
ketchup
barbecue sauce
mustard
molasses
chili powder
salt
pepper
kidney beans
butter
pork
directions:
add all ingredients except hamburger, bacon and onion.
pour all ingredients into large baking pan.
add beans.
add hamburger, bacon and onion.
bake at 350° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cauliflower
head lettuce
onion
crisp bacon
salad dressing
parmesan cheese
directions:
cut up cauliflower.
tear up lettuce (i prefer to use hands instead of knife).
crumble up bacon.
mix all ingredients together with dressing.
sprinkle cheese over top.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
sugar
egg
flour
baking soda
baking powder
salt
cocoa
milk
vanilla
directions:
preheat oven to 425°. cream shortening and sugar. add egg and mix. add dry ingredients with milk and mix. add vanilla and mix again. drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. bake for 7 to 8 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

lean beef
paprika
butter
garlic
beef broth
green onions
green peppers
cornstarch
water
soy sauce
tomatoes
directions:
while rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4-inch thick and cut into 1/4-inch strips.
sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
using a large skillet, brown meat in butter.
add garlic and broth.
cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
stir in onions and green peppers.
cover and cook for 5 minutes more.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
grape-nuts
butter
sugar
eggs
milk
raisins
nutmeg
salt

blend sugar into eggs.
add cereal mixture and remaining ingredients.
mix well.<|endofrecipe|>

bananas
nuts
directions:

beat well.

chill until serving time.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

milk
flour
butter

semi-sweet chocolate chips

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken broth
chicken
potatoes
celery
onion
eggs
salt
milk
flour
directions:
knead briefly and roll out on floured surface as thin as you can.
cut into squares.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
applesauce

pepper

egg

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

salt
garlic

directions:

egg whites

this is a great batter for chicken!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
mix well, store in airtight container.<|endofrecipe|>

directions:

jello
together
by
directions on box in a mixing bowl and

into
a

nuts

butter

clean and boil potatoes whole with skins, leave firm, 15 minutes.

put in plastic bag. seal and refrigerate overnight.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

clove

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

chicken bouillon
water
butter
salt
onion
flour
warm milk
directions:

salt

directions:

in square 9 x 9-inch pan.

nuts

whipping cream

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

curry powder
orange

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar

salt

coloring

shortening
water

butter

knead for 10 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar

vanilla

pie shell

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

oil

flour
vanilla

chill.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter

directions:

pinch
of

a

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs

flour

salt

water
directions:
note:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

red
stalks celery

directions:

if not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.

chips

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

mix all ingredients
well.
bake
in
350°
oven in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

brown chicken on all sides.

pudding,
powdered
sugar	and
milk together with mixer, about
2
minutes
at

to

mix all ingredients together and chill. serve over baked potato.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
raspberry flavored gelatin
boiling water
cranberry sauce
pineapple
pears
directions:
dissolve the gelatin in boiling water. stir in the cranberry sauce, pineapple and pears. use potato masher to mash and mix all together. pour into a tupperware pan of 9 x 9 x 3-inch or larger. makes about 16 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cottage cheese
orange juice
white wine vinegar
basil
salt
pepper
orange zest
pasta
chicken breast
parsley
tomato
directions:
in a blender, puree the first 6 ingredients until smooth.
when done, stir in orange zest.
then stir mix with cooked pasta.
add chicken, tomato, and parsley last.
refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
water
egg noodles
cream of mushroom soup
heavy cream
celery
bell pepper
onion
parsley sprig
garlic
velveeta cheese
directions:
layer precooked noodles then tuna, then veggies.
mix soup with small amount of water; dribble over each layer.
add velveeta cheese.
do another layer and top with cheese.
cok covered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
last 5 minutes cook uncovered to brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
garlic
onion
garlic salt
pepper
italian seasoning
tomatoes
tomato sauce
olive oil
bay leaves
salt
directions:
brown meat and drain.
saute garlic and onion in olive oil. add to meat.
add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring often.
add water if necessary to keep right consistency. add olives, oregano or basil to taste.
serves 50.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
vegetable oil
directions:
wash and cut potatoes into wedges,
leaving
skins
on. in a casserole dish, pour
just	enough	vegetable oil to coat bottom. put the potatoes
in
the casserole dish and sprinkle with mrs. dash extra	spicy
seasoning.
cover
dish	with wax paper and microwave on high
for
20	minutes.
turn	dish and stir taters a couple times
while
cooking.
if
you like real spicy food, sprinkle on
more
seasoning.
when
time
is
up, allow to set for 5 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef
miracle
spaghetti sauce
macaroni
directions:
heat on medium, stirring occasionally.
top with cheese. serves 4 to 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
celery
onion
eggs
rice
chicken broth
salt
cream of chicken soup
mayonnaise
onion
directions:
cut yellow tendons at top of legs (to keep from kicking batter off when cooking).
soak in cold, salty water for 1 hour.
coat with bread crumbs.
let set for 1 hour in refrigerator.
remove and fry in hot grease until brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
swiss cheese
italian ham
flour
paprika
margarine
sherry wine
chicken
cornstarch
whipping cream
directions:
spread chicken breasts flat.
fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.
on waxed paper, mix flour and paprika.
use mixture to coat chicken pieces.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
parsley flakes
soy sauce
garlic salt
bread crumbs
onion
eggs
ketchup
cranberry sauce
chili sauce
brown sugar
lemon juice
directions:
combine ground beef, parsley flakes, soy sauce, garlic, bread crumbs, onion, eggs and ketchup in large bowl; mix well.
form into balls; put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
jumbo shells
parmesan cheese
shredded mozzarella
parsley flakes
sauce
directions:
cook ground beef and drain.
cook shells, drain and cool.
mix together cheese and parsley flakes.
fill with about 2 tablespoons of cheese mix.
put in baking dish (9 x 12-inch) and pour over the meat and sauce plus any leftover cheeses.
bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
spice cake
condensed milk
sour cream
ground cinnamon
apples
lemon juice
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
prepare cake mix as directed.
stir in apples.
pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. meanwhile, in bowl, combine milk, sour cream and lemon juice. remove cake from oven.
spread cream mixture over top; return to oven and bake 10 minutes more or until set.
sprinkle with cinnamon.
refrigerate any leftovers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broiler-fryer
yellow cornmeal
all-purpose
ground ginger
salt
sugar
paprika
onion salt
garlic salt
milk
peaches
soy sauce
brown sugar
ground ginger
directions:
cut chicken into 6 serving size pieces.
mix cornmeal, flour, the 1 teaspoon ginger, salt, sugar, paprika, onion salt and garlic salt.
dip chicken into milk; coat with cornmeal mixture.
place, skin side up, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
bake, uncovered, in a hot oven (400°) for 50 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
water
salt
vegetable cooking oil
cream of tartar
coloring
directions:
cook all ingredients over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture pulls away from pan and is no longer sticky.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
shortening
molasses
cinnamon
ginger
cloves spice
boiling water
flour
soda
salt
eggs
directions:
mix together sugar, shortening and molasses.
add spices, then boiling water.
stir together.
sift, then measure flour and sift with soda and salt into the mixture.
beat well, then add last the 2 well beaten eggs and beat thoroughly.
pour into a long cake pan that has been greased on the bottom and lightly floured before pouring the batter into the pan.
bake in a preheated moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until tested done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
powdered sugar
crunchy peanut butter
rice krispies
margarine
directions:
combine all ingredients and shape into logs 1 x 2-inches. chill, then glaze with melted chocolate chips.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cooking oil
sugar
flour
carrots
eggs
pineapple
cinnamon
vanilla
baking soda
baking powder
pecan
directions:
add in large bowl the oil, sugar, eggs, carrots, pineapple and vanilla.
stir by hand, then add remaining ingredients and stir by hand again.
bake in 2 round cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
stalks celery
rice
pineapple
sugar
lemon juice
directions:
cut up carrots and celery.
mix all ingredients well.
cover and chill before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggplant
tomatoes
swiss cheese
salt
bread crumbs
sweet basil
directions:
soak eggplant slices in cold water for several hours.
drain and arrange layers of eggplant and tomatoes in a buttered baking dish.
sprinkle each layer with grated cheese, salt and pepper. sprinkle top with bread crumbs, more cheese and sweet basil.
dot with butter, bake 300° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cabbage
onion
celery
bell pepper
oleo
flour
salt
cayenne pepper
milk
cheddar cheese
bread crumbs
directions:
boil cabbage 10 minutes, uncovered, until tender-crisp. drain.
place in casserole. blend oleo and flour in saucepan over medium heat. add onion, celery, pepper, salt and cayenne pepper. saute 10 minutes.
add the milk and cheddar cheese. blend well until melted.
pour over cabbage. top with the bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(i use hot mexican velveeta cheese.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef
carrots
potatoes
corn
green beans
onion
tomato juice
salt
basil
oregano
parsley
directions:
in a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
bring to a boil.
reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
if necessary, add 1/2 to 1 cup water to thin soup. yield:
6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cabbage
green onions
sesame seed plus
onions
ramen noodles
directions:
toast sesame seed and almonds in 2 tablespoons of butter until light brown.
cool.
break up noodles.
add onions, sesame seed and almonds.
toss with dressing.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cake
lime
frozen strawberries
cream
frozen blueberries
oranges
directions:
tear up cake in 3 bowls.
sprinkle in dry jello.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
mayonnaise
onion
horseradish
cheddar cheese
buttered bread crumbs
directions:
in saucepan, cook carrots just until crisp-tender.
drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
place carrots in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and reserved cooking liquid.
spread evenly over carrots.
sprinkle with cheese.
top with bread crumbs.
bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
yields 8 to 10 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
salad oil
flour tortillas
ground beef
onion
garlic
green chilies
beans
taco sauce
salt
cheese
shredded lettuce
tomato
olives
directions:
in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, fry 1 tortilla at a time, about 30 seconds on each side until lightly browned and blistered. with tongs, remove tortilla to paper towels to drain. discard any remaining oil.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream-style
green chilies
oil
garlic salt
baking powder
eggs
grits
cheddar cheese
directions:
place all ingredients (except cheese) into a casserole dish and mix together. add most of cheese and mix into the casserole. sprinkle the remaining cheese on top. bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. to test, insert knife into middle; it should be clean when removed. serves 12+. can do ahead.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
thin cucumbers
onions
salt
vinegar
sugar
black pepper
directions:
sprinkle cucumbers and onions with salt.
let set for 2 hours. combine vinegar, sugar and pepper.
pack cucumbers in plastic containers.
cover with vinegar mixture; seal.
freeze.
thaw as needed.
these are real crispy and good!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
semi-sweet chocolate
butter
rice krispies
directions:
melt chocolate and butter in double boiler; add cereal and stir until coated.
press into pie pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
vanilla ice cream
banana
vanilla extract
directions:
put all in blender.
process until smooth.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
golden cake mix
eggs
wesson oil
oranges
cool whip
pineapple
vanilla pudding
directions:
mix cake mix, oil, oranges and eggs and bake for 25 minutes at 350 degrees.
cool completely.
mix cool whip, pineapple, and pudding.
spread over top of cake with a spoon.
refrigerate overnight and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
soda cracker crumbs
salt
egg
cream-style corn
pepper
directions:
in 1-quart glass casserole, heat butter 30 seconds.
add egg, cracker crumbs, corn, salt and pepper; blend evenly.
cook 4 to 6 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
rest 5 minutes before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli spears
cream of mushroom soup
egg
mayonnaise
onion
salt
directions:
cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain well.
cut into bite size pieces and place in buttered casserole dish.
combine soup, egg, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
pour over broccoli and top with 1/2 cup crushed cheese crackers.
bake 30 minutes at 400°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oreos
butter
french vanilla pudding
cream cheese
milk
powdered sugar
directions:
crust:
crush oreos with rolling pin on waxed paper; mix with melted butter and press into pan, 9 x 13-inch or smaller if you want thicker pieces.
put in refrigerator to cool while you make pudding.
save some to sprinkle on top.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
rolled oats
pecans
coconut
flour
brown sugar
salt
water
corn oil
coarse
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
place oats in a processor container and process until fine.
add pecans and process again.
add coconut and again process to blend well.
add flour, sugar, salt, water and oil.
process on "pulse" until a dough forms.
divide dough in half.
roll each half onto a 11 x 16-inch jelly roll pan.
(a straight sided glass works well as a "rolling pin.")
dough will be thin.
sprinkle with salt.
cut dough into diamonds, squares or strips before baking.
bake about 30 minutes until crisp and browned.
store airtight.
great with dips or spreads or even plain.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
thin slices ham
muenster cheese
bacon
directions:
pound chicken breast halves until 1/4-inch thick.
sprinkle with salt and pepper. top each piece of chicken with 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese.
fold chicken over ham and cheese.
wrap each bundle with two slices bacon.
place bundles side by side in a shallow baking pan.
bake in a preheated (350°) oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked and bacon is brown.
serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peanut butter
peanuts
noodles
butterscotch morsels
directions:
melt peanut butter and morsels in double boiler or heavy saucepan over low heat.
mix in noodles and peanuts until all ingredients are moistened.
form little clusters on waxed paper; allow to harden.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
zucchini
tomato
tomato paste
salt
celery
thin slices
directions:
dice zucchini and tomato into 1-inch pieces.
arrange in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
sprinkle with tomato paste; pour over 1/2 can water.
add salt and celery seed; cover with foil.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
remove cover; top with cheese slices and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes more.
serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
active yeast
water
milk
sugar
shortening
salt
flour
directions:
dissolve active dry yeast in warm water, 105° to 115°.
scald milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
cool to lukewarm.
add yeast mixture.
add flour gradually, mixing with spoon, then by hand until well blended.
place on lightly floured board.
knead until smooth and elastic.
place in greased bowl.
rub top with shortening.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
crackers
salt
zucchini
grated carrot
baking powder
pepper
pepper
clove garlic
directions:
combine together and add 2 eggs; mix well.
heat 1/4 cup oil in frying pan; drop by large spoonful into oil.
you can also shape into patties first, then fry, turning once.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
red onion
cheddar cheese
hormel bacon bits
mayonnaise
red vinegar
sugar
directions:
combine finely chopped broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon bits. mix together vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar.
pour this mixture over the salad.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fryer
onions
butter beans
potatoes
okra
corn
tomato juice
salt
red pepper
directions:
boil chicken and onions until tender meat can be removed from bones.
while chicken cools, add beans, potatoes and okra to broth and cook for 45 minutes.
remove chicken from bones; remove skin and chop chicken into small pieces.
add to beans along with corn and tomato juice.
(amount of juice depends upon the amount of chicken broth you have.)
season and simmer for at least another hour.
freezes well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground round
egg
campbell's alphabet
catsup
directions:
mix ground beef, soup and egg.
place in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
top with catsup and bake for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hamburger
onions
worcestershire sauce
salt
horseradish
ketchup
lemon juice
tomato sauce
sugar
pepper
directions:
brown hamburger and onions.
add all ingredients except tomato sauce and lemon juice.
add these just before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
eggs
butter
brown sugar
butter
flour
sugar
salt
vanilla
nuts
milk
directions:
combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, 1/4 cup butter, milk and vanilla. spoon into an ungreased 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. combine brown sugar, flour, nuts and butter.
spread over the potatoes.
bake at 350° for 35 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
water
celery
leeks
chicken bouillon granules
cheddar
milk
water
worcestershire sauce
salt
dry mustard
white pepper
directions:
bring potatoes, 1 1/2 cups water, celery, leeks and bouillon granules to a boil over high heat.
reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 30 minutes, or until potatoes are fork-tender.
remove from heat (do not drain) and mash mixture until smooth.
gently stir in cheese until melted.
stir in milk, beer, worcestershire sauce, salt, dry mustard and white pepper.
stir over low heat until hot.
makes 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornbread mix
onion
cheese
oleo
frozen broccoli
salt
eggs
directions:
mix all ingredients together and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
bake in 375° oven for 45 to 55 minutes, until brown. grated cheese may be sprinkled on top for last 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
marshmallow creme
cream cheese
directions:
bring cream cheese to room temperature. mix marshmallow creme and philadelphia cream cheese together. store in refrigerator. serve with fresh sliced apples.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen asparagus
chicken
cream of chicken soup
mayonnaise
curry powder
bread crumbs
butter
lemon juice
grated cheese
pimiento strips
directions:
cook asparagus according to package directions; arrange in greased baking dish.
place chicken on top.
combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
pour mixture over chicken; sprinkle with cheese and top with buttered bread crumbs. garnish with pimiento.
bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
salt
french mustard
celery
sugar
vinegar
oil
flour
egg
directions:
add egg to other ingredients to thicken.
blend in blender.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
milk
shortening
directions:
mix well and drop by spoonfuls on greased pan.
bake at 450° until golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sweet potatoes
orange rind
cornstarch
sugar
brown sugar
salt
orange juice
butter
directions:
cook sweet potatoes in jackets in 1/2 inch of boiling, salted water until tender, about 30 minutes.
remove skins.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sausage
barbecue sauce
brown sugar
yellow mustard
worcestershire sauce
ketchup
water
directions:
in large saucepan, cut polish sausage into 1/2-inch slices. then add remaining ingredients.
cook on medium for about 30 minutes, then simmer for 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
salt
milk
egg yolks
vanilla
butter
coconut
egg whites
sugar
shell
directions:
combine sugar, flour and salt; add milk and egg yolks and stir until smooth.
add coconut.
cook until thick.
beat the egg whites until foamy.
add sugar gradually and beat until stiff; fold in hot mixture.
pour in baked pie shell and refrigerate. top with cool whip and sprinkle with coconut.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
skinless
lemon yogurt
ground ginger
garlic powder
bread crumbs
directions:
preheat oven to 350 degrees.
dip each piece of chicken in a mixture of yogurt, ginger and garlic powder.
then coat lightly with bread crumbs.
place in a single layer in a non-stick baking pan.
bate at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender and coating is crisp.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crisco
brown sugar
flour
salt
milk
eggs
brown sugar
vanilla
flour
baking powder
flaked coconut
pecans
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
blend crisco and 1/2 cup brown sugar. add 1 cup flour and salt.
stir in milk.
pat evenly in greased pan.
bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
beat eggs, 1 cup brown sugar and vanilla until thick.
stir in remaining ingredients.
pour mixture in pan.
bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown.
cool.
frost and garnish with cherries, if desired. cut into squares.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
blackberries
vegetable oil
eggs
white cake mix
sugar
milk
black raspberry jello
blackberry juice
directions:
cook berries; strain.
reserve 1/4 cup juice for icing.
add water for right measure.
combine all ingredients except eggs. add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
pour into greased and floured bundt pan.
bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
white sugar
salt
cinnamon
baking soda
eggs
vegetable oil
vanilla
pineapple
pecans
bananas
directions:
combine dry ingredients in large bowl. add eggs and oil. stir with a spoon until moist. stir in vanilla, pineapple with juice and nuts. add bananas. pour batter in a 9 x 13 pan. bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes or until cake test done. cool, then frost with cream cheese frosting.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
buttermilk
shrimp
cucumber
bell pepper
green onion
red radishes
dill
directions:
combine all ingredients except dill weed. cover and refrigerate for 8 hours. at serving time, stir well. ladle into chilled bowls and top with a sprinkle of dill weed. makes 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
head cabbage
salt
sugar
vinegar
water
celery
stalks celery
green pepper
carrot
onion
directions:
mix cabbage and salt; let stand 1 hour.
heat sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed to boil in 1-quart saucepan.
boil and stir 1 minute.
cool to lukewarm.
drain cabbage; stir in celery, green pepper, carrots and onion.
stir vinegar mixture into cabbage mixture.
spoon into three 1-pint freeze containers.
cover and label; freeze up to 1 month.
eight hours before serving, place in refrigerator to thaw.
drain well before serving.
garnish with sliced pimiento-stuffed olives.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cracklings
lye
water
directions:
combine all ingredients and cook in a large black kettle until lye eats up grease and cracklings.
let set in pot overnight or until cold and set.
next day, cut into pieces.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
sugar
vanilla
eggs
graham cracker crust
white chocolate chips
almonds
directions:
mix cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. add eggs; mix until blended. stir in 1/2 cup white chocolate. pour into crust; sprinkle with almonds and remaining white chocolate. bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. cool. refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork sausage
eggs
salt
parmesan cheese
hash browns
cheddar cheese
crescent rolls
milk
pepper
directions:
separate rolls into 8 triangles and place on an ungreased pizza pan, points toward center.
press dough over bottom and sides to form a crust.
layer sausage and potatoes on crust.
top with cheddar cheese.
beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
pour over cheese.
top with parmesan cheese..
bake at 375 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
oil
pumpkin
flour
baking powder
cinnamon
salt
baking soda
directions:
mix well in order given.
beat at medium speed until smooth. pour into ungreased pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
frost with icing when cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
baking powder
shortening
egg
water
boiling chicken
directions:
sift first 3 ingredients together; cut in shortening.
stir water and egg together and add to flour mixture.
roll very thin. cut into squares and let rest 20 - 30 minutes.
drop into boiling broth.
cover & cook 20 minutes or until tender.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cheese
butter
flour
brown sugar
butter
salt
vanilla
egg
directions:
blend and beat all ingredients.
spoon filling into unbaked shells, filling each 3/4 full.
sprinkle on chopped pecans.
bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
cool on rack.
freezes well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beans
cream cheese
directions:
dip grease off chili.
pour chili into casserole dish, add cream cheese (cut up) and heat in microwave for 3 minutes.
stir and heat 2 minutes or until hot.
serve with chips.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chuck roast
pork shoulder
onion
garlic
water
tomatoes
tomato sauce
chili powder
salt
cumin
paprika
corn meal
directions:
stir both
meats,
onion
and
garlic in heavy saucepan over medium heat
until	meat is no longer pink.
mix in beer, then all remaining	ingredients, except corn meal.	cover and simmer until chili is reduced to 12 cups, stirring occasionally, about 3 hours. degrease chili.
stir cornmeal into chili. cover and
simmer
30 minutes.

bacon
catsup
onion

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

2
to

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
macaroni
cucumber
tomatoes
mayo
salt
eggs
directions:
*the amount of each item depends on your taste and liking.<|endofrecipe|>

wonderful!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

's cheese

10 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

white sugar

directions:
