combine together and pour in pie shell.
freeze for three hours and dig in!!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
baking powder
salt
eggs
vegetable oil
water
vanilla
cream of tartar
sugar
directions:
combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in small mixing bowl.
make a well in center; add egg yolks, oil, water and vanilla.
beat at high speed of electric mixer 5 minutes or until satin smooth.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
margarine
cream of mushroom soup
processed cheese
dry mustard
tuna
macaroni
peas
potato chips
directions:
in saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
blend in soup, cheese and seasoning.
heat until cheese melts.
combine with tuna, macaroni and peas.
pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
crumble potato chips on top.
bake in moderate oven until nicely browned and bubbling.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
brown sugar
butter
salt
cinnamon
water
cornstarch
vanilla
sugar
rhubarb
directions:
mix flour, brown sugar, oatmeal, butter, cinnamon and salt together.
put into a 10 x 13-inch pan, reserving a few crumbs for topping.
grease pan only if you desire.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hash brown potatoes
margarine
cream of chicken soup
sour cream
onion
cheese
directions:
heat margarine, add soup slowly.
blend sour cream and onion. mix with potatoes and top with grated cheese.
bake 45 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bacon
onion
campbell's pork
ketchup
brown sugar
worcestershire sauce
directions:
cook bacon until almost crisp; drain.
saute onion in bacon drippings until soft; drain.
crumble bacon and combine with rest of ingredients.
mix well by hand.
bake in 2-quart casserole in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
stir occasionally.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hot sausage
ground beef
velveeta cheese
basil
oregano
cocktail size rye bread
directions:
brown meat and drain.
mix in cheese and spices until cheese is melted.
spoon meat mixture on bread and broil just until meat browns.
can be frozen before baking.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
raisins
pecans
lemon zest
lemon juice
salt
sugar
sour cream
mayonnaise
directions:
pre-soak raisins in enough water to cover for about 1 hour, drain well. mix sour cream and mayonnaise in small bowl, set aside. combine remaining ingredients, stirring to blend. pour sour cream and mayonnaise mixture over the carrot/raisin mixture. toss well and serve. makes 4-5 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pumpkin seeds
water
cooking oil
salt
directions:
wash seeds.
steam seeds (colander inside a pot).
put water into the bottom of the colander or strainer.
cook covered at a fairly high heat about 30 minutes; add more water if needed.
dump seeds on paper towel and pat dry.
spread on cookie sheet.
pour a little oil (just enough to make seeds shiny when you stir them around).
sprinkle with salt.
bake at 300° for about 1/2 hour. eat for snack.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
peaches
margarine
nuts
directions:
layer all ingredients in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with peaches first (undrained), dry cake mix second, melted margarine third and chopped nuts or flaked coconut fourth.
bake 55 or 60 minutes in a 325° oven or until golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
buttermilk
vegetable oil
sugar
eggs
flour
baking soda
salt
directions:
mix
together
raisin
bran, buttermilk, oil, sugar and eggs. mix
together flour, soda and salt, then add to buttermilk mixture.
refrigerate
for	6 hours.
mixture keeps for 6 weeks in refrigerator.
bake in lined muffin tins at 375° for 15 minutes. makes 5 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
salt
pepper
vinegar
onion
celery
mayonnaise
mustard
directions:
boil, peel and dice potatoes.
sprinkle with salt and pepper. add vinegar, onion and celery.
mix mayonnaise and mustard.
pour over potatoes and mix.
chill 2 hours.
serve cold.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ladyfingers
cream cheese
sugar
comstock pie filling
directions:
combine cream cheese, sugar and cool whip.
pour into pie plate lined with ladyfingers.
refrigerate.
when set, pour cherries (or blueberries) on pie.
makes 1 pie.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
crisco
sugar
eggs
flour
salt
baking powder
milk
vanilla
directions:
cream together the butter or margarine, crisco, sugar and eggs (add eggs 1 at a time).
sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
add flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternately with milk and vanilla, beginning and ending with flour.
mix well with hand mixer.
bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
cool in pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pie shell
tomatoes
cheddar cheese
mayonnaise
basil
chives
directions:
slice tomatoes in pie shell.
add cheese.
seal with mayonnaise.
sprinkle basil and chives over this.
bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
biscuit
grated cheese
butter
directions:
preheat oven to 400°.
grease cookie sheet.
split each biscuit in half.
place one half from each biscuit on cookie sheet.
pat it out so it is twice as big.
place 1 tablespoon of cheese on each biscuit on the cookie sheet.
stretch the remaining biscuit halves to fit over each of the cheese topped biscuit halves.
place one on top of the other.
with a fork, lightly press down with the tines around all the edges.
melt butter with a pastry brush.
spread butter over biscuits so they are covered completely.
bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
cocoa
milk
egg yolks
butter
directions:
boil first 4 ingredients, stirring constantly.
when thick, take 2 tablespoons of mixture and mix with egg yolks.
then add the egg mixture back into the boiled mixture; boil until thick. take off heat and add butter.
pour into baked pie crust.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
dream whip
o
cheese
pineapple
directions:
mix dream whip.
whip in dry granular jell-o (do not add water).
fold in pineapple and cottage cheese.
refrigerate for 4 hours.
be creative.
you may also use nuts, coconut, cherries, mandarin oranges or cubed peaches.
my favorite is orange jell-o, pineapple, mandarin oranges and coconut.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brownie mix
nuts
dream whip
coffee
brown sugar
directions:
mix brownies by box directions.
use the cake version rather than the chewy version.
stir in nuts.
bake in 2 greased 8 or 9-inch cake pans at 350°.
watch carefully.
since layers are thin, they cook faster than box directions.
cool completely before frosting.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
chocolate
salt
white syrup
butter
vanilla
directions:
mix first 5 ingredients in large saucepan; stir continually while cooking. cook to 245° or hard ball stage when tested in water. take from heat and add butter and vanilla. pour slowly over a dishpan full of popped corn plus lots of nutmeats. be very careful while stirring as this is very hot chocolate and could burn. spread out on several buttered cookie sheets and let cool. happy eating.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
powdered sugar
graham crackers
cinnamon
peanut butter
vanilla
chocolate chips
cake paraffin
directions:
mix first six ingredients.
roll into balls.
in a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
dip balls into chocolate and then put on wax paper.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
all-purpose
sugar
soda
salt
cinnamon
eggs
vegetable oil
vanilla
pineapple
pecans
bananas
cream cheese
directions:
combine the flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
(do not beat with mixer.)
stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
spoon batter in greased and floured 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
graham cracker crumbs
sugar
butter
confectioners sugar
eggs
bananas
lemon juice
pineapple
pecans
cherries
directions:
mix graham cracker crumbs with sugar and melted butter (1 stick).
place in 13 x 9-inch pan to form crust.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vanilla wafer crumbs
margarine
nutrasweet spoonful
unflavored gelatin
milk
cream cheese
cream cheese
lemon juice
lemon rind
vanilla
nutrasweet spoonful
blueberries
raspberries
directions:
mix crumbs, margarine and 3 tablespoons of nutrasweet spoonful in a medium bowl.
pat evenly on bottom of jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peach pie filling
mandarin oranges
pineapple tidbits
bananas
pecans
directions:
mix all ingredients and chill 1 hour before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apples
sugar
flour
salt
baking powder
soda
cinnamon
oil
eggs
nuts
directions:
mix the dry ingredients, then oil.
add the beaten eggs.
add chopped apples last.
bake at 350° for 1 hour.
top with a thin glaze or whipped topping.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cheddar cheese
onion
corn tortillas
butter
flour
chicken broth
sour cream
green chilies
directions:
combine 2 cups grated cheese and onion and roll inside tortillas.
place in 9 x 13 pan.
in saucepan, blend butter and flour; add chicken broth and stir until thickened.
stir in sour cream, green chilies and 1 cup grated cheese.
pour over enchiladas and sprinkle with remaining cup of cheese.
bake at 425 degrees for 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
butter
cocoa
milk
quick-cooking
nuts
vanilla
directions:
mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
bring to boil quickly.
reduce heat to medium and boil 3 or 4 minutes.
remove from heat; stir in rolled oats, nuts and vanilla.
drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
let stand until hardened.
store in refrigerator.
makes 3 dozen cookies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pretzels
margarine
sugar
pineapple
sugar
cream cheese
directions:
melt margarine and mix with broken pretzels and 1/2 cup of sugar.
cook over low heat for 7 minutes.
pour into baking dish and cool, then break into small pieces.
set aside.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cabbage
onions
bell peppers
carrots
white vinegar
sugar
salt
black pepper
cayenne pepper
mustard
peppers
directions:
mix all ingredients in pan; bring to boil.
reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes.
put in sterilized jars and seal.
makes approximately 9 pints.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
flour
cream
lemon juice
lemon zest
parsley
salt
directions:
just mix in blender or shaker and serve over your favorite fish.
makes 4 to 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
asparagus
salt
flour
water
cracker crumbs
egg
milk
butter
eggs
directions:
combine milk, flour, butter or butter substitute and salt. cook over hot water until thick and smooth.
add canned asparagus and chopped eggs.
mix quickly and lightly in cracker crumbs.
dip in egg which has been diluted with water.
roll in cracker crumbs. fry in deep fat at 390° until browned.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onions
green onions
bell pepper
celery
ro-tel
tomato paste
olive oil
garlic
worcestershire
lemons
flour
salt
water
mushroom soup
directions:
wash venison.
season and fry in bacon drippings and remove. make roux with olive oil and flour.
add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
add all seasonings except garlic.
simmer for 1 hour.
add venison to soup and seasoning.
simmer 30 minutes.
add water and garlic.
cook 4 hours.
serve over rice.
serves approximately 16.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onion
egg noodles
cream of mushroom soup
milk
cheddar cheese
potato chips
directions:
brown hamburger and onion.
drain.
cook noodles and drain. blend soup and milk.
heat together.
grate cheese.
crush potato chips.
mix all ingredients together.
place in ungreased, uncovered casserole dish.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
pecans
brown sugar
butter
instant vanilla pudding
milk
marshmallows
bananas
directions:
combine the first 4 ingredients; spread out on cookie sheet. bake for 20 minutes at 350°; stir every 5 minutes with fork. cool.
mix pudding and milk; stir in rest of the ingredients.
top with the first mixture and chill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beans
sour cream
taco seasoning
tomato
black olives
avocado
mayonnaise
cheddar cheese
scallions
directions:
use a quiche size dish.
layer ingredients from bottom to top as follows:<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
eggs
butter
cubed rhubarb
nutmeg
directions:
combine ingredients.
place in a pie crust with a top.
bake at 425° for 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
vanilla pudding
cherry pie filling
pineapple
coconut
directions:
bake cake according to directions on box.
let
cake cool, then crumble.
fix vanilla pudding according to directions on box. in a separate bowl combine cherries, coconut and pineapple.
in a large bowl layer 1/2 cake, then 1/2 pudding and 1/2 fruit mixture. top with cool whip.
repeat process again, topping with cool whip.
refrigerate until serving time.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white beans
lean salt
water
onion
oil
directions:
wash white beans and soak overnight.
use lean salt meat; wash and cut only (do not boil).
add water to cover about three inches over beans and meat in pot.
boil together and remove bubbles that form over top of beans as they begin to boil until there are none left.
add seasonings (onion and garlic only) and oil.
cook until beans are tender.
the length of time depends on if they are new crop beans or if they are old.
new crop beans are in september and they remain tender until december.
beans can be bought in september and frozen for later use.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
bacon
onion
cheddar cheese
mayonnaise
sugar
vinegar
directions:
fry bacon; drain and chop.
chop other ingredients.
mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
combine all.
use day prepared.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oleo
sugar
flour
milk
peaches
directions:
in big pudding pan, melt oleo.
in another pan or bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk.
mix well and pour over melted oleo and then pour over all the peaches.
bake at 350° until done.
the crust will come to top and brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
walnuts
baking soda
baking powder
salt
mace
egg
milk
butter
pineapple
directions:
in a large bowl, mix first 7 dry ingredients well.
in a small bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
stir into dry ingredients until just moist.
pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
flour
egg
salt
directions:
mix all ingredients.
dip sliced onions in mixture.
fry in hot grease until brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apple juice
salt
cornstarch
cinnamon
nutmeg
margarine
apples
ready
directions:
cook apple juice, cornstarch and spices until thick; add salt and stir.
add sliced apples to mixture and mix well.
pour into pie shell and top with second shell.
prick holes in shell and place margarine on top.
bake at 400° until golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
basmati rice
butter
cinnamon
bay leaves
cardamon
cloves
salt
raisins
pistachios
almonds
directions:
wash the rice and set aside to drain.
heat the butter in a nonstick pan.
add cinnamon stick, cardamon pods, bay leaves and cloves and stir for 1 1/2 minutes.
add salt and water (8 cups) to rice, then bring to boil, stirring it a couple of times.
reduce heat to low.
add raisins, almonds and pistachios.
cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
serve piping hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
olive oil
sweet red pepper
sweet green pepper
sweet yellow pepper
tomato
black olives
garlic
parmesan cheese
parsley
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 1 teaspoon olive oil.
halve, core and seed peppers.
cut each half into 3 lengthwise wedges. combine tomato, olives, garlic, 2 tablespoons parmesan cheese and parsley in a small bowl.
divide mixture among pepper wedges.
place pepper wedges in prepared baking dish.
drizzle with remaining 2 teaspoons olive oil.
bake peppers in preheated oven until tender, about 30 minutes. sprinkle with remaining (1 tablespoon) parmesan cheese.
bake additional 5 minutes.
serve immediately or at room temperature. makes six servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
all-purpose
salt
pepper
eggs
vegetable oil
water
mushrooms
italian seasoned breadcrumbs
vegetable oil
tartar sauce
directions:
combine flour, salt and pepper in a small bowl; set aside. combine eggs, 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and water; mix well.
clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
dredge mushrooms in flour mixture; dip in egg mixture.
roll in breadcrumbs.
chill at least 1 1/2 hours.
deep fry mushrooms in hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
drain on paper towels.
serve mushrooms with tartar sauce.
yields 32 appetizers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomato catsup
worcestershire sauce
red pepper
chili powder
tarragon vinegar
salt pork liquor
sugar
garlic
onion
directions:
combine all ingredients.
bring to a boil on high.
remove pieces of garlic.
yields about 1 quart.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
active dry yeast
water
cheese
sugar
onion
butter
dill
salt
baking soda
salt
egg
all-purpose flour
directions:
one cup of dates, cut in small pieces.
put 1 teaspoon of baking soda on the dates.
then pour 3/4 cup of boiling water over them.
let stand until cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beef flank
cornstarch
cold water
vegetable oil
onion
pineapple
water
sugar
white vinegar
instant chicken
soy sauce
green pepper
tomatoes
directions:
trim excess fat from beef; cut beef with grain into 2-inch strips.
cut strips across grain into 1/8-inch slices.
mix cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water.
heat oil in 12-inch skillet or wok over medium-high heat until hot.
add beef and onion; cook and stir until beef is brown, about 3 minutes.
stir in pineapple, 1/2 cup water, the sugar, vinegar, instant bouillon and soy sauce. heat to boiling.
stir in cornstarch mixture.
cook and stir 1 minute. stir in green pepper and tomatoes; cook and stir 1 minute. serve with hot, cooked rice.
makes 5 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
green pepper
oleo
frankfurters
barbecue beans
bean
whole kernel corn
directions:
in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet, cook onion and green pepper in the oleo.
cut ten 1-inch pieces of frankfurters; set aside. thickly slice remaining franks; add to skillet.
stir in the beans, soup, corn and reserved liquid.
heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
roll each biscuit to a 3-inch circle; spread with mustard.
place a reserved frank in the center.
wrap dough around frank; seal and make a 1/2-inch slit in the top.
arrange biscuits, seam sides down; bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground chuck
mushroom soup
bread crumbs
egg
onion
black pepper
directions:
mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients. set aside the rest of the soup. shape into 6 patties. place in shallow baking dish. bake at 350° for 30 minutes. spoon off fat. mix the rest of soup with 1/3 cup water and pour over meat. bake 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hot sausage
cheddar cheese
biscuit mix
directions:
let cheese and sausage sit to room temperature.
mix all ingredients together and form into marble-sized balls.
place on cookie sheet and freeze.
when solid, transfer to freezer bags. when needed, remove amount desired and bake at 325° until golden brown, about 35 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sour cream
sugar
molasses
flour
salt
soda
ginger
cinnamon
boiling water
directions:
mix together eggs, sour cream, sugar and molasses.
add flour, salt, soda, ginger and cinnamon.
mix.
add boiling water; mix.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg whites
sugar
light corn syrup
water
salt
cream of tartar
vanilla
directions:
combine all but vanilla in top of double boiler and beat over boiling water until it stands in peaks.
add vanilla and continue beating until thick enough to spread.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
nilla wafers
cream cheese
sugar
vanilla
eggs
cherry pie filling
directions:
place 1 wafer in each foil-lined muffin pan.
combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
beat well and add eggs.
mix well. fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
let cool.
chill.
top with pie filling.
makes 1 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cold baked potatoes
amount of cooking oil
parsley
directions:
slice cold baked potatoes into thick slices.
pour a small amount of cooking oil onto cookie sheet.
place potato slices in oil, turning so potato slices are completely coated with oil. sprinkle with parsley flakes, garlic powder or garlic salt and a little oregano.
turn slices and sprinkle with same.
bake in hot oven until slightly brown and piping hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
armadillo
rock
salt
directions:
place one armadillo and one large rock about the size of a soft ball.
add salt, pepper, etc.
boil fast for two weeks. throw armadillo away and eat rock.
use very large pot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
noodles
heavy cream
parmesan cheese
butter
salt
directions:
in small saucepan, melt butter with the cream over low heat to just hot enough to melt the cheese.
during this time, cook the pasta.
drain pasta and empty into a warm bowl.
pour cream mixture over noodles, gradually toss in the cheese and mix. lightly salt to taste and season generously with pepper.
serve with additional cheese on the side.
butter bottom of warm glass bowl to serve pasta.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
powdered sugar
flour
baking powder
baking soda
cinnamon
nutmeg
salt
eggs
sugar
cooked apples
pecans
snack raisins
directions:
preheat oven at 375°.
grease a 15 x 10 inch jelly roll pan. line with wax paper, grease and flour paper; sprinkle towel with powdered sugar.
combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt in small bowl.
beat eggs and sugar in large bowl until thick; beat in fruit.
stir in flour mixture; spread evenly into prepared pan.
sprinkle with nuts if desired.
bake 10 to 15 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
immediately loosen and turn cake onto prepared towel; carefully peel paper off, roll up cake and towel together, start with narrow end, cool on wire rack.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apples
sugar
pineapple
directions:
combine apples, pears and sugar.
cook in sauce pan over medium heat about 1 hour or until mixture looks like honey.
then add crushed pineapple and cook 10 more minutes.
very good on a hot buttermilk biscuit.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vegetable combination
cream of mushroom soup
swiss cheese
sour cream
pepper
pimento
onions
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
in a large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can onions.
pour into shallow 1-quart casserole.
bake, covered, for 30 minutes (until vegetables are done).
sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in diagonal rows across the top.
bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are brown.
makes 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
milk
onion
cream-style horseradish
salt
pepper
crabmeat
almonds
directions:
blend all ingredients, except almonds.
put in baking dish. sprinkle with almonds.
bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
serve with crackers or rye chips.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peach halves
peach juice
vinegar
cinnamon
sugar
cloves
directions:
insert whole cloves into peach halves. mix remaining ingredients; simmer 3 minutes. pour over peaches and let set.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onions
shortening
tomatoes
chili peppers
salt
pepper
american cheese
directions:
saute onions until transparent. add the rest of the ingredients except cheese to the onions.
cook until blended.
add cheese. cook until well blended. serve in a chafing dish with fritos or tortilla chips. great dip!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen lima beans
celery soup
onion
green pepper
butter
cheddar cheese
bread crumbs
directions:
cook the beans (not too much, since they cook more in baking). drain.

press broccoli between paper towels to remove excess moisture. combine cornbread mix, eggs, onion, cheese, butter and seasonings.
stir well.
add to broccoli and mix gently (batter will be thick).
pour into greased 8-inch baking pan.
bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
roast
onion
mushroom soup
potatoes
directions:
use deep, long pan.
line with foil.
place roast in bottom. cover with onion slices and mushrooms.
pour soup over roast.
add vegetables.
cook at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
cooking oil
milk
directions:
place flour in medium mixing bowl.
in small bowl, mix oil and water.
add to flour all at once.
stir until all the flour is wet.
turn out on lightly floured surface.
knead 10 times.
roll out until dough is about as thick as your first finger is.
cut with biscuit cutter or 2-inch glass.
leftover dough may be gathered and rekneaded about 5 times.
flatten and cut as before. bake in 450° oven on ungreased baking sheet until brown.
serve hot!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
chocolate
chocolate
crunchy peanut butter
grape-nuts
directions:
mix first 2 ingredients in a large bowl until well blended. sprinkle pudding mix over ice cream/cool whip mixture and blend. add peanut butter and cereal to mixture.
mix together.
spray 9-inch pan with pam.
fold mixture into pan.
cover and freeze.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
onion
salt
rice
water
celery
pepper
directions:
in a large kettle, combine chicken, water, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
cook until chicken is tender, about 1 1/2 hours. remove chicken from broth and pick meat from bone.
return to broth with rice.
heat thoroughly.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork chops
water
packet
chicken
directions:
brown pork chops in hot skillet just until white.
add rice-a-roni in a 9 x 13-inch dish mixed with 2 cups water and packet of seasoning.
place pork chops on top.
bake 30 minutes in a 300° oven.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
milk
sausage
shredded cheese
dry mustard
salt
directions:
brown meat and drain. cover bottom of an 8 x 11-inch dish with toast pieces. scatter sausage or bacon over toast, then cheese. beat eggs.
mix milk, mustard and salt.
add eggs and pour over top of cheese.
refrigerate overnight.
bake at 350° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lemon flavored ice tea
apple pie spice
lemonade mix with equal
directions:
combine all the ingredients.
mix well.
store in an airtight container.
makes 48 servings; one serving equals 3 calories.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
salt
directions:
melt butter in 10-inch skillet over low heat. add cereal; cook and stir until well coated and hot, 2 to 3 minutes.
sprinkle with salt. serve warm or cold.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
brown sugar
sugar
eggs
water
flour
baking powder
soda
salt
oats
gumdrops
directions:
cream shortening, sugars, eggs and water.
sift the flour, baking powder, soda and salt, and then add into mixture.
finally, add in oats and gumdrops.
shape into balls.
roll in coconut. bake at 350° until lightly browned.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

philadelphia cream cheese
water
mayonnaise
onion
celery
gelatine
water
shrimp
directions:

melt in cheese. beat until smooth.
dissolve package of gelatine in water and add to soup.
add mayonnaise.
fold in onion, celery and shrimp.
pour into mold greased with crisco.
refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red beans
tomatoes
mushrooms
onion
sausage
italian sausage
tomato juice
directions:
cook italian sausage.
cut into bite-size pieces.
put everything into a pot and simmer for about 2 hours.
serve over rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg
sugar
cold milk
vanilla
directions:
blend in blender on medium speed.
pour in glass. sprinkle with nutmeg.
makes 1 serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
double-acting baking powder
salt
butter
sugar
egg
almond extract
maraschino cherries
coconut
pecans
directions:
sift flour, baking powder and salt.
cream butter and sugar. add egg and almond extract and beat well.
blend in the dry ingredients gradually.
mix thoroughly.
add cherries, coconut and pecans.
mix well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
raisins
currants
candied citron
pineapple
cherries
baking powder
cinnamon
allspice
sugar
molasses
almonds
pecans
flour
nutmeg
butter
brandy
eggs
milk
directions:
note:
candied citron, pineapple and cherries can be substituted with 1 cup mixed candied fruits.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
onions
green chilies
cheddar cheese
potatoes
pepper
corn tortillas
oil
sour cream
salsa
directions:
in bowl mix shredded roast beef or chicken; add onions, green chilies, cheddar cheese, small diced cooked potatoes and pepper. mix together.
warm corn tortillas; fill with chicken/beef and roll tightly and small.
fry in skillet with hot oil.
eat with sour cream, salsa and guacamole.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
green beans
rice
cream of mushroom soup
mayonnaise
water chestnuts
mushrooms
directions:
combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
mix well.
place in a greased casserole.
bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
serves 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornmeal
baking powder
milk
onion
flour
salt
egg
directions:
combine dry ingredients.
add milk, egg and onion; mix well. drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into deep, hot oil.
fry only a few minutes, or until golden brown on both sides.
may be served with tomato gravy and applesauce.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crisco
brown sugar
sugar
vanilla
water
eggs
flour
soda
salt
candies
directions:
blend crisco and sugars.
beat in vanilla, water, and egg. sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar and egg mixture. mix well. stir in m & m's.	drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown. yield: 6 dozen cookies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
zucchini
butter
carrots
onion
cubes
cream of chicken soup
sour cream
directions:
cook zucchini in boiling salt water until just tender.
drain. in saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
add carrots and onion. saute until tender.
remove from heat.
stir in 1/2 cup stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
gently stir in zucchini.
spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
melt 2 tablespoons butter.
add remaining stuffing cubes and toss gently.
sprinkle over casserole.
bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cheddar cheese
butter
flour
salt
cayenne pepper
directions:
mix cheese and butter and
mix in mixer.
add remaining ingredients.
mix well and put on
cookie sheet.
use star shape cookie press. bake at 350° for 12 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
oil
salt
water
directions:
for double crust:
sift flour; measure.
add salt.
measure oil.
add water; stir.
pour into flour; mix with fork.
roll between wax paper.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green beans
cream of mushroom soup
milk
onions
directions:
thaw and drain beans.
place in casserole.
mix soup with milk.
pour over beans.
mix half of onions in.
place in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
remove from oven and place remaining onions on top.
bake until beans are tender.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen peas
celery
onion
water chestnuts
pimentos
mushrooms
bread crumbs
margarine
directions:
mix first 6 ingredients with peas.
put in a baking dish. brown bread crumbs in margarine and sprinkle on top.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
spinach
bread crumbs
parmesan cheese
oregano
basil
garlic
directions:
boil spinach and cook 1 minute.
place spinach in strainer and press out all excess water. when spinach is strained, add bread crumbs, grated parmesan cheese and seasonings.
mix well.
roll into balls (like meat balls) and fry in oil until brown. add tomato sauce and you have a great substitute for regular meat balls.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onion
tomato soup
green beans
potatoes
egg
directions:
brown ground beef and onion.
add salt and pepper.
pour into greased casserole dish.
add can of condensed tomato soup.
blend well.
spread green beans on top.
make 6 servings instant mashed potatoes.
spoon in mounds over top of casserole.
brush top of mashed potatoes with 1 whipped egg.
bake 30 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
eggs
flour
nutmeg
brown sugar
cinnamon
sugar
sour cream
baking powder
iodized salt
walnuts
directions:
grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
in mixer bowl, combine butter and sugar.
beat until fluffy.
add eggs and sour cream and beat until well blended.
in separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt, stirring to mix well.
slowly add to batter, beating on slowest speed.
pour into prepared pan.
combine brown sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
mix well.
sprinkle evenly over batter.
cover and refrigerate overnight.
next morning uncover. bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean and cake pulls away from pan.
makes 12 servings. if cake is baked without chilling, it may be done in 30 minutes in 350° oven.
keep an eye on it.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
graham cracker pie crusts
cream cheese
milk
confectioners sugar
crunchy peanut butter
cartons
directions:
mix cream cheese and milk well.
add other ingredients.
pour into pie shells.
this recipe freezes.
makes 3 pies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
nonfat yogurt
banana
directions:
drain pineapple.
cube banana.
blend in blender 45 to 60 seconds or until smooth.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
sugar
brown sugar
eggs
vanilla
flour
rolled oats
baking powder
baking soda
salt
butterscotch chips
directions:
bake at 350°f for approx. 10 min.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fruit
honey
mustard
vinegar
directions:
mix all ingredients in a 2-cup microwavable measure. microwave uncovered on high for about 2 minutes or until hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
syrup
condensed milk
vanilla
corn
brown sugar
directions:
mix together butter, brown sugar, syrup, condensed milk and vanilla.
cook on stove until well blended.
add popped corn.
mix well.
(i doubled the amount of popped corn when i made this.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork roast
salt
liquid smoke
directions:
stick holes into roast with large fork.
sprinkle and rub into the meat the salt and liquid smoke.
more salt and smoke may be used according to taste.
wrap roast in heavy foil and cook in 325° oven for 5 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cabbage

hot water
salt
pepper
directions:
clean and shred cabbage in a large skillet.
heat the bacon grease.
add half of the cabbage, salt and pepper.
add rest of cabbage, salt and pepper (a little).
pour the hot water over and simmer on medium until done and water is gone.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

ketchup
directions:
brown 1 lb. ground meat in skillet.
drain all grease from pan.
add bbq sauce, simmer for a few minutes, stirring well.
add ketchup, stir and simmer again then soup (no water).
simmer on low heat 15 - 20 minutes. serve on hamburger buns.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg whites
cream of tartar
sugar
egg yolks
sugar
lemon rind
lemon juice
heavy cream
directions:
meringue shell:
beat egg whites with cream of tartar in medium bowl until foamy.
beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until meringue forms, still glossy peaks.
lightly butter a 9 inch pie plate.
spoon meringue over bottom and side
to form a shell. bake in a slow oven at 275 degrees for 1 hour.
turn oven off and allow meringue to cool in the oven.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
avocados
lemon juice
clove garlic
green onion
tomato
corn chips
directions:
you will need a garlic press.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cranberries
sugar
apples
oranges
pineapple
strawberry jello
water
directions:
grind oranges and apples and mix with pineapple and add sugar. mix jello with 2 cups hot water and add to mixture.
let set in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
zucchini
sugar
egg
flour
carnation milk
butter
vanilla
nutmeg
pie shell
directions:
peel, cut out seeds and make one cup cooked zucchini.
put in blender and add sugar, egg, flour, milk, butter and vanilla. sprinkle nutmeg on top.

bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 300° for 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

ginger
directions:

place chicken pieces in single layer in shallow baking pan (12 to 15 pieces). pour marinade over chicken.
marinate 4 to 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
turn once and baste with sauce.
serve sauce over rice.
serves 6 to 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter

eggs
vanilla
salt
pecans

directions:
cream together butter and brown sugar. add eggs; beat until fluffy. add vanilla, salt and pecans. sift together baking soda and flour. add to mixture. shape with hands into 3 to 4 rolls. do this in a piece of floured plastic wrap or aluminum foil which can be wrapped around roll. store in the refrigerator until ready to slice and bake. bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet until lightly brown, about 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
onions
cream of mushroom soup
celery

rice
directions:

saute celery and onions in margarine until tender.

bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brown sugar
lemon juice
curry powder
black pepper
salt
paprika
worcestershire sauce
salad oil
directions:
mix together and baste chicken while cooking.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peaches
peach jello
sugar
yellow cake
butter
water
directions:
slice peaches and put in pan.
mix dry jello and sugar together and sprinkle over peaches.
take dry cake mix over that. pour butter over cake mix.
pour water over all.
cook 45 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion powder
carrots
directions:
mix softened cream cheese, mayo and seasonings together, then let stand.
spread crescent rolls in cookie sheet, jelly roll size pan.

let cool.
spread cream cheese mixture on crust.

cover with wax paper and refrigerate until ready to serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
cheese

onion salt
black beans
flour tortillas
directions:
beat cheeses, sour cream and onion salt in small mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
place beans in food processor or blender container; process until smooth.
spread thin layer of beans onto each tortilla; spread cheese mixture over beans.
roll tortillas up tightly.
chill 30 minutes.
cut into 1/2-inch slices.
serve with salsa.
makes 12 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen lemonade
orange juice
pineapple juice
lemon juice
cranberry juice
cold water
cold ginger ale
directions:
pour juices into punch bowl. stir in water and ginger ale. makes 20 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh peaches
sugar
shasta creme soda
condensed milk
almond extract
vanilla
milk
directions:
put peaches in blender.
add sugar.
let sit at least 30 minutes.
add remaining ingredients.
use rock salt and ice as you would with any homemade ice cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oysters
butter
flour

directions:
chop and scald oysters in their liquid.
blend butter and flour and add slowly to cream heated in double-boiler.
stir until this is thickened and smooth, then add oysters and their juices.
just before serving soup, stir in the whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
pecans
margarine
cream cheese
confectioners sugar
vanilla instant pudding
milk
directions:
mix floured pecans.
melt butter and pour over flour and pecans mixture.
mix well and press into bottom of large dish. bake at 350° until brown.
cool.
blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup cool whip.
spread over cooled crust.
mix pudding and milk.
spread over cream cheese layer. put cool whip on top of strawberry.
decorate with strawberries, if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cucumbers
carrots
artichokes
onion
boston lettuce
chives
mint
chicken broth
laurel leaf
directions:
cut 2 carrots and 2 turnips into bite size pieces.
make 4 cylinders by cutting the cucumber in half, emptying the pulp and slicing off the ends.
cook turnips, carrots and cucumber cylinders until tender.
cook asparagus tips separately (also until tender).
save asparagus stalks for herb sauce (below).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground meat
tomato sauce
taco seasoning mix
cream cheese
taco cheese
taco chips
directions:
brown ground meat and drain.
add 2 cans tomato sauce.
add 1 package taco seasoning mix.
spread 1 package cream cheese in 8-inch pie pan.
put meat mixture on top.
sprinkle with taco cheese and heat.
serve with chips or crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
water
raisins
shortening
sugar
eggs
vanilla
flour
baking powder
soda
salt
cinnamon
nutmeg
nuts
directions:
combine raisins and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil. cook for 3 minutes.
remove from heat and let cool (do not drain). in mixing bowl, cream shortening.
gradually add sugar and eggs and vanilla.
combine dry ingredients.
gradually add to cream mixture and blend thoroughly.
stir in nuts and raisins.
drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on baking sheet.
bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
milk
eggs
water
beef
directions:
have milk, eggs and water at room temperature.
preheat oven to 400°.
mix
flour and salt in a bowl.
pour into a well in the center of the flour mix the milk.
stir. beat eggs until fluffy. beat into the batter. add water and beat well until large bubbles appear.
pour batter into a 9 x 12-inch hot ovenproof baking dish with beef drippings or butter melted in it.
bake for 20 minutes. reduce heat to 350° and bake about 10 minutes more.
cut into squares and serve immediately.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yeast
water
flour
salt
sugar
shortening
directions:
dissolve yeast in water.
sift dry ingredients.
stir yeast mixture into dry.
add shortening.
knead on floured board until smooth.
roll out 1/2-inch.
cut into biscuits; let rise 1 hour. bake in hot oven until brown.
makes 8 buns.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
garlic
olive oil
tomato puree
water
salt
pepper
oregano
sugar
lasagna
beef
parsley
ricotta cheese
parmesan cheese
mozzarella cheese
directions:
saute garlic in tablespoon of olive oil (do not brown garlic). add tomato puree, water, salt, pepper, oregano and sugar.
bring to a boil.
lower heat and simmer for 2 hours.
brown chopped beef; add parsley, season to taste and add 2 tablespoons grated parmesan cheese.
simmer until all chopped beef is cooked through. set aside.
using a 6-quart kettle, boil water (with 1 tablespoon salt added).
when a rolling boil starts, add lasagna.
cook according to directions on package, drain and blanch with cold water.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white cornmeal
milk
onion
egg
directions:
combine ingredients; mix well.
heat vegetable oil (approximately 2-inches deep) to 375°.
drop mixture by rounded tablespoonful into hot vegetable oil.
fry a few at a time, until golden brown.
drain on paper towels.
makes about 2 dozen.
they are delicious.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
green pepper
margarine
condensed cream
mushrooms
pimentos
basil
noodles
chicken
cottage cheese
cheddar cheese
parmesan cheese
bread crumbs
directions:
in a skillet, saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
remove from heat.
stir in soup, mushrooms, pimientos and basil; set aside.
in large bowl combine noodles, chicken and cheese.
add mushroom sauce and mix well.
transfer to a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
sprinkle with crumbs.
bake 15 minutes longer. yield:
12 to 15 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
soda
salt
sugar
shortening
sour cream
directions:
sift together dry ingredients.
cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
add sour cream; mix to form a soft dough.
turn out on well floured surface and knead gently for about 20 seconds.
roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness.
cut with biscuit cutter dipped in flour and place on ungreased baking sheet.
bake at 450 degrees for approximately 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shell
pumpkin
milk
ginger
egg
salt
nutmeg
cinnamon
directions:
in large bowl, add ingredients and mix well.
bake at 375° for 1 hour.
cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
margarine
sugar
baking powder
eggs
sesame seed
directions:
mix margarine and sugar.
add eggs and stir well.
add flour and baking powder and mix well.
chill until dough is not sticky. roll out to a long shape into seeds.
cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
unsweetened chocolate
sugar
eggs
flour
vanilla extract
salt
pecans
directions:
in saucepan, melt butter and chocolate, stirring constantly. remove from heat. stir in sugar. let cool slightly. add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well. add flour, vanilla and salt. stir well. then add nuts and stir. pour in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breast
soy sauce
pineapple
bell pepper
brown sugar substitute
directions:
marinate chicken in soy sauce.
place chicken in baking dish. sprinkle with brown sugar substitute.
pour remaining soy sauce over chicken.
bake uncovered for 1/2 hour at 350°.
uncover and add bell pepper and pineapple.
bake 1/2 hour longer.
serves 1.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crust
sweet chocolate
butter
sweet condensed milk
flour
vanilla
salt
eggs
flaked coconut
pecans
directions:
melt the chocolate and 1/4 cup butter.
add the condensed milk, flour, vanilla, salt and the beaten eggs.
mix well.
add the coconut (reserve small amount for top) and pecans.
bake until firm to touch at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white potatoes
onions
salt
milk
parsley
black pepper
directions:
put potatoes and onions in kettle with salt and cover with cold water (about 4 cups).
bring to boiling point.
cover and cook gently for 20 minutes.
transfer to a blender and puree vegetables or mash to a pulp in the water.
add milk and season to taste with salt and plenty of pepper.
garnish with chopped parsley.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mixed nuts
shredded wheat chex
cheerios
salad oil
worcestershire sauce
seasoning salt
garlic salt
directions:
mix all in large roaster and bake in slow 250° oven for 2 hours.
stir every 15 minutes; cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
water
butter
brown sugar
salt
mustard
directions:
in 2-quart casserole, cook carrots in water on "high" for 9 to 10 minutes, stirring twice; drain.
cover and set aside.
melt butter on "high" for 30 seconds.
stir in brown sugar, salt and mustard.
pour over drained carrots; cover.
heat on high for 2 minutes.
serves 4.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apples
marshmallows
thin celery
walnuts

combine these ingredients along with kitchen ready tomatoes in a large pot.
add tabasco sauce and pepper to taste.
simmer over low heat, covered, for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
bacon
onion
cream of chicken soup
milk
sour cream
salt
parsley
white pepper
directions:

when ready to serve, crumble some of the bacon on top of soup.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
baking soda
mince meat
condensed milk
flour
peels
walnut meats
directions:
butter and flour 9 inch tube pan.
sift together flour and baking soda.
combine eggs, mince meat, condensed milk, fruits and nuts.
fold in dry ingredients.
pour into pan.
bake slow at 300° oven for 2 hours.
until center springs back when lightly touched with fingers and top is golden.
cool slightly and turn out of pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
meal
flour
salt
soda
baking powder
sugar
buttermilk
egg
shortening
directions:
mix dry ingredients.
add buttermilk, egg and melted fat. bake 45 minutes in loaf pan which has been greased and sprinkled well with meal.
pan size for one loaf: 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inches or 10 1/4 x 3 5/8 x 2 5/8-inches; 2 small loaves: 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inches.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen hash brown potatoes
cheddar cheese
cream of potato soup
sour cream
onion flakes
garlic salt
parsley
pepper
margarine
directions:
mix together in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
should be at room temperature before baking.
bake at 350° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
cake mix
pecans
directions:
place pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. spoon pie filling over pineapple.
cover with dry cake mix. place pecans on top of mix evenly.
bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
white karo
water
butter
soda
peanuts
directions:
mix sugar, karo and water.
boil until syrup forms a soft ball.
add peanuts and cook until golden in color (hard ball in cold water).
add butter and soda.
pour into greased pan.
break into pieces when hard.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white sugar
coconut
flour
egg yolks
milk
margarine
sugar
egg whites
vanilla
directions:

then add coconut, margarine and vanilla.
cook 2 more minutes, stirring constantly.
let cool, then pour in baked pie shell.

brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

awake frozen orange juice
cranberry juice
ginger ale
directions:
combine cold water with awake and cranberry juice cocktail. stir and chill.
just before serving, add chilled ginger ale and ice cubes.
makes 7 quarts punch.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh squash
onion
cracker crumbs
cheddar cheese
mayonnaise
cream of mushroom soup
salt
directions:
boil squash and onion in salted water until tender.
drain well and mash.
add other ingredients.
top with additional cracker crumbs.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
vegetable oil
salt
onions
green pepper
clove garlic
rice
tomato sauce
chicken broth
directions:
brown chicken in oil in 12-inch skillet until golden.
sprinkle with salt and pepper.
remove from skillet.
cook and stir in onions, green pepper, garlic and rice in skillet until oil is absorbed.
stir in sauce and chicken broth.

bring to boil.
cover and simmer 40 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fruit cocktail
pineapple
bananas
mandarin oranges
coconut
instant lemon pudding
vanilla pudding
directions:
drain mandarin oranges.
mix pudding with all fruit.
add coconut and oranges.
mix well.
chill for 1 hour before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
shrimp
crackers
cream cheese
chives
directions:
melt in microwave the margarine and cream cheese. drain and save juice of shrimp. add drained shrimp to cream cheese.
add chives and 6 tablespoons of juice. mix well.
sprinkle with paprika.
serve with crackers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh cranberries
orange
celery
lemon jello
boiling water
sugar
pecans
pineapple
pineapple juice
apple
directions:
mix jello and boiling water.
stir until jello melts.
add all other ingredients.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vinegar
catsup
black pepper
red pepper
red pepper
directions:
bring to a boil and set for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breast halves
pineapple
green pepper
brown sugar
water
soy sauce
vinegar
ginger
directions:
cut chicken into bite size pieces and saute in skillet using pam, until brown.
to dutch oven add juice from 20 oz. can of pineapple chunks, brown sugar, water, soy sauce, vinegar and ginger.

simmer until heated through and green pepper is tender.
serve over rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onion
green pepper
tomatoes
tomato sauce
water
bay leaf
salt
black pepper

velveeta cheese
parmesan cheese
directions:

add green pepper and onion.
cook until tender.
stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
in a 2-quart casserole dish, layer half the noodles, half the meat sauce and half the velveeta cheese.
repeat layers.

bake 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
baking powder
baking soda
salt
sour cream
peach preserves
egg
flour
vanilla extract
pecans
directions:
position rack in center of oven and preheat to 400°.
line 10 muffin cups with muffin papers.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
kernel corn
condensed cream
milk
celery
onions
cheddar cheese
bacon bits
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
combine corn, soup, milk, celery, 2/3 cup french fried onions, cheese and bacon bits in large bowl. spoon mixture into 2-quart square baking dish.
cover; bake 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
stir; sprinkle with remaining 2/3 cup french fried onions.
bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until fried onions are golden.	makes 4 to 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pecans
yellow cake
cold water
eggs
wesson oil
rum
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
grease and flour 10-inch tube or 12-cup bundt pan.
sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
mix all cake ingredients together.
pour batter over nuts.
bake 1 hour.

prick top.
spoon and brush glaze evenly over top and sides.
allow cake to absorb glaze.
repeat until glaze is used up.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mixed beans
water
ham hocks
onion
garlic
ground red pepper
tomatoes
lemon juice
salt
black pepper
ham
directions:
select beans from:
northern, pinto, lima (large or small), black-eyed, garbanzo, small white, kidney (red or white), pink, red, black, and navy.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
strawberry jello
cottage cheese
directions:
mix pineapple and jello.
boil 3 minutes.
cool.
mix with cottage cheese and cool whip.
chill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mushrooms

butter
salt
pepper
chicken broth
cream

flour
directions:
saute mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
blend in flour and seasonings.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
cauliflower
purple onion

sugar

directions:

let cool.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

garlic

milk

fontina cheese

rotelle
parmesan cheese
directions:
combine first 4 ingredients in medium bowl.

let stand at room temperature while cooking pasta.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
baking soda
salt
margarine
peanut butter
sugar
eggs
vanilla
directions:
in small bowl, stir flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
blend in sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
add flour mixture and blend well.

makes 6 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crisco
egg
cloves
soda
salt
sugar

molasses

ginger
directions:
cream shortening with 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
add egg and molasses; mix well.

chill 1 hour.
roll dough into 1-inch balls.
roll in sugar.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

take out yolks.
mix yolks, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and mustard.

vanilla

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
corn

water
sherry
salt

water

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

in olive oil in a large skillet.

well
and
heat.
return
meat
to

add cream
to

salt

oil

red
tomatoes

directions:

margarine

directions:
spray
9
x
5
x
3-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
on paper plate or sheet of wax paper combine dry

preheat oven to 350°.
in medium bowl,

a

then

onto

pan

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

catsup
oil
vinegar
sugar
red pepper

worcestershire sauce

salt
directions:
mix well.
cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

velveeta cheese
directions:
combine all the ingredients until smooth.

chill until firm.<|endofrecipe|>

onion

directions:
cook and drain noodles.

butter

cool.

stir and cook 1 minute.
add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.

cinnamon
directions:

bring to a boil.
remove from heat and pour over dough.

remove from oven and let set 2 to 3 minutes.

20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

vegetables

pepper
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
egg
milk

baking powder
salt
berries
directions:
*if using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

margarine
sugar
coconut
crushed soda crackers

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

fruit cocktail
pineapple
topping
graham cracker crust
directions:
mix ingredients; pour into graham cracker crusts.
allow to congeal in refrigerator.
makes 2 pies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
marshmallows

pineapple
nuts
directions:
put all ingredients in a bowl and stir together.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

egg
sugar
oil
flour
salt
soda
baking powder
directions:
mix all together in order listed.
beat by hand.
it won't be smooth.

directions:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peanut butter
confectioners sugar
cornstarch
sugar

egg yolks

directions:

in pie shell.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken thighs

mix with spoon by hand.
put on top of crust.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
crisco
eggs
sugar
flour
vanilla
directions:

add flour and eggs alternately.
add vanilla.
pour into pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn
milk
crackers
sugar
eggs
salt
bell pepper
onion
garlic
grated cheese
directions:
mix and bake at 400° until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter

vanilla
directions:

spread on two large cookie sheets that have been well buttered.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

celery
fresh spinach

onion

fresh ground black pepper
directions:

in a large bowl, toss all ingredients together until well blended.

very tasty!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

grated sharp
milk
macaroni
velveeta cheese
directions:
cook macaroni according to package directions. drain. add margarine and all of the cheeses.
stir until cheese melts.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apple cider
ginger ale
lemons
oranges
lemon
orange
directions:

serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
graham cracker crumbs

apple pie filling
walnuts
ground cinnamon
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
place butter in a square pan and melt in oven.
sprinkle in crumbs and stir well.
press mixture to bottom of pan.
in a bowl, mix milk, sour cream and lemon juice. spread evenly over crumbs.
spoon pie filling evenly over creamy layer.
in a small bowl, mix nuts and cinnamon. sprinkle over pie gently.
bake 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
cool slightly.
may be served warm or cold.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter
pet milk
caramels
chocolate chips
nuts
directions:

put 1/2 in a pan and bake 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.

cook 18 to 20 minutes at 350° (no longer).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green chilies
clove garlic
vegetable oil
tomatoes
onion
oregano
chicken
sour cream
cheddar cheese
flour tortillas
directions:
saute chilies and garlic in oil, in large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat until soft.
add tomatoes, breaking up, reserved liquid, onion and oregano.
simmer 30 minutes until thick.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
mayonnaise
milk
directions:
mix and put in greased muffin pans.
serve hot with butter. tastes great!
really!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pecans
brown sugar
egg whites
directions:
mix together.
form into small balls.
roll in granulated sugar.
press into top of each cookie with thumb, a piece of pecan or candied fruit.
bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flank steak
garlic
vegetable oil
white wine vinegar
salt
white pepper
white wine
shallot
fresh chervil
bay leaf
egg yolks
water
butter
directions:
score both sides of steak in a diamond pattern. rub with garlic.
place in a shallow bowl. coat lightly with the vegetable oil, vinegar, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon white pepper. let steak stand for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fruit cocktail
oranges
apples
handful of pecans
handful
mayonnaise
directions:
drain juice from fruit cocktail.
mix all fruit, pecans and marshmallows with enough mayonnaise to moisten.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
cornstarch
salt
eggs
milk
vanilla
angel
pie shell
directions:
combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
add beaten egg yolks. stir in milk; cook over slow heat until thick.
add vanilla and coconut.
save enough coconut to put on top of egg whites.
beat egg whites.
add 1/4 cup sugar gradually.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lean ground beef

chilies
longhorn cheese
onion
milk
corn tortillas
directions:
crumble beef into heated skillet.
add onion.
cook over medium heat until meat loses red color.

bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
yields 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
marshmallows
whipped cream
pie shell
directions:
dissolve marshmallows in 1/2 cup milk (may want to use a double boiler to dissolve).
stir in hershey bar until melted. cool this mixture.
add 1/2 pint whipped cream.
pour in pie shell.
refrigerate 4 hours.
can garnish with whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
condensed milk
lemon juice
strawberries
pie shell
directions:
beat together, cheese and milk then add lemon juice and fold in. add fresh sliced strawberries and pour in baked pie shell. do not sugar the strawberries.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
noodles
hamburger
mozzarella cheese
bread
milk
egg
spaghetti sauce
parsley
directions:
brown hamburger and drain well.
add diced cheese, parsley, salt, pepper, bread, milk and egg.
mix well.
boil noodles and stuff with meat mixture.
put some spaghetti sauce on bottom of cake pan and put noodles in (tightly).
top with remaining sauce. cover with foil and bake 1/2 hour at 350 - 375 degrees.
remove foil and top with parmesan cheese and a bit of parsley for color. bake an additional 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peaches
water
sugar
butter
directions:
mix together in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cookie crumbs
butter
caramels
milk
pecan
cream cheese
sugar
vanilla
eggs
chocolate
directions:
preheat oven to 325° if using a silver 9-inch spring-form pan (or to 300° if using a dark nonstick spring-form pan).
mix crumbs and butter; press firmly onto bottom and 2-inches up side of pan. place caramels and milk in small microwavable bowl.
microwave on high 3 minutes or until caramels are completely melted, stirring after each minute.
stir in pecans.
pour half of the caramel mixture for later use.
beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended.
pour over caramel layer in crust.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
cream of tartar
cold water
vegetable oil
couple
directions:
put all ingredients into a saucepan.
cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
dough will become hard to stir.
take off heat. let cool; knead.
place in plastic sack or wrap.
will keep for a long time.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

ground lean pork
egg
rice
chile powder
salt
tomatoes
water
onion
salt
directions:

brown.
combine tomatoes, water, onion and salt.
bring to boil; add meat balls.
cover and cook slowly about 1 1/2 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apple juice
ginger ale
orange juice
directions:
combine all ingredients
in
a	blender.
combine fruit juices and ginger ale.
pour
over
block	of ice.
float over block of ice.
float orange slices on top of punch.	yields 50 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
prunes
lemon peel
apricots
see moi
hawaiian salt
brown sugar
anise seed
whiskey
lemon juice
directions:
mix and soak all ingredients for 2 to 3 days, the longer the better.
mix every day.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
eggs
soda
salt
pineapple
directions:
mix all the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
sprinkle top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
bake 30 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
poultry seasoning
ginger
flour
directions:
wash chicken and dry. shake in bag flour, poultry seasoning and ginger with chicken.
bake at 375° for 1 hour.
melt 1 stick butter and baste every 1/2 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh spinach
cream cheese
butter
salt
bread crumbs
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
cook spinach for 5 to 8 minutes or as directed on package. drain and mix with cream cheese, 4 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
pour into casserole.
melt remaining butter. toss with crumbs and sprinkle over casserole. bake 20 to 30 minutes. even spinach haters like this!

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

mix lightly through berries.
pour into pastry lined pie pan.
dot with butter; wet around edge of pie crust.
cover with top crust, which has slits cut in it.
seal and flute..

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apricots
sugar
water
flour
salt

margarine

nuts
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

beans

cheddar cheese

directions:

brown meat and onions in a skillet, drain grease, if necessary.

simmer 5 minutes.
unroll dough into 4 long rectangles.
place in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

cut into squares and top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes, taco sauce, sour cream, etc.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
water
cooking oil
food coloring
directions:
mix dry ingredients together in a bowl.
slowly add water and oil and knead to a pliable dough.
add a little salt and flour if sticky.
add drops of food coloring and knead until the desired color is achieved.
keep in an airtight container.
do not refrigerate.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar

coconut
butter
vanilla
directions:
combine sugar, corn syrup and 1/2 cup half and half in a heavy saucepan.
cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (230° on candy thermometer).
add 1/2 cup half and half; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage again.
add remaining half and half; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture again reaches the soft ball stage.
remove mixture from heat; add coconut, butter and vanilla. stir until butter is melted.
pour into a greased 8 x 4 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan; let stand until cool.
turn candy out onto a marble slab or waxed paper.
cut into 1-inch squares.
let stand overnight.
wrap individually in plastic wrap.
yield:
about 32 (1-inch) pieces.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

hormel chili without beans
onions
pepper cheese
directions:
layer cream cheese, chili and cheese.
sprinkle onions and green peppers on top.
bake until the cheese is melted in a 350° oven.
serve hot with doritos or tortilla chips.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cheerios
potatoes
nuts
salad oil
brown sugar
worcestershire sauce
garlic salt
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
noodles
ground beef
salt
pepper
garlic salt
tomato sauce
cheese

sour cream

green onions

directions:

then last half of noodles, cover with remaining half of meat mixture and top with shredded cheddar cheese.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
butter
vinegar
brown sugar
water

salt
directions:
mix all ingredients in saucepan.
cook until onion is tender on low heat.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

margarine
egg
green chiles
cheddar cheese
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

butter

nuts
rice krispies
chocolate chips
paraffin
directions:
mix first 6 ingredients together.

nuts
directions:

cook until done.
mash with potato masher.
add 1 small can evaporated milk. add milk and butter and celery salt.

sugar

salt

vanilla
directions:
butter a 9 x 13 pan.
set aside.
mix cocoa, sugar, and salt in a large, heavy pan.

cook over med heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to full boil.

remove from heat, add vanilla, and butter, but do not stir.
allow to cool until lukewarm (about 110°).

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

salt
flour
butter
eggs
directions:

set aside.
heat together crisco, boiling water, sugar and salt until melted.

mix all with electric mixer.
let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours. knead 100 times.
roll dough to 1/4-inch thick.
cut up into 1 to 2-inch squares.
dip each piece into melted butter.
place in bundt pan.

blend in flour and seasonings.

pecans

's cajun

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

green pepper

turmeric

directions:
mix together in microwave bowl.
cover with saran wrap.
cook on high temperature for 3 1/2 minutes.
stir and repeat 3 1/2 minutes.

onion
mayonnaise

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

milk
eggs
directions:

bake about 1 1/2 hours, possibly with reduced heat the last half hour.
baste occasionally with syrup.
syrup will be thick when done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
garlic
olive oil
tomatoes
oregano
basil
salt
pepper
mozzarella cheese
parmesan cheese
directions:

bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of celery

paprika
chicken breasts
vegetables
rice
directions:
microwave:
in a 2-quart casserole dish, blend soup, mayonnaise and paprika.

cover.

let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
stir before serving.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

margarine
corn muffin
directions:

pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cinnamon

directions:

let stand 4 hours or overnight.
drain off liquid and cook until it coats a spoon.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

oil

directions:

reserve 2 cups of yellow batter.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
brown sugar

eggs
unsweetened chocolate
almonds
vanilla
flour
salt
baking powder
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
cream butter.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
deli-style
yellow mustard
onion
butter
poppy seeds
swiss cheese
bacon
directions:
mix butter, mustard, onion and poppy seeds. cut the crust from the loaf - do not remove the bottom crust. slice 3/4 of the way through the loaf every 1 to 1 1/2 inches. "paint" the entire loaf with the mustard mixture (between the slices also-not the bottom). fold one or two slices of cheese and place between each bread slice across the loaf. top each slice of bread with a slice of partially cooked bacon. bake in a 350 degree oven of 15 minutes. the cheese should appear "melty". place the loaf under the broiler to brown the bacon, watching closely so it doesn't burn. slice and serve with your favorite soup.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

tomatoes
salt
basil
thyme
white pepper
vermicelli
peas
parsley
parmesan cheese
directions:
in a 5-quart kettle, cook bacon over medium heat until it begins to brown.
mix in onion, mushrooms, garlic and carrots. cook, stirring, until onion is soft.
add broth, tomatoes, salt, basil, thyme and pepper.
bring to boiling.
cover.
reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
stuffing
broccoli
noodles
cream of chicken soup
directions:
put in 9 x 12-inch dish a layer of stuffing.
pick chicken off bones and lay on top of stuffing.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bacon
round steak
carrots
onion

turn into bowl and beat again until fluffy.
fold in spinach, cottage cheese, celery and onion.
turn into mold and chill until firm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
flour
salt
pepper
milk
american cheese
fully cooked ham
green onion
eggs
mushrooms
bread crumbs
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
baking powder
milk
salt
butter
directions:

mix other ingredients, except pie filling, together.
add to melted butter.
pour 1 can of pie filling over this; do not stir.
bake in a 325° oven for 55 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cauliflower
broccoli
onion
sugar
miracle
pet milk
vinegar
directions:
cut the cauliflower, broccoli and onion together in a large bowl.
mix sugar, milk, vinegar and miracle whip together.
add to the vegetables; mix well and chill in the refrigerator.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
shortening
eggs
flour
salt
lemon juice
vanilla flavoring
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
cream together sugar and shortening. add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
add flour, one tablespoon at a time.
beat well.
beat in salt, lemon juice and vanilla flavoring; beat well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
cream of chicken soup
couple
directions:
mix. bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
miracle
milk
ground cumin
onion powder
ground red pepper
garlic powder
chicken breasts
sesame crackers
salsa
directions:
preheat oven to 425°.
mix together 1/2 cup salad dressing, milk and seasonings.
lightly dip chicken into salad dressing mixture.
coat well with crumbs.
place on greased cookie sheet. bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
mix remaining salad dressing and salsa. serve with nuggets on toothpicks.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butterscotch chips
mein noodles
peanuts
beans
directions:
melt butterscotch chips in pan over low heat.
add noodles and peanuts to melted chips and stir.
drop large spoonfuls of this mixture onto cookie sheets lined with wax paper.
shape each into a nest with your fingers.
put 4 to 6 jellybean "eggs" into each nest.
chill in the refrigerator.
wonderful recipe for the kids to help with!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen spinach
milk
eggs
mayonnaise
flour
onion
bacon
ham
cheese
directions:
mix ingredients.
pour into 9 5/8-inch pie crust.
bake at 325° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
layer
milk
coconut
sugar
directions:
prepare cake mix as directed on package.
bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
cool for 15 minutes.
when cool, make holes through cake. combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut in saucepan.
bring to a boil.
reduce heat and simmer for three minutes.
carefully spoon over warm cake allowing liquid to soak down through holes.
let cool.
fold 1/2 cup coconut into cool whip and spread over the cake.
sprinkle the rest of the coconut over the cake.
chill overnight.
store leftover cake in the refrigerator.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground up deer meat
chili seasoning
tomato sauce
kidney beans
tomato juice
directions:
cook deer meat.
add chili seasoning with tomato sauce and tomato juice.
takes about 20 to 25 minutes.
add kidney beans, if desired.
great with hot dogs!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen broccoli
cream of mushroom soup
cheddar cheese
milk
mayonnaise
egg
bread crumbs
butter
directions:
cook broccoli according to directions on package, then drain. stir together soup and cheese; gradually add milk, mayonnaise and egg, stirring to blend.
put broccoli in dish and pour mixture over top.
combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over top. bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bananas
sugar
sour cream
pecans
cherries
pineapple
directions:
mix banana, pineapple, sugar and sour cream.
add pecans and cherries.
freeze in individual molds or cut in squares.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
chicken breast
cream of chicken soup
mayonnaise
water chestnuts
lemon juice
curry powder
shredded cheese
butter
bread crumbs
directions:
place broccoli in bottom of pan.
sprinkle chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
combine soup and other ingredients adding next. top with bread crumbs and cheese.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

cream cheese
vanilla
graham cracker crumbs
butter
lemon juice
sugar
directions:
dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
add lemon juice. cool.
cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
add gelatin and mix well.
whip the chilled can of milnot and fold into gelatin mixture.
mix together the crushed graham crackers and melted butter.
pack 2/3 of mixture in bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs. chill several hours.
cut into squares and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork chops
butter
onion
green pepper
mushroom soup
beef consomme
rice
directions:

remove from skillet; brown onion and green pepper.
combine mushroom soup and beef consomme with rice, then onion and pepper.
place in 2-quart casserole with pork chops on top.
cover with foil.
bake 45 minutes at 350°.
(trim bones from chops, if desired.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange jello
salt
boiling water
vinegar
mayonnaise
pineapple
cottage cheese
celery
green pepper
green onions
directions:
mix first four ingredients together and add mayonnaise. beat. mix the rest of the ingredients together and add cool jello mixture. use 9 x 13 pan, sprayed with pam.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shredded coconut
chicken breast
butter
flour
directions:
preheat oven to 350°. place the coconut, butter and flour in separate plates. (the butter will need to be in a bowl.)
coat chicken lightly with flour. dip in melted butter. coat chicken generously with coconut. this can be done by rolling the chicken in coconut. place chicken in a baking dish and keep in the oven for approximately 30 to 40 minutes or until the coconut has "browned" and the chicken has been fully cooked.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
zucchini
watchers
ricotta cheese
green pepper
mushrooms
mozzarella cheese
directions:
slice zucchini and cook in microwave for 3 minutes.
layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
bake for 1 hour at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
cream of chicken soup
water
chiles
dressing
white cheese
butter
directions:
mix soup, water or wine and diced chiles.
place chicken in 13 x 9 baking dish.

sprinkle top with dressing.
drizzle melted butter over all.
bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes or until chicken is done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
cheddar
pineapple
salt
onion
green peppers
directions:
beat cream cheese until fluffy and add other ingredients.
mix well.
use medium size melon ball scoop.
make into balls. roll in finely chopped nuts.
refrigerate.
makes 125 balls.
great for weddings!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese

vanilla wafer crumbs

almonds
cocoa
powdered sugar
directions:
combine cream cheese and chocolate, mixing until well blended. stir in crumbs and preserves.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

bell pepper
onion
pimentos

mayonnaise
directions:
cook macaroni and drain.
mix all ingredients.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

celery salt

directions:
mix all ingredients, breaking up crackers.
add crab meat, picked over.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
