chicken breasts
cream of chicken soup
cheddar cheese
mayonnaise
butter
bread crumbs
directions:
steam broccoli until tender.
spread butter on chicken and bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion
parmesan cheese

paprika
pepper
directions:
in a 2-quart ziploc bag, place last 5 ingredients.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

white rice

onion
celery
directions:
thaw and drain broccoli.
saute onion and celery in 3/4 stick of butter.
mix all ingredients together.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs

directions:
combine butter and sugar.
mix in eggs and vanilla.
add combined dry ingredients and butterfingers.
mix well.
pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

pour in colander and drain well.

flour

place chicken in baking dish.
mix broth and chicken soup; heat to boiling.
pour over chicken.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

onion
kidney beans
tomatoes
tomato sauce
chili powder
salt
cheddar cheese
directions:
brown ground beef, drain.
stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
cover, simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. top with cheese.
sprinkle with additional chopped onion if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
rice
ground beef
celery
onion
bell pepper
tomatoes
water
salt
pepper
granulated beef bouillon
worcestershire sauce
pepper
directions:
in large electric skillet or frying pan with tight fitting lid, fry ground beef and onion until brown and onion is tender.
drain grease.
add all other ingredients.

yields 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
sauce
water
cottage cheese
parmesan cheese
eggs
salt
pepper
directions:
brown beef in 3-quart saucepan.
drain excess fat.
add sauce and water.
simmer 10 minutes.
combine rest of ingredients, except lasagne for filling.

spread 1/2 of cheese filling over sauce.
repeat layers of lasagne, sauce and cheese filling.

bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
salt
shortening
milk
flour
directions:
mix eggs, salt and sugar thoroughly.
add milk and stir.
add shortening and mix.
slowly add flour.
cook as you would pancakes on a lightly greased griddle.
you may substitute brown sugar for the white sugar.
these are great with jam or syrup.
roll them up if you wish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vanilla pudding
yellow cake
rum
oil
water
eggs
pecans
butter
sugar
rum
directions:
preheat oven to 325°.
butter bundt type cake pan.
coat with pecans.
beat pudding, cake mix, rum, oil, water and eggs together just until smooth.
pour into pan and bake 1 hour.
cool cake. poke holes in cake.
heat butter, sugar and rum until sugar is dissolved.
dribble over cake.
let set several hours or overnight.
remove from pan.
yumm!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

egg
onion
worcestershire sauce
salt
milk
butter

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
shortening
sugar
eggs
buttermilk
baking soda
flour
vanilla extract
black walnuts
flaked coconut
cream of tartar
cream cheese frosting
black walnuts
directions:
cream the butter and shortening.
gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer. add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
combine buttermilk and soda. stir until soda dissolves. add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
mix after each addition. stir in vanilla. add 1 cup walnuts and coconut, stirring well.
beat egg whites (at room temperature) and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
fold into batter.
pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. cool in pans 10 minutes. remove from pans.
let cool completely on wire racks. spread cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and
sides of cake.
press additional walnuts onto sides of cake.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
garlic salt
pepper
celery
margarine
spaghetti sauce
italian seasoning
wild rice
directions:
cook rice; cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips and sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
saute chicken and celery in margarine 4 to 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
stir in spaghetti sauce and italian seasoning.
bring to a boil and then simmer 10 minutes.
serve over rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
graham crackers
raisins
marshmallows
milk
pecans

crush crackers, marshmallows and chip up cherries and nuts. add pecans and mix.

instant coffee

walnuts
halves
shell
directions:

bake in lower third of oven for 25 minutes.

refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cookies
butter
cream cheese
powdered sugar
milk
vanilla pudding
whipped topping
gummy worms
directions:
crush cookies (reserve 1/4 cup).
cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
mix milk and pudding.
combine butter mixture with pudding.
fold in whipped topping and cookies.
top with reserved cookie crumbs and gummy worms.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cucumbers
onions
directions:
soak in cold water and 2 tablespoons salt.
in 2 hours drain. mix 1/2 cup vinegar, 1 1/2 cups sugar dissolved real good.
pour over cucumbers.
bag and freeze.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
white syrup
butter
salt
vanilla
pecan halves
pastry shell
directions:
add sugar, corn syrup and butter to beaten eggs.
add vanilla and salt; mix thoroughly.
stir in pecan halves.

bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

flour
vegetable oil
margarine
shallots
garlic
water
white wine
chicken broth
ground rosemary
salt
pepper
chives
directions:
skin and bone chicken breast; cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
in a 10-inch nonstick skillet, combine oil and margarine and heat over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
dredge chicken in flour; cook in skillet until browned on all sides (3 to 4 minutes). remove chicken from pan; set aside.
add shallots and garlic to skillet; saute until softened.
add water, wine, broth mix and seasonings.
using a wooden spoon, stir well.

return chicken to skillet; cook until sauce is thick and chicken is heated through. serve sprinkled with chives.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen hash brown potatoes
green onions

sour cream
butter
cheddar cheese

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red cabbage
apples
bacon fat
onion
water
salt
pepper
cloves
bay leaf
vinegar
directions:

cook over medium heat, covered, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cabbage
green onions
ramen noodles
kernel sunflower seeds
apple cider vinegar
oil
sugar
directions:
combine apple cider, vinegar, oil, sugar and broth packs from ramen noodles.
refrigerate.
combine cabbage, green onions, crushed ramen noodles (uncooked) and sunflower seeds.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
butter
green pepper
celery
bay leaf
parsley
salt
cayenne pepper
tomato paste
water
shrimp
rice
directions:
in 2-quart saucepan, cook onion in butter, stirring, until onion is tender.
stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
crisco
molasses
vanilla
baking powder
flour
soda
directions:

boil 5 minutes.

mix.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
vanilla
eggs
butter
chocolate
directions:

add vanilla and chocolate and mix.
add 1 egg and beat on high for 5 minutes.
add second egg, beat on high for 5 minutes.
pour into precooked pie shell, chill for 4 hours.

do not try to double recipe for 2 pies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter

directions:

add eggs and vanilla; mix well.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

orange juice
water
pineapple sherbet
vanilla ice cream
directions:

spoon in ice cream and sherbet.
serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

flour
milk

pimento
salt

buttered bread crumbs
directions:
saute onion
in butter until soft; blend in flour.
add milk, stirring	constantly.
cook
until
thickened.	add crabmeat, pimento,
salt, pepper and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
place 1/2 mixture in greased casserole; cover with 1/2 bread crumbs. add remaining crab mixture;
top with remaining bread crumbs. bake for 20 minutes at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
graham cracker crumbs
sugar
butter
philadelphia cream cheese
sugar
flour
vanilla
sour cream
eggs
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bacon
northern beans
brown sugar
mustard
onion
catsup
syrup
directions:
lightly brown bacon and onion in skillet.
add remaining ingredients.
turn on low heat and simmer 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
sugar
flour
vanilla
vinegar
eggs
pie shell
directions:
combine first 6 ingredients, blending well; pour in pie shell. bake at 300° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
lemon juice
egg
bread crumbs
parmesan cheese
butter
lemon wedges
directions:

directions:

stir in 1 cup of whipped topping. pour 2 cups milk in bowl.

beat with whisk 2 minutes.
let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping.
spoon into crust. arrange cookies over pudding mixture.

refrigerate 4 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

directions:
put the dry ingredients in a small bowl.
make sure all lumps are crushed and well blended.
put mayo in mixing bowl, then mix the horseradish, mustard, cayenne and vinegar into the mayo with an electric mixture.

is exceptionally good with beef or pork.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
flour
salt
cinnamon
baking soda
eggs

carrots
directions:

beat eggs and oil together; add to dry ingredients.
mix well.
add carrots last and mix.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

pimentos
stalks celery
almonds
bell pepper
onion
mayonnaise
lemon juice
salt
cheddar cheese
potato chips
directions:
combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. place in greased casserole dish.

last 5 to 10 minutes before done, place on cheese and crushed chips.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cookies

margarine
sugar
milk
vanilla
salt

fruit

sugar

mushrooms

pepper

onion
ham
vinegar
water
salt
sugar
directions:

o

cherries

directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red beans

directions:
cook beans until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
combine first 7 ingredients.

directions:

in

listed, adding eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.

and floured bundt pan.

eggs
and oil lightly.

ingredients
and

mix and knead until doughy.<|endofrecipe|>

a

sugar,
stirring
constantly.

stir
until

with
a

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

carrots
directions:

of each quahaug half (in shell).
sprinkle red pepper and parsley
on top.
top
each
one with 1/4 slice of raw bacon. place
in
large shallow
pan
and
bake
in 350° oven for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green tomatoes
meal
salt
shortening
black pepper
directions:
wash tomatoes and pat dry.
cut tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices. sprinkle with salt and pepper.
dip each slice in corn meal and lay aside on waxed paper.
heat oil.
fry tomato slices until golden brown.
drain on paper towels.
serve hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
apples
crescent rolls
margarine
sugar
cinnamon
orange juice
directions:
unroll crescent rolls and separate into 8 triangles.
cut each in half lengthwise to make 16 triangles.
place an apple slice at wide end of each triangle and roll up.
arrange in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
drizzle with melted butter.
combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
pour orange juice into pan, but not over rolls.
bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
if you like more tender apples, cover with aluminum foil and bake 10 minutes longer.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potato
tuna
tartar sauce
parsley
lemon juice
egg
crackers
olives
directions:
peel potato, cut into quarters and boil for 15 minutes. remove and mash. mix in the drained tuna, potato, tartar sauce, parsley and lemon juice. divide the tuna mixture into 6 parts. create a fish shape about 3/4 inch thick. beat the egg
shallow bowl and crush crackers in another shallow bowl. dip the fish into the egg, then into the cracker crumbs. place the pattie on cookie sheet and refrigerate for 2 hours. bake the fish at 375° for 15 minutes. an olive
can be placed on each fish for the eye.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green onions
margarine
creamer
chicken broth
potatoes
carrots
regular rice
frozen spinach
directions:
cook onions in butter until soft.
add nondairy creamer all at once to boiling chicken broth and stir to blend.
add potatoes, carrots and rice to cooked onions; stir.
cover and cook 15 minutes; add to broth.
add frozen spinach and continue boiling for 15 minutes more, stirring often to prevent sticking.
salt and pepper to taste.
can be frozen and reheated.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
hamburger
eggs
bread crumbs
onion
garlic powder
brown sugar
vinegar
mustard
tomato sauce
directions:
put the eggs, bread crumbs and onions in the hamburger.
put the rest of the ingredients in the tomato sauce.
pour 1/2 the tomato sauce in the hamburger mixture and put the rest on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cake
semi-sweet chocolate chips
eggs
vanilla
sugar
whipping cream
directions:
cut angel food cake into three layers.
melt chocolate; beat egg yolks lightly.
whip egg whites until stiff, adding sugar, beaten egg yolks and melted chocolate.
slowly add vanilla.
whip the cream into peaks.
spoon a layer of chocolate and then a layer of cream between each layer of cake.
wrap cake in wax paper and put in refrigerator for several hours before using.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mayonnaise
salt
vinegar
lemon
black pepper
sugar
directions:
heat almost to a boil.
after chicken is almost done on the grill, coat with white sauce.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
sugar
eggs
milk
nutmeg
butter
directions:
stir all ingredients together, except butter, then stir in the melted butter.
drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corned beef
sauerkraut
dark rye bread
swiss cheese
cream of celery soup
directions:
mix dressing and soup together.
beginning with bread cubes, layer all ingredients in a lightly buttered 4-quart casserole. pour soup mixture over all.
bake at 325°, covered, about 1 hour or until bubbly.
uncover last 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
active dry yeast
margarine
egg
water
sugar
flour
directions:
mix yeast and water together.
add margarine.
mix in egg, sugar and flour.
bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tortillas
cream cheese
green chilies
black olives
sour cream
picante
directions:
mix all ingredients except tortillas.
spread thin layer of mixture over tortilla and chill at least 3 hours (overnight is best).
cut into 1-inch pieces.
serve with picante.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
elephant
brown gravy
peas
rabbits
salt
directions:
cut elephant into bite size pieces.
this should take about two months.
add enough brown gravy to cover.
add peas.
cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks at 450°.
this will serve 3,800 people.
if more are expected, add the rabbits.
do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
trout
egg
light cream
all-purpose
cooking oil
butter
almonds
lemon juice
directions:
thaw fish, if frozen.
bone trout, if desired. season. combine egg and cream or milk.
dip fish in flour, then in egg-cream mixture and again in flour.
in a large skillet, heat together the oil and 2 tablespoons of the butter.
fry trout in hot oil mixture for 5 to 6 minutes on each side or until golden and fish flakes easily with a fork.
in a skillet, cook almonds in remaining butter until nuts are golden brown.
remove from heat. stir in lemon juice.
place trout on a platter; pour almond mixture over.
serves 4 to 6.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground meat
ro-tel tomatoes
tomato soup
onion
cheddar cheese soup
garlic powder
jalapenos
mozzarella cheese
cheddar cheese
doritos
cream of celery soup
salt
directions:
brown and drain ground meat and onion.
mix tomatoes, soups and peppers.
stir in meat and onion.
layer in pan doritos, meat mixture and grated cheese.
bake at 350° until cheese melts.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
salt
pepper
oil
onion
vegetable juice cocktail
directions:
dredge meat in flour, salt and pepper. saute meat in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
add onions and juice.
cover and simmer about 2 hours or until tender or bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 2 hours.
thicken gravy as desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
steak
soy sauce
cornstarch
sherry
sugar
oil
broccoli
salt
onion
directions:
mix together first 6 ingredients and set aside.
cut broccoli in florets about 2 inches long.
peel stalk and slice in 2 inch lengths less than 1/2 inch thick.
put 2 tablespoons oil in hot skillet or wok over high heat.
add broccoli and stir-fry until broccoli is dark green, not over 2 minutes.
remove and add 2 tablespoons oil to skillet.
add onions and beef; stir-fry 2 minutes.
add broccoli to skillet and stir-fry to warm broccoli. serve with rice.
makes 2 to 3 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beans
brown sugar
mustard
ketchup
bacon
directions:
put half of beans in a baking dish.
add 3/4 cup sugar and ketchup.
add remaining beans and ketchup and add mustard.
break up bacon to cover the top of the baking dish.
bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour tortillas
sausage
eggs
american cheese
hot sauce
directions:
brown sausage; add beaten eggs (usually 6) to sausage and scramble together.
heat tortillas in wet paper towels (30 to 60 seconds).
place cheese slice on hot tortilla and add sausage and eggs.
use hot sauce as desired.
roll 'em up and eat.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
olive oil
tarragon vinegar
lemon juice
garlic
mustard
sugar
salt
freshly ground black pepper
directions:
combine mustard, sugar, salt and a generous amount of pepper. mix in garlic.
add vinegar and lemon juice and stir thoroughly. add oil and mix well.
stir or shake vigorously just before using. makes about 3 cups or 24 servings of 2 tablespoons each.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
baking potatoes
sour cream
cheddar cheese
salt
butter
directions:
bake potatoes wrapped in foil. cut potatoes down middle while leaving in foil. spoon out potato, leaving skin in foil.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
raisins
water
egg
shortening
oats
liquid sweetener
vanilla
cinnamon
flour
salt
baking soda
directions:
combine raisins and water; simmer 15 minutes.
cool.
add beaten egg, softened shortening and vanilla.
stir.
add oats and sweetener.
add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
mix well. pour into 1 layer cake pan.
bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vanilla wafer crumbs
sugar
butter
cream cheese
milk
eggs
lemon juice concentrate
strawberry preserves
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
bake for 8 minutes; cool.
reduce oven temperature to 300°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
cream cheese
sugar
vanilla
salt
biscuit mix
eggs
directions:
beat together butter and cream cheese.
add sugar, vanilla and salt.
beat all together, then add biscuit mix.
add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
put in greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° around 45 minutes or when cake falls in middle.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
broccoli
cheddar cheese
cream of chicken
milk
directions:
boil chicken until tender.
shred into bite sizes.
cook broccoli until half done.
save 1 cup cheese for topping.
layer chicken and broccoli in casserole.
mix remaining cheese, soup and milk together.
pour over chicken and broccoli.
sprinkle with cheese.
bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until broccoli is tender.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh cranberries
oranges
sugar
pineapple
walnuts
lemon juice
boiling water
lemon jello
salt
directions:
make relish by grinding together cranberries and oranges, including the peel of one orange.
mix with lemon juice, sugar and salt.
this can be frozen.
to make salad, dissolve jello in the boiling water.
stir in the rest of the ingredients plus 2 cups of the cranberry, orange mixture.
jell in the refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours.
makes 8 to 10 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sausage
quick grits
boiling water
butter
eggs
milk
cheddar cheese
salt
directions:
brown sausage; sprinkle in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole. cook grits in boiling water per package instructions until thickened and creamy.
add butter to grits and pour over meat.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pared apples
water
cinnamon
salt
sugar
flour
butter
directions:
heat oven to 350°.
spread apples evenly in an 8 x 8-inch square or 9-inch round baking dish/pan.
sprinkle with water, cinnamon and salt mixture.
toss lightly.
mix sugar, flour and butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
spread over apples. bake at 350°, uncovered, about 40 minutes.
serve warm with milk, cream or ice cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white bread
cream cheese
vanilla
milk
butter
sugar
cinnamon
directions:
combine cream cheese with milk and vanilla; mix well.
cut off crust from bread.
roll each slice very thin and spread with cream cheese mixture.
roll each bread slice up tightly.
dip each roll in melted butter and dip in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
cut each roll into 3 pieces and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
bake in a 300° oven for about 10 minutes.
cool and serve on a platter with a bowl of sour cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
onion
cooking oil
rice
boiling water
tomatoes
kidney beans
salt
pepper
worcestershire sauce
chili powder
directions:
brown meat and onion in oil.
add rice and cook until golden. stir in all remaining ingredients.
simmer 15 to 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread type
sugar
active dry yeast
water
directions:
combine flour, sugar and undissolved active dry yeast in a large bowl.
gradually add warm water to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
cover with transparent wrap; let stand
in warm place for 2 days.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shortening
sugar
eggs
bananas
flour
soda
salt
nuts
directions:
if bananas are large and firm, 3 would be enough; however, if they are small or have any bad spots, i use 4.
cream shortening and sugar.
add unbeaten eggs and mix well.
sift together flour, soda and salt; add half of flour mixture and stir well.
add bananas.
add remainder of flour mixture.
blend thoroughly.
add nuts and mix thoroughly.
pour in lightly greased loaf pan.
bake from 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
sugar
eggs
vanilla
flour
salt
baking powder
nutmeg
yogurt
pears
directions:
cream margarine, gradually beat in sugar.
beat in eggs, one at a time.
combine all dry ingredients.
add to egg mixture, alternating with yogurt.
stir in pears and vanilla.
pour into buttered dish or loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
bake at 350° for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh broccoli
cream of chicken soup
bread crumbs
chicken
milk
butter
directions:
preheat oven to 425 degrees. chop broccoli and steam for 5 to 10 minutes. in a mixing bowl, combine soup and milk. in a separate small bowl, mix bread crumbs and butter.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
soda
salt
sugar
buttermilk
shortening
yeast
directions:
sift flour, soda, salt and sugar together.
add buttermilk and shortening (scalded).
dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
stir into flour mixture.
let stand for 10 minutes.
knead on floured surface; shape into desired rolls.
place on lightly greased baking sheet.
let rise until doubled in bulk.
bake at 400° until lightly browned.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vegetarian skallops
bread crumbs
sauce
parmesan cheese
egg
mozzarella cheese
olive oil
directions:
combine bread crumbs and 1/4 cup parmesan cheese.
dip each piece of gluten into eggs, then bread crumbs and brown in hot oil until golden brown.
layer in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish:
gluten, tomato sauce, mozzarella cheese.
top with sauce and 1/4 cup parmesan cheese.
bake at 350° for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sweet oranges
sugar
coconut
powdered sugar
directions:
peel and slice oranges.
take out seeds.
use a large dish (clear is nice).
put one layer of oranges; sprinkle with sugar, then a layer of coconut.
keep layering until all oranges are used up.
be sure to end up with a layer of coconut on top.
sprinkle with powdered sugar last.
let stand for 2 hours before serving. goooood!!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
eggs
flour
baking powder
milk
vanilla
pineapple
butter
powdered sugar
pineapple
directions:
cream shortening, butter and sugar. add eggs, one at a time beating after each addition.
sift flour and baking powder.
add it alternately with milk, a teaspoon of milk at a time.
stir in vanilla, pineapple and juice and blend well.
pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan (10-inch) and place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when lightly touched.
let stand for a few minutes, then run knife around edge and remove carefully to cooling rack.
combine topping ingredients and pour over cake while still hot.
pour the following over hot baked cake:<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange gelatin
water
marshmallows
vanilla frozen yogurt
orange segments
directions:
mix gelatin and water in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart microwavable bowl. microwave on high 1 1/2 minutes.
stir until dissolved completely.
add marshmallows; microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until marshmallows are puffed and almost melted.
stir mixture slowly until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is smooth.
add frozen yogurt.
stir with wire whisk until melted. stir in oranges.
pour into 6-cup ring mold.
refrigerate 45 minutes, or until set.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chocolate chips
shortening
eggs
sugar
flour
baking powder
salt
vanilla
pecans
directions:
melt chocolate chips and shortening in pan over hot water. beat eggs and sugar.
add flour, baking powder and salt.
add chocolate mixture, vanilla and pecans.
pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
cool before cutting.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
carrots
onion
green pepper
tomato soup
sugar
mustard
salt
oil
vinegar
directions:
scrape and slice carrots.
boil in salt water until tender. do not overcook.
drain and cool.
mix remaining ingredients.
add to carrots.
mix well.
cover and refrigerate overnight.
keeps well for several days.
may be reheated or served cold.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
onions
parsley
light brown sugar
cider vinegar
nutmeg
pepper
salt
directions:
boil potatoes in their skins, peel and slice fairly thin; meanwhile, in a 10-inch skillet slowly cook the bacon (in 2 batches) until crisp; drain on brown paper, crumble and keep warm, reserve bacon fat.
return 3 tablespoons of fat to skillet; add the onion and cook gently until wilted.
add parsley, sugar, vinegar, pepper and nutmeg.
stir well and heat; add hot potatoes; mix well. mix in the bacon and salt.
serve at once.
makes 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crisco
sugar
eggs
buttermilk
flour
salt
soda
vanilla
directions:
mix shortening, sugar and eggs alternately putting in flour and buttermilk.
grease and flour middle and bottom of pan.
bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg
oil
unsweetened applesauce
flour
soda
baking powder
nutmeg
cinnamon
raisins
directions:
beat all together.
spoon in muffin pan.
bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tart apples
granulated nutrasweet
cinnamon
nutmeg
flour
directions:
peel, core and slice apples.
(you can leave half unpeeled, if desired; this leaves more fiber.)
mix in small bowl the flour, sweetener and spices.
put sliced apples and dry ingredients in a plastic bag.
mix thoroughly until all apple slices are coated.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
sugar
egg
vanilla extract
mashed ripe bananas
flour
baking powder
baking soda
salt
baking cocoa
directions:
in mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
add egg and vanilla; beat until thoroughly combined.
blend in the bananas.
combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
add to creamed mixture and mix well.
divide batter in half.
add cocoa to half.
spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
spoon remaining batter on top and swirl with a knife.
bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until the bars test done.
cool.
yields 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
parmesan cheese
garlic salt
italian herb seasoning
paprika
freshly popped popcorn
directions:
combine parmesan cheese, garlic salt, herb seasoning and paprika in a small bowl; mix well.
sprinkle mixture over popcorn, tossing until evenly coated.
store in airtight container.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
ro-tel
green peas
vermicelli noodles
worcestershire sauce
directions:
cook chicken in water.
remove and cut up.
add noodles to chicken broth.
cook just until tender.
add melted velveeta, ro-tel sauce and peas.
bake at 350° until juice is absorbed in an 11 x 13-inch dish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
salt
margarine
olive
onion
clove garlic
ground cloves
cinnamon stick
white wine
tomatoes
tomato paste
water
directions:
sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
in large saucepan, heat margarine and oil and saute chicken pieces, turning often, until all sides are lightly browned.
add onion and garlic and saute until transparent, but not brown.
add ground cloves and cinnamon and stir.
then add wine, tomatoes and tomato paste, diluted in a little water.
mix well with chicken pieces.
add the 2 cups of water; bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
stir occasionally during cooking.
taste for seasoning and serve with pasta or rice.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
salad oil
onion
salt
worcestershire sauce
directions:
marinate steaks overnight. turn several times. roll in seasoned cracker crumbs (to taste) and roast in oven at 350°. turn every 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
brown sugar
egg
vanilla
buttermilk
baking soda
salt
flour
rhubarb
directions:
blend margarine, brown sugar, egg and vanilla in a large bowl. mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl. put dry ingredients into margarine/sugar mixture.
add buttermilk.
mix well. stir in rhubarb. spread into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup white sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon. bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork sausage
velveeta cheese
bread
directions:
crumble and brown the sausage; drain.
stir in cubed velveeta and continue stirring until smooth.
spread on slices of french bread.
place slices on a cookie sheet in 350° oven until hot (5 to 10 minutes).
easy and delicious!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
butter
solid crisco
eggs
flour
salt
baking powder
vanilla
lemon extract
milk
directions:
halfway through mixing cake, turn oven to 200°.
cream butter, crisco and sugar; add eggs, mixing well.
sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
add the dry ingredients alternately with the milk, vanilla and lemon to the creamed mixture (beginning and ending with the flour mixture).
bake in a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
when cake goes in the oven, turn to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(you may need to cover cake loosely with aluminum foil the last 1/2 hour of baking to keep it from getting too brown.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
onion
clove garlic
bacon drippings
zucchini
soy sauce
directions:
saute onion and garlic in bacon drippings in skillet until golden.
add remaining ingredients and 2 tablespoons water. simmer, covered, for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender-crisp. yields 4 to 6 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
cornmeal
sugar
water
maple syrup
directions:
bring water to a boil.
add sugar and cook until it dissolves. remove mixture to cool for later use.
sieve plain flour and baking powder into a mixing bowl.
slowly blend in syrup and stir well to form a batter.
add cornmeal and mix well.
let mixture sit awhile. pour the above cornmeal batter into small greased bowls, 3/4 full. arrange them on a steamer.
steam them for 20 to 30 minutes until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
onion
celery
garlic
cream of mushroom soup
chicken broth
cheddar cheese
pimento
parsley
chicken
directions:
melt butter.
saute onion and celery.
mix everything together and top with buttered bread crumbs and paprika.
bake in a covered glass dish about 45 minutes at 350°.
serves 8 to 10.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes
green chiles
olives
onion
olive oil
vinegar
corn chips
directions:
mix tomatoes, chiles, olives and onion. add olive oil and vinegar.
serve with corn chips.
(or use canned tomatoes and blend all ingredients in a blender, leaving out oil and vinegar.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
oil
venison stew meat
onions
garlic
worcestershire sauce
bay leaf
oregano
salt
pepper
water
potatoes
carrots
flour
cold water
directions:
heat oil in a dutch oven.
brown meat.
add onions, garlic, worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, oregano, salt, pepper and water. simmer, covered, 2 hours or until meat is tender.
add potatoes and carrots.
continue to cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 to 45 minutes.
mix flour and cold water; stir into stew.
cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
remove bay leaf.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
oil
eggs
mandarin oranges
instant pudding
pineapple
directions:
mix
cake
mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges; bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
beat with mixer pudding, cool whip and pineapple.	ice cake; refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours before serving.
can top with coconut and nuts if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
graham cracker crumbs
butter
sugar
cream cheese
sour cream
eggs
directions:
mix together.
grease sides of pan.
bake for 1 hour.
leave in oven for 1 more hour with door open.
bake at 350°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
salt
pepper
mustard
egg
milk
vinegar
directions:
cook until thickened, then add 2 or 3 hunks of butter; let cool.
great for potato or macaroni salad.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green pepper
pimento
celery
macaroni
chicken
green pepper
garlic
bay leaf
salt
black pepper
mayonnaise
directions:
place clean washed
chicken
in
large	pot, cover with cold water, cut	up green pepper, garlic, black pepper, onions and bay leaf.
add	salt
to
taste.
boil until done.
remove from pot when done

salt
cayenne
directions:
in a small saucepan heat to bubbling (but do not brown) the butter.
into blender container put:
3 egg yolks, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, salt and pepper.
cover container and turn to low speed.
immediately remove cover and put in the hot butter in a steady stream.
when all butter is blended, turn off motor.
makes 3/4 cup.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white confectionery coating
sprinkles
directions:
line 2 large cookie sheets with aluminum foil.
over hot (not boiling) water, melt white coating, stirring frequently until smooth.
remove from heat.
while holding pretzel rod over saucepan, spoon melted white coating over pretzel within 1 inch of the top.
shake off excess.
sprinkle with nonpareils, colored sugars or sprinkles; place on prepared cookie sheets.
repeat with remaining pretzel rods.
(if coating becomes too thick, place over hot water or low heat.)
refrigerate to set coating.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
greens
bacon
red pepper
black pepper
sugar
salt
directions:
thoroughly clean greens and shred.
fry a few pieces of bacon in a deep pot.
add greens and stir constantly until greens are tender.
add red and black pepper and salt.
when almost done, add a little sugar to taste.
do not add water or overcook.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
vanilla ice cream
basket
milk
honey
directions:
mix all ingredients in blender.
blend until smooth and creamy. serve immediately in tall glasses.
makes 4 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
flour
buttermilk
oil
vanilla
soda
directions:
mix dry ingredients.
add oil, egg yolks, milk and vanilla. add stiffly beaten egg whites last.
cook at 350° to 375° until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
corn meal
flour
baking powder
salt
milk
vegetable oil
taco sauce
chili beans
green pepper
shredded monterey jack cheese
directions:
heat oven to 450°.
grease 14-inch round pizza pan or 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
sprinkle 1 tablespoon corn meal evenly into pan.
combine remaining 1/2 cup of meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
add milk and oil and stir with fork until mixture forms a ball.
press into the pan and shape edge to form a rim.
bake 15 minutes.
spread taco sauce evenly over crust.
top with beans, pepper rings and cheese and continue baking until cheese is melted.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
campbell's condensed golden corn soup
milk
broccoli flowerets
carrots
cauliflowerets
cheddar cheese
directions:
in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat soup and milk to boiling.
stir in vegetables.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
regular jimmy dean sausage
ground beef
oregano
velveeta cheese
worcestershire sauce
garlic salt
loaves
directions:
crumble ground meat and sausage; brown and drain.
add velveeta in chunks.
add oregano, worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
cook until cheese melts.
spread on rye bread.
bake frozen at 400° for 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
ground vanilla wafers
coconut
chocolate chips
pecans
coconut
milk
directions:
preheat oven to 300°.
melt margarine in baking pan.
add ground vanilla wafers top.
add coconut, chocolate chips, chopped pecans and a little coconut.
pour eagle brand milk over all. bake 45 minutes.
cool before cutting.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground chuck
salt
onion
celery
tomato sauce
homemade noodles
directions:
crumble ground chuck in large pot.
cover with water, salt and pepper to taste.
start cooking on high.
chop up onion and celery.
skim off excess grease.
take tomato sauce and dump in. rinse can with water and add to meat mixture.
let boil and add homemade noodles.
cook just until noodles are done.
soup will be thick so add more broth, sauce or water if you like.
this is delicious with garlic bread and cole slaw.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
brown sugar
cinnamon
yellow cake mix
sugar
pumpkin
milk
margarine
directions:
mix eggs, sugar, cinnamon, pumpkin and milk with a mixer for 2 to 3 minutes.
blend well.
pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
sprinkle entire box of cake mix evenly over the top.
then sprinkle with chopped nuts.
bake 1 hour at 350°.
let cool and serve cold.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
italian salad dressing
vinegar
sugar
salad oil
water
salt
pepper
carrots
cucumbers
green pepper
onion
directions:
combine first 7 ingredients.
stir in carrots, cucumbers, green pepper and onion.
cover and refrigerate overnight.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
salt
vinegar
sugar
mustard
miracle whip
directions:
cut eggs in half.
mash yellows, add all ingredients and mix. add more mustard to taste.
fill whites of eggs with mixture and sprinkle with paprika or a slice of green olive.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
peaches
sugar
eggs
flour
salt
vanilla
almond flavoring
milk
whipping cream
directions:
add 1/2 cup sugar to peaches and set aside.
combine flour, salt and 2 cups sugar and add to milk.
in a large saucepan, heat milk on medium.
beat eggs and gradually stir into milk.
cook on medium until mixture coats a spoon.
stir constantly.
remove from heat.
add whipping cream, peaches and flavorings.
chill in refrigerator, then churn in ice cream freezer.
makes 5 quarts.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
dates
water
soda
butter
sugar
eggs
vanilla
cocoa
flour
nut meats
cake
whipped cream
directions:
pour hot water over dates and soda.
cool.
cream butter and sugar; add eggs, vanilla, cocoa, flour and nuts if desired. sprinkle small chocolate pieces on top.
bake at 350° until toothpick inserted is "clean."
serve with whipped cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
frozen spinach
tuna fish
onion
lemon juice
butter
flour
milk
onion salt
mustard
salt
mayonnaise
directions:
cook and drain spinach.
make cream sauce of milk, flour and butter.
season with onion salt, dry mustard, salt and pepper. blend in mayonnaise and lemon juice.
place tuna fish, flaked, in 2-quart casserole.
add 1/2 of the sauce.
mix remaining sauce with cooked spinach and pour over tuna.
top with onion rings and bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
black pepper
salt
oil
eggs
yeast
directions:
mix ingredients well, let raise once.
roll out and spread with filling.
roll up and bake at 375° until brown, 40 minutes to an hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
bacon
beef
cream of mushroom soup
sour cream
almond slivers
directions:
halve chicken
breasts and wrap each half in a slice of bacon. cover the
bottom
of a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish with dried beef.
arrange chicken on top of this.
blend soup and
sour cream;
pour
over chicken.
sprinkle with almonds. bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
makes 6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
salt
hot milk
sour cream
mushrooms
butter
directions:
mash potatoes with milk and sour cream.
saute mushrooms in butter.
pour butter and mushrooms in a well made in the potatoes. cover with more potatoes.
dot the top with butter and bake for 30 minutes at 500°.
can be prepared a day before and reheated in oven or microwave.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crackers
peanuts
butter
sugar
light corn syrup
vanilla extract
baking soda
directions:
preheat oven to 250°.
combine crackers and nuts in a greased large shallow baking pan. in a saucepan, bring butter, sugar and corn syrup to a boil and cook for 5 minutes. remove from heat; add vanilla and soda. pour caramel mixture over crackers and nuts. stir well. bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
pour onto waxed paper and break apart; allow to cool. store in airtight container.
yields approximately 9 cups of snack mix.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red apples
lemon juice
celery
walnut pieces
mayonnaise
directions:
add all ingredients to large bowl and toss.
serves 4.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk powder
chocolate flavored
creamer
powdered sugar
cocoa
directions:
combine all ingredients in a large container.
store in a covered container.
to serve, combine 1/3 cup mix with 2/3 cup boiling water; stir well.
yields about 36 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
strawberry jell-o
cold water
boiling water
cranberries
orange
apple
walnuts
cinnamon
ground cloves
directions:
dissolve jell-o in boiling water.
chill jell-o until slightly thickened.
add all ingredients to slightly thickened jell-o. pour into a mold.
refrigerate overnight.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
salt
eggs
clams
clam juice
directions:
mix all together; drop by teaspoons in hot oil.
cook until golden brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
whole wheat flour
packets sugar
baking powder
yellow cornmeal
milk
egg substitute
nonstick vegetable spray
directions:
mix flour, sweetener, baking powder and cornmeal together. combine eggs, milk and oil; add to flour mixture and stir until just moistened.
pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground chuck
italian salad dressing
pepper
salt
onion
green pepper
carrots
worcestershire sauce
bread crumbs
chili sauce
eggs
garlic powder
catsup
chili sauce
brown sugar
worcestershire sauce
directions:
mix all ingredients together except the last 4 and shape into a loaf.
bake at 350° for 1 hour. remove from oven. top meat loaf with a mixture of the catsup, chili sauce, brown sugar and worcestershire sauce.
cook 1/2 hour longer, then remove and serve after cooling 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
baking powder
sugar
salt
baking soda
unsalted butter
low-fat farmer cheese
buttermilk
directions:
sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
cut in butter and cheese until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
make a well and pour in 3/4 cup buttermilk.
mix lightly with a fork to make a stiff but workable dough, adding more buttermilk if needed.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yellow cake mix
eggs
sour cream
instant chocolate pudding
water
kahlua
oil
chocolate chips
nuts
directions:
mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream, chocolate pudding, water kahlua and oil.
add chocolate chips and nuts.
bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bacon
pineapple
cheese
bread
directions:
spread both sides of bread with margarine or butter.
place on ungreased cookie sheet.
put two slices of cheese on each piece of bread; top with one pineapple ring and 2 slices of bacon.
bake at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes.
yummy and quick!<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
bread
corned beef
sauerkraut
mayonnaise
swiss cheese
margarine
directions:
place corned beef, then sauerkraut, mayonnaise and cheese on 4 slices of bread.
top with other bread slices.
spread butter on outside of bread.
grill in skillet or on griddle until browned and cheese melts.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
onion
cheddar cheese
oleo
salt
white
margarine
directions:
boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
cool and peel.
grate and mix with grated cheese, dip, melted butter, salt and pepper. pour in greased 9 x 13-inch flat casserole.
put 1/2 stick margarine on top.
cook until bubbly at 350°.
add crushed ritz, potato chips or plain crackers and lightly brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fruit cocktail
vanilla wafers
vanilla ice cream
directions:
place sieve over bowl.
pour fruit cocktail into sieve; drain juice into bowl.
put cookies in plastic bag; roll with rolling pin until crumbs are formed.
spread ice cream evenly in cake pan. place fruit on top.
sprinkle evenly with cookie crumbs.
let freeze about 1 hour and serve.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
flour
milk
eggs
pie filling
directions:
melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
mix milk, flour and eggs until smooth.
pour into pan over melted margarine.
spoon pie filling over batter.
bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cheddar cheese
cream cheese
sherry
chives
brandy
directions:
combine all ingredients in large bowl.
mix with wooden spoon or electric mixer until smooth and spreadable.
spoon into a crock and cover tightly.
chill several hours or overnight.
will keep 2 to 3 weeks.
makes 4 cups.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
salad oil
frankfurters
red
carrot
onion
garlic
celery
dry lentils
pepper
chicken flavor
directions:
about 2 hours before serving, in 5-quart dutch oven over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook frankfurters until lightly browned on all sides, stirring frequently.
with slotted spoon, remove frankfurters to bowl; cover and refrigerate.
in drippings remaining in dutch oven over medium heat, cook celery, red pepper, carrot, onion and garlic until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
meanwhile, rinse lentils in running cold water and discard any stones or shriveled lentils.
add lentils, pepper, bouillon, 11 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt to vegetable mixture in dutch oven.
over high heat, heat to boiling.
reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour or until lentils are very tender and soup has thickened.
return frankfurters to dutch oven and cook until done.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white sugar
brown sugar
white corn syrup
egg whites
boiling water
pecans
directions:
combine sugar, syrup and water; stir constantly until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling. cook to hard ball stage without stirring; remove from heat.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken strips
buttermilk
ground turmeric
salt
flour
directions:
wash
chicken	strips	thoroughly.
drain.
mix
ranch dressing mix and buttermilk.
soak chicken strips 2 to 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
water
mint leaves
tea
orange juice
pineapple
lemon juice
water
ginger ale
maraschino cherries
lemon
directions:
boil sugar with 2 quarts water for 5 minutes.
add crushed mint. cool and strain.
add tea, juices, and remaining water.
add ginger ale and cherries just before serving.
serve over ice and garnish with fruit slices.
yields 100 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green pepper
onion
meat
water
tomatoes
rice
salt
directions:
brown meat.
add pepper and onion.
cook until tender.
drain fat.
add tomatoes and water.
cook for 10 minutes.
add rice and cook slowly for 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
tomato juice
corn flake crumbs
egg
salt
pepper
onion
directions:
preheat oven to
350°.
combine all ingredients and mix well. press firmly into ungreased 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan. bake about 1 hour. let stand 10 minutes before slicing.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
shell
sugar
water
cornstarch
drops red food color
strawberry
directions:
cook sugar, water, cornstarch and food color until clear.
add jell-o and cool.
fill pie shell with whole strawberries and pour filling over.
chill and serve with whipped topping.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork
onion
green pepper
ketchup
pepperoni
barbecue sauce
brown sugar
directions:
mix all ingredients together.
bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
cocoa
salt
milk
butter
vanilla
directions:
line an 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil; butter foil.
in heavy 4-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and salt; stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full rolling boil, without stirring, to 234° or until syrup, when dropped into very cold water, forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water.
remove from heat.
add butter and vanilla; don't stir.
cool at room temperature to 110° (lukewarm).
beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
spread quickly into prepared pan; cool, then cut into squares.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
biscuits
apples
cinnamon
sugar
water
butter
directions:
pinch biscuits in half.
wrap quartered apples in half a biscuit.
place in dish.
sprinkle with cinnamon.
put 1 cup of sugar and water over dumplings.
cut up butter in chunks and sprinkle over dumplings.
bake slowly at 350° until brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
all-purpose
baking powder
baking soda
salt
ground cinnamon
pecans
zucchini
eggs
sugar
honey
vegetable oil
vanilla
directions:
combine first 5 ingredients.
stir in pecans.
shred enough zucchini to measure 2 cups.
combine zucchini and remaining ingredients.
add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. cool in pans 10 minutes, remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
lemon juice
water
sugar
blueberries
watermelon balls
grapes
nectarine
directions:
boil lemon juice, water and sugar; cool.
cut one large banana and put in mixture.
pour over fruit; put kiwi on top.
you can put cherries in the middle.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground chuck
onion
campbell's tomato soup
milk
crackers
green bell pepper
directions:
preheat oven to 350°.
mix all ingredients.
pour in baking dish.
spread catsup on top.
bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
cream of mushroom soup
mayonnaise
cheddar cheese
eggs
roll
margarine
directions:
cook broccoli and chop if needed. combine first five ingredients together and pour into casserole dish sprayed with pam cooking spray. crush crackers in hand and pour melted margarine over them. stir to cover crackers well with margarine. bake for 30 minutes at 350°. do not cover. serves 4 to 6 people.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
herb stuffing mix
cream of mushroom soup
cream of chicken soup
directions:
skin chicken.
boil unsalted.
cool and pull from bones. place layer of chicken in casserole dish, then a layer of stuffing mix.
dilute mushroom soup with 1 can of chicken broth.
spoon mushroom soup over layer of stuffing mix; use about half of it. then place another 2 layers.
spoon remaining mushroom soup. place another 2 layers.
let stuffing mix be on top.
dilute the cream of chicken soup with can of chicken broth.
spoon all on top layer.
it is best to add more chicken broth on the layers of stuffing for moisture.
cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
tomatoes
garlic salt
white vinegar
red pepper
cooking oil
directions:
blend all ingredients in food processor 30 seconds to 1 minute.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cornstarch
water
apricot
lemon juice
sugar
peaches
vanilla ice cream
directions:
in small saucepan, mix cornstarch and water.
add the jam, lemon juice and sugar.
bring to a boil.
cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes; reduce heat.
add peaches and heat through.
serve warm over ice cream.
yield:
3/4 cup.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
all-purpose
baking powder
baking soda
salt
butter
sugar
light brown sugar
egg
milk
lemon juice
frozen cranberries
walnuts
directions:
preheat oven to 375°.
measure flour, baking powder, soda and salt into a bowl; stir with a fork to mix.
cream butter until fluffy; beat in egg, milk and lemon juice.
stir in flour mixture; stir in cranberries and walnuts.
drop dough by teaspoons about 1 inch apart onto greased baking sheet.
bake 15 minutes or until firm and golden.
remove from cookie sheets to wire racks; cool.
yields about 8 dozen cookies.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
soy sauce
brown sugar
dry mustard
garlic
yellow mustard
directions:
mix all ingredients but chicken.
pour liquid in a gallon size plastic bag with zipper seal.
place wings in bag.
seal the bag to coat the wings.
place bag in 9 x 13-inch pan and marinate overnight.
pour contents of bag in pan and bake 1 hour in 375° oven.
after 1 hour, drain the liquid from the pan and bake for another 15 minutes.
remove and serve hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pumpkin
apple
raisins
pecans
sugar
lemon juice
directions:
wash and dry pumpkin; slice off top and reserve for top. scrape out seeds.
mix remainder of ingredients and fill pumpkin. place lid on pumpkin; place on a cookie sheet.
bake at 350° until apples are tender, checking for doneness at 40 minutes, although it may take up to 1 hour and 45 minutes, depending on size of the pumpkin.
casserole may be served hot or cold with roast pork, ham or poultry.
serve from the shell, spooning some pumpkin with each portion.
top with sour cream if desired.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
milk
nutmeg
vanilla
milk
whipping cream
directions:
beat egg well.
then add the rest of the ingredients.
beat real good with mixer, then add 1/2 pint of whipping cream.
mix on low speed.
can double recipe using same amount of whipping cream.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
butter
ground almonds
vanilla flavor
directions:
put all ingredients on a board and work together until the mixture does not stick.
form a large ball; cut into 4 pieces. roll each one in a long roll; slice 30 pieces from each roll.
roll each slice in a crescent shape.
bake in moderate oven at 350° until set but not brown (about 10 to 12 minutes).
take off cookie sheet and while warm roll in sugar.
yields about 5 or 6 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
coffee
powdered sugar
directions:
mix together and store in covered plastic container.
when you want to use, put 1/3 cup mix in cup with hot water.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chickpeas
grape leaves
onions
mint
parsley
scallions
lemons
rice
salt
directions:
fresh grape leaves must be washed and blanched for 1 minute in hot water to make them pliable.
combine half of the lemon juice with the chickpeas, onions, rice, scallions, parsley, mint and seasonings.
mix thoroughly.
place a generous teaspoon of the mixture on a grape leaf, veined or under side up.
roll from stem end, tucking in the sides.
place extra leaves at the bottom of the cooking pot to keep grape leaves from splitting.
pack the rolled leaves evenly and snugly over the loose leaves at bottom and add enough water to cover.
an inverted dish on top will help keep leaves from spreading.
simmer on top of stove for about 35 minutes or until rice is cooked.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
butter
water
vanilla
milk chocolate
nuts
directions:
put first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
stir gently over low heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
continue to cook until mixture is rather brown or a little, tested in cold water, is very brittle.
pour into a buttered, oblong pan (we use an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 7/8-inch pan).
while this is still hot (after about 3 minutes), place chocolate bars on top of mixture.
then, sprinkle with nuts.
when candy is cold, break into pieces.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fresh crabmeat
cream cheese
sour cream
mayonnaise
lemon
milk
worcestershire sauce
dry mustard
garlic salt
cheddar cheese
paprika
directions:
blend cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon, 1/2 cup milk, worcestershire sauce, mustard, garlic salt and 1/2 cup cheddar cheese.
add more milk if necessary to make creamy.
add crab and blend.
place in 2-quart oblong baking dish.
sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheddar cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika. bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, until crusty brown and bubbly on top.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream cheese
milk
confectioners sugar
chocolate
vanilla
salt
marshmallows
flaked coconut
directions:
mix cream cheese and milk until well blended.
gradually add sugar.
stir in chocolate, vanilla, and salt.
fold in marshmallows.
drop rounded teaspoons of mixture into coconut; toss until well covered.
place on baking sheet and chill until firm.
makes 4 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potato
cheddar cheese
milk
butter
salt
carrot
directions:
cut the cooked potato in half lengthwise and scoop the insides into a bowl.
mash in the cheese, milk, butter, salt and pepper, then spoon the mixture back into the potato skin.
warm for 2 minutes on high in the microwave.
decorate the halves with an extra sprinkle of cheese, then add carrot stick masts, red or yellow pepper sails and broccoli sailors.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
butter
potato chips
garlic salt
pepper
directions:
place pieces skin side	up,
not
touching,
in greased shallow pan.
sprinkle with
rest of melted butter and crumbs. bake at 375° about 1 hour.	do not turn.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
salmon
cream cheese
lemon juice
onion
liquid smoke
pecans
parsley
green onions
green peppers
salt
crackers
directions:
drain salmon and remove bones.
combine salmon with cream cheese, mashing together with fork until blended.
stir in lemon juice, onion, salt, pepper and liquid smoke.
mix well.

noodles
tuna
peas
cream of mushroom soup
milk
parsley
salt
directions:
cook noodles until tender, then drain. pour in casserole dish.
add tuna, soup and peas.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
veal cutlets
all-purpose
salt
pepper
garlic powder
butter
fresh lump crabmeat
green onions
mushrooms
worcestershire sauce
hollandaise sauce
fresh parsley
directions:

spoon crabmeat mixture evenly over asparagus.

yields 6 to 8 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
shortening
oleo
eggs
vanilla
milk
salt
baking powder
flour
directions:
cream sugar and shortening.
add eggs, vanilla and milk.
mix salt, baking powder and flour.
add to mixture and roll 1/4-inch thick.
cut with 2-inch round cookie cutter.
bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
these cookies will not be brown.
remove from pan while hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
n
milk
oil
directions:
dip potatoes in milk and coat with shake 'n bake mix.
salt to taste.
bake on cookie sheet that has 1/8-inch cooking oil.
bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
turn 2 or 3 times.
serve with sour cream or favorite dipping sauce.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of mushroom soup
cream of chicken soup
velveeta cheese
frozen vegetables
directions:
cook vegetables.
add to soup, milk and cheese.
heat until cheeses melt.
be careful as soup will burn on bottom easily. freezes very well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cake
eggs
vegetable oil
water
flour
chocolate chips
directions:
drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
bake at 375° for 8 or 9 minutes.
not a brown cookie.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pineapple
bananas
condensed milk
flaked coconut
pecans
directions:
mix all ingredients; pour into baked pie shell.
chill several hours before serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggs
sugar
milk
vanilla
coconut
butter
flour
directions:
mix all ingredients.
pour into an 9-inch ungreased pyrex pie plate.
bake at 350° until done.
you may omit coconut and have an egg pie.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
beans
bacon
directions:
fry bacon until golden brown and crisp.
then add the can of beans and wienies.
cook until piping hot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
eggplant
oil
tomato sauce
mozzarella cheese
parmesan
directions:
peel eggplant.
slice 1/2 inch thick and brush with oil. broil 3 to 4 inches from heat, 6 to 8 minutes, turning once.
heat sauce, spoon over eggplant and sprinkle with cheese.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fryer
onions
paprika
water
potatoes
salt
wide noodles
directions:
saute onions and chicken in hot oil.
add paprika.
add water to	cover
chicken.
add
potatoes,
salt and pepper to taste. simmer 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
when done, take chicken out.
take meat off bones and put meat back into the pan with broth.
cook wide
noodles.
add
to
broth.
serve with sour cream
and vinegar.
(you may add a small amount of sour cream and vinegar to the pot, if you like.)<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cucumbers
lime
water
vinegar
sugar
celery
salt
mixed pickling spice
directions:
mix the lime with the 2 gallons water and pour over cucumbers. let stand 24 hours.
stir often, but gently.
stir these several times so the lime mixes with the cucumbers.
rinse well; cover with clean, cold water.
let stand for 4 hours; drain well.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
sugar
eggs
milk
flour
baking powder
vanilla
salt
directions:
mix all ingredients adding flour (cup at a time) last.
may require a bit more or less flour; dough should be easy to roll and not too sticky.
roll out to about 1/8-inch thick (don't make it too thin); cookies are supposed to be soft and fluffy, not thin and crusty.
place on cookie sheet, not too close together and bake at 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes, depending on thickness. when done, the backs of the cookies should be a very light shade of tan (not dark!).
remove from cookie sheet and place on a flat surface to cool.
after cookies are completely cooled, you can frost and decorate.
makes about 10 to 12 dozen.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
rice pilaf
mayonnaise
orange marmalade
sour cream
lemon juice
curry powder
chicken
red delicious apples
raisins
salad greens
almonds
directions:
prepare rice pilaf following package directions.
place in large bowl, cover and chill.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken breasts
chicken broth
cream of chicken soup
cream cheese
margarine
cracker crumbs
directions:
cook chicken until tender.
bone and cut into bite size.
mix broth, cream of chicken soup and cream cheese together.
melt margarine and pour over crackers.
mix.
layer crackers in bottom of baking dish, then chicken, then soup mixture.
repeat until all ingredients are used, topping with crumbs.
bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
egg noodles
peas
cream of mushroom
tuna
salt
pepper
green onions
celery
cheddar cheese
margarine
milk
water chestnuts
onion rings
directions:
cook noodles al dente.
drain.
combine noodles with all ingredients, except onion rings and cheese.
place in buttered casserole dish.
top with onion rings and cheese.
cover and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
soy sauce
salad oil
salt
ginger
garlic salt
sherry
honey
directions:
combine all ingredients, except wings, in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
arrange wings in single layer in marinade.
cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight, turning pieces once or twice.
bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender, turning them a few times as they cook.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
white chicken
cream of mushroom soup
cream of chicken soup
shredded cheese
onion
milk
green chilies
doritos
directions:
in a mixing bowl mix chicken, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup.
cut up onion in small pieces; add evaporated milk and 1/2 small can of mild green diced chilies.
mix all this together; set aside.
layer bottom of 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch pan with crushed doritos.
put shredded cheese over top of mixture.
cook for 40 minutes at 300°.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
mushrooms
butter
flour
chicken broth
light cream
parsley
salt
nutmeg
pepper
white wine
chicken
parmesan cheese
additional parsley
directions:
in a skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
stir in flour.
gradually add the chicken broth.
cook, stirring constantly, until sauce comes to a boil.
remove from heat.
stir in cream, parsley, salt, nutmeg, pepper and wine.
fold in the chicken and spaghetti.
turn into a greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
garnish with fresh parsley, if desired.
serves 6 to 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
bacon
onion
sugar
flour
beef bouillon
salt
pepper
vinegar
water
ground allspice
directions:
cook unpeeled potatoes.
in frypan, fry bacon until crisp. drain on paper towels, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
crumble bacon.
to reserve drippings, add onion.
cook until tender.
add sugar, flour, bouillon and spices.
stir until smooth.
stir in vinegar and water; bring to boil.
peel warm potatoes.
slice and add to sauce mixture with bacon.
toss lightly to coat.
serve warm.
makes 4 to 5 servings.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
soft shell tacos
chicken breasts
onion
green pepper
cream of chicken soup
oil
water
cheddar cheese
sour cream
directions:
cut chicken breasts into strips and saute chicken, onion and green pepper in oil until chicken is fully cooked. pour in soup and 3/4 cup of water. simmer for about 5 minutes. fill soft taco shells with mixture and roll them up. place enchiladas in a baking dish and cover with shredded cheese. bake at 350° until cheese is fully melted. serve with garnish (sour cream and salsa).<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
red leaf
bermuda onions
mandarin oranges
jicama
almonds
sugar
directions:
caramelized almonds.
over low - medium heat coat almonds with sugar until sugar coats almonds.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
margarine
sugar
flour
eggs
vanilla
salt
chocolate chips
pecans
directions:
melt margarine and mix sugar and flour.
add eggs, vanilla, salt, chocolate chips and pecans.
pour in unbaked pie shell. bake at 325° for 50 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
eggs
margarine
flour
buttermilk
baking powder
vanilla
nutmeg
directions:
cream sugar and margarine.
add eggs and flavoring.
add baking powder and soda.
add flour alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
drop by rounded spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
top each cookie with a raisin and/or colored sugar crystals.
bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
crabmeat
cream cheese
onion
horseradish
salt
slivered almonds
directions:
remove cartilage from crabmeat.
blend together cream cheese, milk, onion and horseradish.
gently mix in crabmeat.
add salt and pepper.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork chops
butter
salt
garlic
potatoes
cabbage
directions:
in separate pan, cook 1 to 2 potatoes per pork chop and 1/3 chopped medium cabbage until very well done.
remove chops from pan to platter and keep warm.
drain potatoes and cabbage; add to frying pan pork chops were cooked in.
mash potatoes and cabbage in drippings.
serve potatoes with pork chops and corn relish.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
brown sugar
shortening
eggs
milk
rolled oats
salt
baking soda
allspice
cinnamon
ground cloves
nutmeg
flour
raisins
nuts
directions:
cream sugar and shortening.
add eggs and milk.
add rolled oats.
separately mix all dry ingredients.
add all together. afterwards, add nuts and raisins.
do not grease cookie sheets. set oven at 375°.
drop onto cookie sheet and keep in oven about 10 minutes.
watch carefully.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
broccoli
eggs
oregano
tomatoes
parmesan cheese
cheddar cheese soup
directions:
cook broccoli in unsalted water 5 to 10 minutes until tender; drain. preheat oven to 350°.

bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

eggs
mushroom soup

mayonnaise
onion
oleo
crackers
directions:

mix all other ingredients, except oleo and crackers, and add broccoli.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

salt

egg
brown sugar

water
molasses
oil
cooking oats
apricots
raisins

directions:

spread in a pam sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

oleo
cheese
salt
mustard
cayenne pepper
worcestershire sauce
milk
egg
flour
directions:
in top of double boiler, melt oleo and cheese. when smooth, stir in salt, mustard, cayenne pepper and worcestershire sauce. slowly stir in milk. when smooth and hot, turn off heat. quickly stir in beaten egg and flour. serve immediately over toast.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

sugar
margarine
orange juice
all-purpose
cinnamon
egg
whipped cream
directions:
peel and core apples.
combine flour, sugar and cinnamon; cut margarine into flour mixture with 2 knives or pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
brush apples with egg and roll in flour mixture.
place in greased baking dish.
fill cavities of apples with any remaining flour mixture.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cucumber
onion
green peas
salt
pepper
mayonnaise
directions:
add cucumbers, peas and onion in bowl.
add salt and pepper to taste.
mix well with mayonnaise.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

instant coconut pie filling
directions:
in medium bowl, mix the 3 boxes of instant pie filling with the half and half.
add 1 teaspoon coconut extract.
beat according to directions on the box.
in large bowl, cream the cheese and gradually add powdered sugar (a full cup makes it sweeter).
add 1 teaspoon extract and the whipped topping.
blend the pie filling mixture with the cream cheese.
stir in coconut. divide among the 3 crusts.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
potatoes
onion
cheese
flour
milk
salt
directions:
layer potatoes, onions, cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
add milk.
layer into 2 layers.
put remaining cheese on top.
bake at 350° for 45 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
milk
flour
butter
sugar
vanilla
directions:
blend milk and flour.
cook to a thick paste in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until all mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball on the spoon.
cool.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
chicken
pineapple
sugar
pepper
garlic powder
ginger
oil
soy sauce
water
honey
balsamic
bread crumbs
olive oil
fresh boneless
directions:

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
macaroni
ground beef
onion
bell pepper
corn
tomato paste
water
salt
directions:

prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on package.
brown beef, onion and bell pepper.

bake 15 to 20 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

vanilla
directions:
in a small bowl, mix the cream cheese and sugar together until fluffy.
in a large bowl, mix the milk, vanilla and pudding together until fluffy.

fold in cool whip.
chill for 7 hours.
remove middles from 10 cookies, then chop into fine powder.
use these for top layer.
chop centers and rest of cookies to fine powder. layer cookies and cool whip mixture in a flowerpot, starting with cookies.
add flower.
keep cool until serving.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
fryer
celery soup
chicken stock
oleo
flour
salt
pepper
milk
directions:
cut up meat in pieces.
place in a greased casserole dish. mix together celery soup and chicken stock; bring to a boil.
pour mixture over chicken.
next, mix together oleo, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
beat until smooth and pour over chicken.
bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
ground beef
brown gravy mix
water
onion
onion powder
garlic powder
directions:
in
a
mixing
bowl,
combine
ground beef, one package brown gravy mix, 1/2 cup water, onion, onion powder and garlic powder. shape
in
6
or
8 patties and place in pan at least 1-inch deep;
broil
in oven, turning to brown on both sides. when browned,
combine
remaining package of gravy mix with 2 cups
of hot
water;
pour
over patties after they have been drained of grease.
place in oven again and turn heat to 450° (425°
glass). when gravy begins to boil, leave in oven until it
thickens a little, about 10 minutes depending on pan size. serves 6 to 8.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
collard greens
ham hocks
directions:
pick leaves off stems.
throw stems away.
cut up leaves; wash.
wash ham hocks.
put ham hocks in 3-quart pot full of water.
cook ham hocks until tender.
put greens in with ham hocks.
salt to taste.
cook until leaves are soft.
serve with southern fried cornbread.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
yeast
cottage cheese
butter
sugar
onion
dill
salt
baking soda
egg
flour
directions:
combine all ingredients except flour.
mix thoroughly (not with mixer).
add flour gradually.
cover and let rise about 1 hour in a warm place.
punch down; put in greased small loaf pans or casserole dish.
let rise, covered, 30 to 40 minutes.
bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
recipe can be doubled, but use 9 x 13-inch pan.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
sugar
mayonnaise
flour
water
baking soda
cocoa
vanilla
directions:
mix mayonnaise and sugar until blended.
sift dry ingredients and add alternately with water.
add vanilla and blend until smooth.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

margarine
pecans

directions:
mix all ingredients well, including pineapple juice; mash together and put into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:

directions:
heat oven to 375°.
combine flours, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until it is smooth, 2 or 3 minutes.
shape the dough into a round loaf and, using a sharp knife, slash a large x 1/4-inch deep across the top. place loaf on a lightly greased baking sheet and bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until the bottom of the loaf sounds hollow when tapped.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
green onions
cabbage
bell pepper
frozen peas
sunflower nuts
almonds
chicken flavored ramen noodles
sugar
vinegar
oil
black pepper
salt
directions:
break up uncooked noodles.
add onions, cabbage, green pepper, frozen peas and nuts.
mix together flavor packet from noodles, sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper and salt.
pour over cabbage mixture. mix and let set 24 hours in refrigerator.
mix and serve.
easy to make, tastes good and serves a lot.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
strawberry jello
frozen strawberries
sugar
salt

whipping cream
directions:
dissolve the jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water. stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt. cool until it begins to thicken. fold in whipped cream. cover bottom of a 9-inch pan with 1/2 of the torn pieces of cake.
pour over half of the strawberry cream mixture. add another layer of remaining cake pieces and pour remaining strawberry cream mixture on top. refrigerate at least 4 hours.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
orange juice concentrate
eggs
pumpkin puree
butter
sour cream
orange
honey
unbleached white flour
baking soda
baking powder
salt
directions:
mix orange juice, eggs, pumpkin puree, butter, sour cream and orange zest until well blended.
mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
add wet mixture to dry mixture.
stir gently until dry ingredients are moistened, but avoid overmixing.
bake in oiled muffin tins at 350° until golden brown on top, approximately 25 minutes.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
caramels
parkay margarine
cold water
rice krispies
directions:
microwave caramels, margarine and water in glass bowl on high for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until smooth, stirring every minute.
pour cereal; toss until well coated.
press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
let stand until firm.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
pork chops
mustard
butter
onion
flour
pet milk
directions:

melt butter and fry chops until brown and mustard starts to fall off.
saute onion in reserve butter.
add flour and stir until thin and brown.
pour in milk.
stir until thick; add water if necessary.
add chops and simmer for 1 hour.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
cream of broccoli soup
milk
soy sauce
pepper
frozen broccoli
onions
directions:
cook and drain broccoli.
in a shallow baking dish combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
stir in broccoli and 1/2 can of the onions.
bake at 350° for 25 minutes; top with remaining onions.
bake 5 minutes more.<|endofrecipe|>

<|startofrecipe|>ingredients:
flour
sugar
milk
eggs
vegetable oil
powdered sugar
funnel
directions:
combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl, beating until smooth. heat 1/4 inch oil to 375° in a skillet.
cover bottom opening of funnel with finger.
pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
